re/article writing lesson discussion from March 20\n- **NOT FOUND** in session files despite multiple search approaches\n- Root cause: Multiple context crashes on March 19-20 due to token limits\n- **X version of post 001** was never created (noted at 11:50 SAST March 20 before crash)\n- User frustrated: \"we were about to start something yesterday and there is also at least 1 task I did not complete\"\n- Lesson: Session file extraction works but content may be lost or stored in non-text formats during crashes\n\n## 30-Minute Sprint Check-in (2026-03-21 11:52 SAST)\n\n- Reminder received and handled internally\n- Current focus: Resolving lost session data / finding NurseSphere discussion\n- RAG status unchanged from prior: Core RAG complete, Task 3 pending new content\n- No new Nava articles detected for ingestion\n\n## Confirmed Incomplete Tasks (2026-03-21 12:00 SAST)\n\nUser confirmed two pending tasks that didn't get done due to context crashes:\n1. **X version of post 001** — LinkedIn post 001 was ready, X derivative was never created\n2. **Article writing lesson** — User was about to teach how they write articles, session crashed before it started\n\nThese are now officially recorded as pending work.\n\n## Split Brain Root Cause Identified (2026-03-21 12:05 SAST)\n\nFound in TinyBackUp/20260320 config:\n```json\n\"session\": {\n  \"scope\": \"global\",\n  \"dmScope\": \"main\"\n}\n```\nThis configuration caused WhatsApp to have its own session scope while TUI used \"main\" — they never synced context. The fix was setting \"scope\": \"global\" in config.\n\n## 30-Minute Sprint Check-in (2026-03-21 12:50 SAST)\n\n**RAG Project Status:**\n- Core RAG: ✅ Complete (March 17)\n- Task 3 (Ingestion): ⏳ Pending — no new Nava articles detected for re-ingestion\n- Voice note transcription: ⏳ Pending\n\n**Current Blocker:** Compaction failing (73%/60k timeout) — session context bloated\n- Need: Manual compact or gateway restart to recover\n\n**Priority Queue:**\n- Post 001