{"type":"message","id":"33f41794","parentId":"c4edad35","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:15:50.669Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_25861edc-4f52-4f53-9074-63f004c20a83","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== LINKEDIN: header + first 500 chars after first header ===\n## LI01\n\n**Date:** 2025-08-13\n\n**Author:** Yosef Boston\n\n**File:** Screenshot 2026-03-22 162333.png\n\n\n**Full Text:**\n\nBy Yosef Boston • 8/13/2025\n\nNava Healthcare Recruitment reposted this\n\nNAVA\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\n355 followers\n7mo • \n\n🚩 The Hidden Cost of “Wait-and-See” Hiring | 📍 Healthcare Staffing\nWhen hospitals wait until they feel the pain of a staffing gap, it’s already too late.\n\n⏰ Schedule gaps lead to burnout\n🔥 Perks? None. Only losses in safety, revenue & morale\n\n💡 What You’ll Learn in Part 1 of Our New Blog Series:\n🟥 Why reactive recruitment always backfires\n🏥 How it leads to open beds, missed revenue, and attrition\n⚠️ The cascading impact on patient safety and team morale\n\n✅ Who Should Read This?\nHealthcare leaders, HR teams, and anyone still relying on outdated, just-in-time staffing models.\n\n📌 This is the first of a 10-part series unpacking the true costs and solutions of broken staffing systems.\n\n👉 Read it here → https://lnkd.in/dVJANuRz\n\n#HealthcareStaffing #RecruitmentStrategy #WorkforcePlanning\n#HospitalOperations\n\n1. Counting the Costs: Why Reactive Recruitment Fails\nMedical Staffing Strategies\nnavahc.com\n\n\n---\n\n## LI02\n\n=== X: header + first 500 chars after first header ===\n## X144427\n## X144450\n## X144524\n## X144546\n## X144602\n## X144612\n## X144628\n## X144637\n## X144657\n## X144715\n## X144843\n## X144855\n## X144930\n## X144940\n\n=== File sizes ===\n-rw-rw-r-- 1 tiny4lurv tiny4lurv 16K Mar 22 18:34 /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/facebook-posts.md\n-rw-rw-r-- 1 tiny4lurv tiny4lurv 48K Mar 22 18:33 /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/linkedin-posts.m