{"type":"message","id":"82d5dba8","parentId":"33f41794","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:15:56.320Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_503ae377-4d6d-4837-82f6-d0ab1cd98d84","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check paired corpus has actual content, and show full sample entries\necho \"=== PAIRED CORPUS: first complete entry ===\" && awk '/^## X01 — \"Crisis/,/^## X02/' ~/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/x-linkedin-paired-corpus.md | head -60\necho \"\"\necho \"=== LINKEDIN: sample entry (LI07 - has author attribution) ===\" && awk '/^## LI07/,/^## LI08/' ~/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/linkedin-posts.md | head -60"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":32201,"output":189,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32390,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1774239356320}}
{"type":"message","id":"1d7aca08","parentId":"82d5dba8","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:15:56.339Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_503ae377-4d6d-4837-82f6-d0ab1cd98d84","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== PAIRED CORPUS: first complete entry ===\n## X01 — \"Crisis by Design Part 1: This Is Fine\"\n**Date:** 2025-09-08\n**Platform:** X (Twitter)\n**Meme:** \"This Is Fine\" dog in burning room\n**Full Text:**\nThe US healthcare system is short approximately 200,000 nurses. And yet, every year, hospital boards approve miserly 2-3% raises.\n\nAsk them why and they'll say \"our hands are tied.\"\n\nThey are not wrong.\n\nBut the fire keeps growing.\n\nPart 2 ↓\n\n---\n\n## X02 — \"Crisis by Design Part 1 cont.\"\n\n=== LINKEDIN: sample entry (LI07 - has author attribution) ===\n## LI07\n\n**Date:** 2025-09-25\n\n**Author:** Yosef Boston\n\n**File:** Screenshot 2026-03-22 162114.png\n\n\n**Full Text:**\n\nBy Yosef Roston - 9/25/2025\n\nNAVA Healthcare Recruitment reposted this\n\nNAVA Healthcare Recruitment\n355 followers\nSmo • 🔗\n\n🏆 The High Cost of Misaligned Partnerships | 🇺🇸 United States\n🗓️ Schedule: When your recruiting partner’s goals don’t match yours\n💰 Perks: None - only risks to patient safety and quality scores\n\nCrisis by Design: A 10-Part Editorial Series on Systemic Failures in US Healthcare Staffing\n\n⭐ Part 5 of 10: The Architecture of Trust: Exposing Critical Failures in Healthcare Recruitment Agencies\n\nThis week, we examine a foundational flaw in healthcare staffing: the broken trust in the traditional recruitment agency model. A groundbreaking 2024 study reveals that heavy reliance on agencies often correlates with lower quality-of-care scores. \n\n⚠️ In this article, we unpack: \n1. 📚 Why the transactional “contingency” model is failing hospitals.\n2. 💰 The hidden costs of working with a misaligned partner.\n3. 🏗️ How to build a new foundation based on transparency, accountability, and shared risk.\n\nIt’s time to demand more than just resumes. It’s time to build an architecture of trust.\n\n📖 Read Part 5 → https://lnkd.in/dHhnYYGb\n\nStart the series on Part 1 → https://lnkd.in/dVJAnuRz\n\n[Image of a man in a suit with the text \"5. The Architecture of Trust: Exposing Critical Failures in Healthcare Recruitment Agencies\" and the website \"navahc.com\"]\n\n❤️ 2 💬 2 reposts\n\n\n\nLove 💬 Comment ↪️ Repost\n\nTell them what you loved…\n\n\n---\n\n## LI08"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":13,"aggregated":"=== PAIRED CORPUS: first complete entry ===\n## X01 — \"Crisis by Design Part 1: This Is Fine\"\n**Date:** 2025-09-08\n**Platform:** X (Twitter)\n**Meme:** \"This Is Fine\" dog in burning room\n**Full Text:**\nThe US healthcare system is short approximately 200,000 nurses. And yet, every year, hospital boards approve miserly 2-3% raises.\n\nAsk them why and they'll say \"our hands are tied.\"\n\nThey are not wrong.\n\nBut the fire keeps growing.\n\nPart 2 ↓\n\n---\n\n## X02 — \"Crisis by Design Part 1 cont.\"\n\n=== LINKEDIN: sample entry (LI07 - has author attribution) ===\n## LI07\n\n**Date:** 2025-09-25\n\n**Author:** Yosef Boston\n\n**File:** Screenshot 2026-03-22 162114.png\n\n\n**Full Text:**\n\nBy Yosef Roston - 9/25/2025\n\nNAVA Healthcare Recruitment reposted this\n\nNAVA Healthcare Recruitment\n355 followers\nSmo • 🔗\n\n🏆 The High Cost of Misaligned Partnerships | 🇺🇸 United States\n🗓️ Schedule: When your recruiting partner’s goals don’t match yours\n💰 Perks: None - only risks to patient safety and quality scores\n\nCrisis by Design: A 10-Part Editorial Series on Systemic Failures in US Healthcare Staffing\n\n⭐ Part 5 of 10: The Architecture of Trust: Exposing Critical Failures in Healthcare Recruitment Agencies\n\nThis week, we examine a foundational flaw in healthcare staffing: the broken trust in the traditional recruitment agency model. A groundbreaking 2024 study reveals that heavy reliance on agencies often correlates with lower quality-of-care scores. \n\n⚠️ In this article, we unpack: \n1. 📚 Why the transactional “contingency” model is failing hospitals.\n2. 💰 The hidden costs of working with a misaligned partner.\n3. 🏗️ How to build a new foundation based on transparency, accountability, and shared risk.\n\nIt’s time to demand more than just resumes. It’s time to build an architecture of trust.\n\n📖 Read Part 5 → https://lnkd.in/dHhnYYGb\n\nStart the series on Part 1 → https://lnkd.in/dVJAnuRz\n\n[Image of a man in a suit with the text \"5. The Architecture of Trust: Exposing Critical Failures in Healthcare Recruitment Agencies\" and the website \"navahc.com\"]\n\n❤️ 2 💬 2 reposts\n\n\n\nLove 💬 Comment ↪️ Repost\n\nTell them what you loved…\n\n\n---\n\n## LI08","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774239356337}}
