{"type":"message","id":"4f7860a0","parentId":"d4bad801","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:18:03.412Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_d2284f68-8ba4-4742-870e-2e0e5f714429","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== LINKEDIN LI08 (full) ===\" && awk '/^## LI08/,/^## LI09/' ~/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/linkedin-posts.md\necho \"\"\necho \"=== PAIRED X01 (full) ===\" && awk '/^## X01 — \"Crisis/,/^## X02 — \"Crisis/' ~/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/x-linkedin-paired-corpus.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":34070,"output":145,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34215,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1774239483412}}
{"type":"message","id":"87c43288","parentId":"4f7860a0","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:18:03.439Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_d2284f68-8ba4-4742-870e-2e0e5f714429","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== LINKEDIN LI08 (full) ===\n## LI08\n\n**Date:** 2025-10-11\n\n**Author:** Tiny Manyonga\n\n**File:** Screenshot 2026-03-22 162039.png\n\n\n**Full Text:**\n\nBy Tiny Manyonga • 10/11/2025\n\nNAVA Healthcare Recruitment\n355 followers\nSma • 🛡️\n\nThe most expensive staffing decisions aren’t the ones you make; they’re the ones you delay.\n\nReactive recruitment, a familiar strategy in many health systems, creates a dangerous “backfill spiral.” A single unfilled nursing role quietly triggers a chain reaction of burnout, increased clinical risk, and significant financial bleed that rarely shows up on a balance sheet until the damage is done. \n\nThis is more than a hiring problem; it’s a systemic liability. Before you can build a better talent pipeline, you must understand the true cost of inaction. \n\nThe first article of our 10-part series, *Crisis By Design*, breaks down the quantifiable losses in liability, turnover, and revenue. Read the full analysis here.\n\n[Image of a woman with her head in her hands with arrows circling around her pointing to: Prolonged Vacancy, Staff Reshuffling & Extended Shifts, Higher Costs (OT + Agency), Burnout, and Resignation.]\n\n1. Counting the Costs: Why Reactive Recruitment Fails Medical Staffing Strategies\n\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\n\n\n\nLike\nComment\nRepost\n\n\n---\n\n## LI09\n\n=== PAIRED X01 (full) ===\n## X01 — \"Crisis by Design Part 1: This Is Fine\"\n**Date:** 2025-09-08\n**Platform:** X (Twitter)\n**Meme:** \"This Is Fine\" dog in burning room\n**Full Text:**\nThe US healthcare system is short approximately 200,000 nurses. And yet, every year, hospital boards approve miserly 2-3% raises.\n\nAsk them why and they'll say \"our hands are tied.\"\n\nThey are not wrong.\n\nBut the fire keeps growing.\n\nPart 2 ↓\n\n---\n\n## X02 — \"Crisis by Design Part 1 cont.\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":21,"aggregated":"=== LINKEDIN LI08 (full) ===\n## LI08\n\n**Date:** 2025-10-11\n\n**Author:** Tiny Manyonga\n\n**File:** Screenshot 2026-03-22 162039.png\n\n\n**Full Text:**\n\nBy Tiny Manyonga • 10/11/2025\n\nNAVA Healthcare Recruitment\n355 followers\nSma • 🛡️\n\nThe most expensive staffing decisions aren’t the ones you make; they’re the ones you delay.\n\nReactive recruitment, a familiar strategy in many health systems, creates a dangerous “backfill spiral.” A single unfilled nursing role quietly triggers a chain reaction of burnout, increased clinical risk, and significant financial bleed that rarely shows up on a balance sheet until the damage is done. \n\nThis is more than a hiring problem; it’s a systemic liability. Before you can build a better talent pipeline, you must understand the true cost of inaction. \n\nThe first article of our 10-part series, *Crisis By Design*, breaks down the quantifiable losses in liability, turnover, and revenue. Read the full analysis here.\n\n[Image of a woman with her head in her hands with arrows circling around her pointing to: Prolonged Vacancy, Staff Reshuffling & Extended Shifts, Higher Costs (OT + Agency), Burnout, and Resignation.]\n\n1. Counting the Costs: Why Reactive Recruitment Fails Medical Staffing Strategies\n\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\n\n\n\nLike\nComment\nRepost\n\n\n---\n\n## LI09\n\n=== PAIRED X01 (full) ===\n## X01 — \"Crisis by Design Part 1: This Is Fine\"\n**Date:** 2025-09-08\n**Platform:** X (Twitter)\n**Meme:** \"This Is Fine\" dog in burning room\n**Full Text:**\nThe US healthcare system is short approximately 200,000 nurses. And yet, every year, hospital boards approve miserly 2-3% raises.\n\nAsk them why and they'll say \"our hands are tied.\"\n\nThey are not wrong.\n\nBut the fire keeps growing.\n\nPart 2 ↓\n\n---\n\n## X02 — \"Crisis by Design Part 1 cont.\"","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774239483436}}
