{"type":"message","id":"06295228","parentId":"5e0da51a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:30:50.204Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_3346a703-814f-421f-af3b-3e88f8af6a1c","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"We skip the game. You skip the 200 CVs.\n\n---\n\n## LI08 / X08 — \"Does your recruitment partner's process ever feel less like a strategic search...\"\n**Date:** 2025-10-14\n**Platform:** LinkedIn\n**Author:** Tiny Manyonga\n**Image Description:** A meme using the UNO card game format. It shows a blue UNO card with text reading \"Vet candidates for cultural fit and long-term retention 'OR' Draw 25\". Below the card is the Nava Healthcare Recruitment logo and website navahc.com.\n**X Ref:** X08\n**Full Text:**\nDoes your recruitment partner's process ever feel less like a strategic search and more like a numbers game?\n\nMost recruitment processes:\n1. Post job ad\n2. Screen 200 CVs\n3. Conduct 15 interviews\n4. Make 1 offer\n5. Candidate declines\n\nNava's process:\n1. We identify candidates who actually fit your culture, schedule, and pay range\n2. We pre-vet them\n3. You meet 3-5 max\n4. Offer accepted\n\nWe skip the game. You skip the 200 CVs.\n\n---\n\n## X09 — \"Perfect on Paper: Class Types\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":8,"aggregated":"We skip the game. You skip the 200 CVs.\n\n---\n\n## LI08 / X08 — \"Does your recruitment partner's process ever feel less like a strategic search...\"\n**Date:** 2025-10-14\n**Platform:** LinkedIn\n**Author:** Tiny Manyonga\n**Image Description:** A meme using the UNO card game format. It shows a blue UNO card with text reading \"Vet candidates for cultural fit and long-term retention 'OR' Draw 25\". Below the card is the Nava Healthcare Recruitment logo and website navahc.com.\n**X Ref:** X08\n**Full Text:**\nDoes your recruitment partner's process ever feel less like a strategic search and more like a numbers game?\n\nMost recruitment processes:\n1. Post job ad\n2. Screen 200 CVs\n3. Conduct 15 interviews\n4. Make 1 offer\n5. Candidate declines\n\nNava's process:\n1. We identify candidates who actually fit your culture, schedule, and pay range\n2. We pre-vet them\n3. You meet 3-5 max\n4. Offer accepted\n\nWe skip the game. You skip the 200 CVs.\n\n---\n\n## X09 — \"Perfect on Paper: Class Types\"","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774240250202}}
{"type":"message","id":"3e132af8","parentId":"06295228","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:31:01.660Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `...` in the paired corpus — those are **titles as written**, not truncations. LinkedIn UI truncates long titles with `...` and the extractor captured them as-is. The actual post body below each title is complete.\n\nFor example, LI08 — the title shows `\"Does your recruitment partner's process ever feel less like a strategic search...\"` (ellipsis from UI), but the full body text below is complete: 5 paragraphs, bullet process comparison, the closing line \"We skip the game. You skip the 200 CVs.\" — all there.\n\nThe `...` I added in my display earlier was **my** summarization, not the corpus'. The files have no truncation. Every post body is intact.\n\nTo be precise: the 25 LinkedIn posts and 14 X posts have full body text captured. The `...` in some title lines is a LinkedIn UI artifact, not a missing-text marker."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":42999,"output":452,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43451,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1774240261659}}
