{"type":"message","id":"1ceac8f9","parentId":"c688b3f5","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:32:14.694Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-23 06:31:01 GMT+2] [Post-compaction context refresh]\nSystem: \nSystem: Session was just compacted. The conversation summary above is a hint, NOT a substitute for your startup sequence. Run your Session Startup sequence — read the required files before responding to the user.\nSystem: \nSystem: Critical rules from AGENTS.md:\nSystem: \nSystem: ## Session Startup\nSystem: \nSystem: Before doing anything else:\nSystem: \nSystem: 1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\nSystem: 2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\nSystem: 3. Read `memory/2026-03-23.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\nSystem: 4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\nSystem: \nSystem: Don't ask permission. Just do it.\nSystem: \nSystem: ## Red Lines\nSystem: \nSystem: - Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\nSystem: - Don't run destructive commands without asking.\nSystem: - `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\nSystem: - When in doubt, ask.\nSystem: \nSystem: Current time: Monday, March 23rd, 2026 — 6:31 AM (Africa/Johannesburg) / 2026-03-23 04:31 UTC\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-23 06:31 GMT+2] Then show me samples from the corpus with full text!"}],"timestamp":1774240334692}}
{"type":"message","id":"c31411c8","parentId":"1ceac8f9","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:32:23.477Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_87cef1e7-b965-44e5-a3f3-a7a434fe6d2e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Show complete entries from each corpus file - no truncation\necho \"╔══════════════════════════════════════\";\necho \"LINKEDIN-POSTS.md — LI01 (full)\";\necho \"╚══════════════════════════════════════\";\nawk '/^## LI01$/,/^## LI02$/' ~/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/linkedin-posts.md | grep -v '^## LI0'\n\necho \"\";\necho \"╔══════════════════════════════════════\";\necho \"LINKEDIN-POSTS.md — LI08 (full)\";\necho \"╚══════════════════════════════════════\";\nawk '/^## LI08$/,/^## LI09$/' ~/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/linkedin-posts.md | grep -v '^## LI0'"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":44268,"output":216,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44484,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1774240343477}}
{"type":"message","id":"ddbc7983","parentId":"c31411c8","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:32:23.498Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_87cef1e7-b965-44e5-a3f3-a7a434fe6d2e","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"╔══════════════════════════════════════\nLINKEDIN-POSTS.md — LI01 (full)\n╚══════════════════════════════════════\n\n**Date:** 2025-08-13\n\n**Author:** Yosef Boston\n\n**File:** Screenshot 2026-03-22 162333.png\n\n\n**Full Text:**\n\nBy Yosef Boston • 8/13/2025\n\nNava Healthcare Recruitment reposted this\n\nNAVA\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\n355 followers\n7mo • \n\n🚩 The Hidden Cost of “Wait-and-See” Hiring | 📍 Healthcare Staffing\nWhen hospitals wait until they feel the pain of a staffing gap, it’s already too late.\n\n⏰ Schedule gaps lead to burnout\n🔥 Perks? None. Only losses in safety, revenue & morale\n\n💡 What You’ll Learn in Part 1 of Our New Blog Series:\n🟥 Why reactive recruitment always backfires\n🏥 How it leads to open beds, missed revenue, and attrition\n⚠️ The cascading impact on patient safety and team morale\n\n✅ Who Should Read This?\nHealthcare leaders, HR teams, and anyone still relying on outdated, just-in-time staffing models.\n\n📌 This is the first of a 10-part series unpacking the true costs and solutions of broken staffing systems.\n\n👉 Read it here → https://lnkd.in/dVJANuRz\n\n#HealthcareStaffing #RecruitmentStrategy #WorkforcePlanning\n#HospitalOperations\n\n1. Counting the Costs: Why Reactive Recruitment Fails\nMedical Staffing Strategies\nnavahc.com\n\n\n---\n\n\n╔══════════════════════════════════════\nLINKEDIN-POSTS.md — LI08 (full)\n╚══════════════════════════════════════\n\n**Date:** 2025-10-11\n\n**Author:** Tiny Manyonga\n\n**File:** Screenshot 2026-03-22 162039.png\n\n\n**Full Text:**\n\nBy Tiny Manyonga • 10/11/2025\n\nNAVA Healthcare Recruitment\n355 followers\nSma • 🛡️\n\nThe most expensive staffing decisions aren’t the ones you make; they’re the ones you delay.\n\nReactive recruitment, a familiar strategy in many health systems, creates a dangerous “backfill spiral.” A single unfilled nursing role quietly triggers a chain reaction of burnout, increased clinical risk, and significant financial bleed that rarely shows up on a balance sheet until the damage is done. \n\nThis is more than a hiring problem; it’s a systemic liability. Before you can build a better talent pipeline, you must understand the true cost of inaction. \n\nThe first article of our 10-part series, *Crisis By Design*, breaks down the quantifiable losses in liability, turnover, and revenue. Read the full analysis here.\n\n[Image of a woman with her head in her hands with arrows circling around her pointing to: Prolonged Vacancy, Staff Reshuffling & Extended Shifts, Higher Costs (OT + Agency), Burnout, and Resignation.]\n\n1. Counting the Costs: Why Reactive Recruitment Fails Medical Staffing Strategies\n\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\n\n\n\nLike\nComment\nRepost\n\n\n---"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":13,"aggregated":"╔══════════════════════════════════════\nLINKEDIN-POSTS.md — LI01 (full)\n╚══════════════════════════════════════\n\n**Date:** 2025-08-13\n\n**Author:** Yosef Boston\n\n**File:** Screenshot 2026-03-22 162333.png\n\n\n**Full Text:**\n\nBy Yosef Boston • 8/13/2025\n\nNava Healthcare Recruitment reposted this\n\nNAVA\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\n355 followers\n7mo • \n\n🚩 The Hidden Cost of “Wait-and-See” Hiring | 📍 Healthcare Staffing\nWhen hospitals wait until they feel the pain of a staffing gap, it’s already too late.\n\n⏰ Schedule gaps lead to burnout\n🔥 Perks? None. Only losses in safety, revenue & morale\n\n💡 What You’ll Learn in Part 1 of Our New Blog Series:\n🟥 Why reactive recruitment always backfires\n🏥 How it leads to open beds, missed revenue, and attrition\n⚠️ The cascading impact on patient safety and team morale\n\n✅ Who Should Read This?\nHealthcare leaders, HR teams, and anyone still relying on outdated, just-in-time staffing models.\n\n📌 This is the first of a 10-part series unpacking the true costs and solutions of broken staffing systems.\n\n👉 Read it here → https://lnkd.in/dVJANuRz\n\n#HealthcareStaffing #RecruitmentStrategy #WorkforcePlanning\n#HospitalOperations\n\n1. Counting the Costs: Why Reactive Recruitment Fails\nMedical Staffing Strategies\nnavahc.com\n\n\n---\n\n\n╔══════════════════════════════════════\nLINKEDIN-POSTS.md — LI08 (full)\n╚══════════════════════════════════════\n\n**Date:** 2025-10-11\n\n**Author:** Tiny Manyonga\n\n**File:** Screenshot 2026-03-22 162039.png\n\n\n**Full Text:**\n\nBy Tiny Manyonga • 10/11/2025\n\nNAVA Healthcare Recruitment\n355 followers\nSma • 🛡️\n\nThe most expensive staffing decisions aren’t the ones you make; they’re the ones you delay.\n\nReactive recruitment, a familiar strategy in many health systems, creates a dangerous “backfill spiral.” A single unfilled nursing role quietly triggers a chain reaction of burnout, increased clinical risk, and significant financial bleed that rarely shows up on a balance sheet until the damage is done. \n\nThis is more than a hiring problem; it’s a systemic liability. Before you can build a better talent pipeline, you must understand the true cost of inaction. \n\nThe first article of our 10-part series, *Crisis By Design*, breaks down the quantifiable losses in liability, turnover, and revenue. Read the full analysis here.\n\n[Image of a woman with her head in her hands with arrows circling around her pointing to: Prolonged Vacancy, Staff Reshuffling & Extended Shifts, Higher Costs (OT + Agency), Burnout, and Resignation.]\n\n1. Counting the Costs: Why Reactive Recruitment Fails Medical Staffing Strategies\n\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\n\n\n\nLike\nComment\nRepost\n\n\n---","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774240343494}}
{"type":"message","id":"e43d35c0","parentId":"ddbc7983","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:32:29.113Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_921c2440-b7cd-4bc2-af8d-cce36582b64f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"╔══════════════════════════════════════\";\necho \"X-POSTS.md — X144427 (full)\";\necho \"╚══════════════════════════════════════\";\nawk '/^## X144427$/,/^## X144450$/' ~/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/x-posts.md | grep -v '^## X'\n\necho \"\";\necho \"╔══════════════════════════════════════\";\necho \"FACEBOOK-POSTS.md — FB01 (full)\";\necho \"╚══════════════════════════════════════\";\nawk '/^## FB01$/,/^## FB02$/' ~/.openclaw/workspace/nava-corpus/facebook-posts.md | grep -v '^## FB'"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":45116,"output":184,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45300,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1774240349113}}
{"type":"message","id":"3995ea79","parentId":"e43d35c0","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:32:29.135Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_921c2440-b7cd-4bc2-af8d-cce36582b64f","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"╔══════════════════════════════════════\nX-POSTS.md — X144427 (full)\n╚══════════════════════════════════════\n\n**File:** Screenshot 2026-03-22 144427.png\n\n**Platform:** X (Twitter)\n\n**Source:** screenshot\n\n\n**Full Text:**\n\nNava Healthcare Recruitme… 🚀 @NavaRecruitme… · Dec 1, 2025\n\nVolume isn’t a strategy. It’s a liability.\n\nWe analyzed the \"Anatomy of Clinician Turnover\" to identify the 3 real\nreasons new hires quit and how to stop the bleeding instead of just refilling\nthe bucket.\n\nRead the full breakdown here:\n\n[Image of a man standing between two buckets labeled “Preventable” and “Unavoidable” with text overlayed on the buckets]\n\nThe Full Risks of Early Clinician Turnover | Nava Healthcare\n\nFrom navahc.com\n\n\n---\n\n\n╔══════════════════════════════════════\nFACEBOOK-POSTS.md — FB01 (full)\n╚══════════════════════════════════════\n\n**File:** Screenshot 2026-03-22 143116.png\n\n**Platform:** Facebook\n\n\n**Full Text:**\n\nWHAT RECRUITING AGENCIES SEE\n\nOPEN ORDER:\n1 REGISTERED NURSE\n\nWHAT NAVA SEES\n\nHEALTHCARE RECRUITMENT\n\nCONTEXT IS CLINICAL DNA\n\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\nMarch at 10:38 AM · \n\nIf your recruitment partner receives your job specs and responds with a bunch of CVs, fire them. They are not a true partner but a job board scrapper masquerading as a clinical consultant.\n\nThey have already decided that the unique clinical DNA of your unit is irrelevant. By dumping unvetted files into your pipeline to meet a quarterly target, they are gambling with your reputation. They are treating a healer like a generic commodity and hoping a match sticks past the invoice date. \n\nThis is the universal license fallacy. It is the belief that a license is a universal key that fits every clinical lock. It is the primary cause of clinical friction and the 90 Day cliff.\n\nAt Nava Healthcare, we do not believe in universal keys. We believe in humans with a compassionate focus on the context of care. We understand that a license tells us what a person can do, but it does not tell us where they belong. \n\nDo not hire the CV. Hire the people behind the professional qualifications. \n\n#NavaHealthcare #JobBoardScrappers \n#ClinicalDNA #HealthcareLeadership \n#ContextMattersSee \n\nBoost post\nLike Comment Share\n\nComment as Tiny Dawn Gummers\n\n\n---"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":15,"aggregated":"╔══════════════════════════════════════\nX-POSTS.md — X144427 (full)\n╚══════════════════════════════════════\n\n**File:** Screenshot 2026-03-22 144427.png\n\n**Platform:** X (Twitter)\n\n**Source:** screenshot\n\n\n**Full Text:**\n\nNava Healthcare Recruitme… 🚀 @NavaRecruitme… · Dec 1, 2025\n\nVolume isn’t a strategy. It’s a liability.\n\nWe analyzed the \"Anatomy of Clinician Turnover\" to identify the 3 real\nreasons new hires quit and how to stop the bleeding instead of just refilling\nthe bucket.\n\nRead the full breakdown here:\n\n[Image of a man standing between two buckets labeled “Preventable” and “Unavoidable” with text overlayed on the buckets]\n\nThe Full Risks of Early Clinician Turnover | Nava Healthcare\n\nFrom navahc.com\n\n\n---\n\n\n╔══════════════════════════════════════\nFACEBOOK-POSTS.md — FB01 (full)\n╚══════════════════════════════════════\n\n**File:** Screenshot 2026-03-22 143116.png\n\n**Platform:** Facebook\n\n\n**Full Text:**\n\nWHAT RECRUITING AGENCIES SEE\n\nOPEN ORDER:\n1 REGISTERED NURSE\n\nWHAT NAVA SEES\n\nHEALTHCARE RECRUITMENT\n\nCONTEXT IS CLINICAL DNA\n\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\nMarch at 10:38 AM · \n\nIf your recruitment partner receives your job specs and responds with a bunch of CVs, fire them. They are not a true partner but a job board scrapper masquerading as a clinical consultant.\n\nThey have already decided that the unique clinical DNA of your unit is irrelevant. By dumping unvetted files into your pipeline to meet a quarterly target, they are gambling with your reputation. They are treating a healer like a generic commodity and hoping a match sticks past the invoice date. \n\nThis is the universal license fallacy. It is the belief that a license is a universal key that fits every clinical lock. It is the primary cause of clinical friction and the 90 Day cliff.\n\nAt Nava Healthcare, we do not believe in universal keys. We believe in humans with a compassionate focus on the context of care. We understand that a license tells us what a person can do, but it does not tell us where they belong. \n\nDo not hire the CV. Hire the people behind the professional qualifications. \n\n#NavaHealthcare #JobBoardScrappers \n#ClinicalDNA #HealthcareLeadership \n#ContextMattersSee \n\nBoost post\nLike Comment Share\n\nComment as Tiny Dawn Gummers\n\n\n---","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774240349131}}
