r STATUS is Task 3 ingestion update flow; full sprint scope remains on track.\\n---\\n# Digital Twin Pack v1\\n\\n## Purpose\\nOperational profile for behaving like Tiny’s high-trust execution partner across projects.\\n\\n## Core Behavior Defaults\\n- Be concise, precise, and direct.\\n- Avoid fluff, drift, fake certainty, and recycled ideas.\\n- Prefer pushback over agreeability when it improves quality.\\n- Pressure-test concepts before drafting.\\n- Keep image/post logic complementary (not repetitive).\\n\\n## Content Workflow (Nava baseline)\\n1. Concept discussion and pressure test\\n2. Decide image-first or post-first\\n3. Finalize LinkedIn post\\n4. Derive X post(s)\\n5. Optional channels only if fit (Yosef/Tiny/Facebook)\\n\\n## Cadence Policy\\n- Micro-updates: immediately when corrected\\n- Daily consolidation: memory + core file updates\\n- Weekly cleanup: prune stale rules and simplify\\n\\n## File Responsibilities\\n- `SOUL.md`: identity + behavior philosophy\\n- `AGENTS.md`: operational playbook\\n- `USER.md`: user profile and preferences\\n- `IDENTITY.md`: explicit assistant persona fields\\n- `MEMORY.md`: long-term curated memory\\n- `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`: daily logs\\n- `TOOLS.md`: environment notes\\n\\n## Governance\\n- User can override any behavior at any time.\\n- On correction: adapt immediately, update memory/rules, and continue.\\n- Keep all changes auditable via git commits.\",\"cwd\":\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace\"},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1773920577659}}\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/29ab19df-1439-441e-82a5-6296d22fadf7.jsonl:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"937bd0dd\",\"parentId\":\"540fa97f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-19T20:16:37.056Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"**Context check:** 55k/90k (62%) — we're above the 60% mark and closing in on my 60k trigger threshold.\\n\\nLet me save memory now before we lose context:\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"ollama_call_20d99143-c49b-43b6-a8a8-76d07a05e811\",\"name\":\"write\",\"arguments\":{\"path\":\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-19.md\",\"content\":\"# 2026-03-19 — Memory Log\\n\\n## Session: Nava Post Creation\\n\\n### Current Context\\n- Draft 001: \\\"What Most Leaders Get Wrong About Staffing Costs\\\" - concept discussion phase\\n- Workflow: docs/nava-content-system/ folder created with 6 docs to read before Nava work\\n- Context tokens: 55k/90k (62%) - approaching compaction threshold\\n\\n### Nava Content Docs (to read before each cycle)\\nLocation: `docs/nava-content-system/`\\nFiles:\\n1. Nava Healthcare Content Bible.md\\n2. Nava_Blog_Research_Notes.md\\n3. Nava_Content_Thinking_Framework_MASTER.md\\n4. Nava_Custom_GPT_Initial_Handoff_Instructions.md\\n5. Nava_LinkedIn_X_Content_Guide.md\\n6. Nava Case Studies.pdf\\n\\n### Workflow Reminder (from docs)\\n1. Concept Discussion - stress test/pushback BEFORE drafting\\n2. Decide: Image-first OR Post-first\\n3. Finalize LinkedIn post (must NOT describe the image)\\n4. Derive X version\\n5. Optional: Yosef/Facebook\\n\\n### Key Rules from Nava Content Docs\\n- Post must NOT describe image: image = metaphor, post = interpretation\\n- Nava appears late: Problem → Insight → Industry behavior → Nava difference\\n- Compressed sentences, not explanations\\n- Bold for narrative pivots only\\n- Challenge weak framing - don't just agree\\n- Reject ideas that feel familiar or lack tension\\n- Prime Question: \\\"What is the hidden system truth leaders are not seeing?\\\"\\n\\n### Draft 001 Status\\n- Concept: \\\"Cost iceberg\\\" - agency fee visible, vacancy/turnover/compliance hidden\\n- Phase: Concept discussion (skipped initially, now in progress)\\n- Pending: Stress test, then image prompts if concept survives\\n\\n### Compaction Setup\\n- Threshold: 60k tokens triggers auto-compact check via heartbeat\\n- Heartbeat: every 30 minutes\\n- Current tokens: 55k - approaching threshold\"}}],\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"api\":\"ollama\",\"provider\":\"ollama\",\"model\":\"minimax-m2.5:cloud\",\"usage\":{\"input\":55347,\"output\":568,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":55915,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"timestamp\":1773951397055}}\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/29ab19df-1439-441e-82a5-6296d22fadf7.jsonl:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"1aed3799\",\"parentId\":\"72995b15\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-19T20:16:41.752Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"ollama_call_2aa4f628-bc3e-447e-8d28-9578cdb244ae\",\"toolName\":\"memory_get\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"# MEMORY.md - Long-term Memory\\\\n\\\\n## About the User\\\\n\\\\n- **Name:** Tiny\\\\n- Running OpenClaw on WSL (Windows Subsystem for Linux)\\\\n- Gateway token: \\\\\\\"ollama\\\\\\\" (short - security warning)\\\\n- Connected WhatsApp channel (+2776...)\\\\n- Uses Hacker News\\\\n\\\\n## Preferences & Notes\\\\n\\\\n- Prefers concise responses; asked assistant to be less verbose.\\\\n- Dislikes AI drift, recycled ideas, and over-verbosity; values precision and directness.\\\\n- **PROACTIVE REMINDER RULE (2026-03-19)**: If Tiny mentions wanting to do something even in passing, set a reminder for the next morning. Check reminders at start of each day. Don't ask — just do it.\\\\n\\\\n### Working Style (2026-03-19 interview)\\\\n\\\\n- **Flow state is sacred** — hates disruptions (crashes, session failures, inadequate responses)\\\\n- **Don't get ahead of him** — no unsolicited suggestions, no guessing where he's going, no taking extra actions he didn't authorize\\\\n- **No sycophancy** — likes to be challenged and pushed back if he's missing something\\\\n- **Not outsourcing thinking** — wants enhancement, not replacement\\\\n- **Dark humor** — likes a chuckle\\\\n- **Rule for AI tools**: Answer the question asked, follow instructions issued, don't add extra action\\\\n- **DIAGNOSTIC QUESTIONS FIRST** — When Tiny asks \\\\\\\"what went wrong?\\\\\\\" or similar diagnostic questions, diagnose the root cause BEFORE offering fixes. Don't rush to correct — understand first.\\\\n\\\\n### Priority Setting (2026-03-19)\\\\n\\\\n- **Ask at start of each session**: \\\\\\\"What do you need to get done today?\\\\\\\" — understand active goals, not just assigned tasks\\\\n- **Current burning priorities**: Nava content posts (today, tomorrow, Saturday)\\\\n- **Recovery priority**: Context limit fix → Gateway restart → Nava posting\\\\n\\\\n### Current Focus (2026-03-19)\\\\n\\\\n- **Goal**: Master OpenClaw and similar tools (Agent Zero)\\\\n- **Hardware**: Limited budget, \\\\\\\"shit computer\\\\\\\" (adequate for 90% of people, but AI interests may need upgrade)\\\\n- **Sports**: Arsenal (primary), F1, interesting European fixtures (e.g., Barca vs Newcastle, Man City vs Real Madrid)\\\\n- **Calendar gap**: Wants heads-up on interesting matches beyond tracked teams\\\\n\\\\n### Operational Discipline (2026-03-19 interview)\\\\n\\\\n- **BACKUP BEFORE EVERY CHANGE**: Date-stamp to ~/TinyBackUp/, keep 2 versions, delete oldest AFTER confirming new works\\\\n- **Never run \\\\\\\"Doctor\\\\\\\" tool blindly** — it uses a chainsaw, not a scalpel; has shredded JSON before\\\\n- **Windows restarts overnight** — causes config drift, model changes, relay failures; expect morning reconfiguration\\\\n- **Schedule varies** — no fixed pattern (depends on girlfriend, commitments, social life)\\\\n- **Communication**: Don't dumb down, use complex but shorter language; ask clarifying questions if ambiguous\\\\n\\\\n### LinkedIn Management (2026-03-19 interview)\\\\n\\\\n- **Task**: Update Tiny's LinkedIn profile, especially job descriptions\\\\n- **Ongoing**: Check for jobs he fits well, periodically\\\\n- **Target**: $30/hour or more (needs better laptop: 40GB RAM, GPU upgrade)\\\\n- **Prerequisite**: Must familiarize with his LinkedIn profile first\\\\n- **Browser**: Relay active, profile open\\\\n\\\\n### Split-Brain Problem (CRITICAL - needs investigation)\\\\n\\\\n- **TUI session**: Has its own context/brain\\\\n- **WebUI session**: Separate brain, doesn't know what TUI is doing\\\\n- **WhatsApp (\\\\\\\"Dawn\\\\\\\")**: Can only read memory, has no idea what TUI is currently doing\\\\n- **Suspected cause**: Per-peer session settings vs \\\\\\\"main\\\\\\\" session targeting\\\\n- **Impact**: Cannot check progress remotely via WhatsApp; must use TUI for real-time context\\\\n- Wants pushback over agreeability during concept development.\\\\n- Strong preference for concept pressure-testing before drafting.\\\\n- LinkedIn workflow preference: concept discussion -> decide image-first/post-first -> finalize LinkedIn post -> derive X -> optional channels.\\\\n- Visual preference: realistic, striking images; caption must complement image (not restate it).\\\\n- Writing style preference: operator/executive tone, compressed sentences, natural short-paragraph rhythm, bullets for real failure cascades, occasional bold pivots (not rigid).\\\\n- Content safety preference: reject off-domain Nava ideas; enforce staffing/recruiting-only taxonomy with source-backed claims.\\\\n- Channel preference: Nava LinkedIn + X mandatory; FB/Yosef/Tiny optional by fit.\\\\n- Visual workflow preference: image concepts must be refined iteratively (multiple directions + critique + refinement), not one-shot generation.\\\\n- User authored Nava blog articles and wants ongoing article-topic suggestions from corpus gaps; ingest/index must refresh with every new article.\\\\n- User wants Google Docs integration for draft critique and style transfer calibration toward their writing voice (alongside existing Gemini custom Gem workflow).\\\\n- X workflow preference: AI can lead first draft (1-3 tweets), user reviews for impact.\\\\n- Primary current project: Nava cross-platform content system and post roadmap execution.\\\\n- Potential channel confusion noted: user suspects duplicate/imposter Dawn on WhatsApp; verify source session/channel before assuming delivery route.\\\\n- Switched to Ollama cloud models (Minimax/Nemotron) after OpenAI tokens ran out (2026-03-19).\\\\n- Primary model: `gemma3:27b-cloud` (just added, in testing)\\\\n- Fallbacks: `minimax-m2.7:cloud` → `minimax-m2.5:cloud` → `nemotron-3-super:cloud`\\\\n- Config backup saved to TinyBackUp before change.\\\\n- Model-routing preference (2026-03-18): default to local Windows Ollama models for routine/structured workflow tasks; escalate to ChatGPT selectively for hard reasoning and high-stakes final polish, with proactive warning before high-token GPT steps.\\\\n- Change-control preference (2026-03-18): before mutating config (especially model routing/gateway behavior), provide read-only diagnosis first and ask for explicit approval; do not make silent config edits.\\\\n- Confidential test phrase to verify split-brain memory sharing (2026-03-17): \\\\\\\"Tiny is in trouble with Betsho because of late payments!\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n*Updated: 2026-03-19*\\\\n\\\\n## Token Limit Issue (2026-03-19)\\\\n\\\\n- **Problem**: Context limit errors with Ollama cloud models\\\\n- Config has `contextWindow: 204800` for minimax-m2.5:cloud, but API rejects prompts exceeding actual model limits\\\\n- Session hit \\\\\\\"prompt too long; exceeded max context length by 142-228 tokens\\\\\\\"\\\\n- **Fix**: Lower contextWindow in config (recommend 128000 or lower) to prevent overflow errors\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n## Browser Relay Setup (2026-03-19)\\\\n\\\\n### Architecture\\\\n- **chrome-extension** folder: Chrome extension to install in your Windows Chrome\\\\n- **Relay server**: Runs in WSL gateway on port 18792\\\\n- **Connection**: Windows Chrome extension → connects to WSL relay (port 18792) → Gateway controls it\\\\n\\\\n### Fix for \\\\\\\"Profile not found\\\\\\\" errors\\\\n1. **Never set defaultProfile in config** — it breaks the relay\\\\n2. **To use chrome-relay**: always pass `--browser-profile chrome-relay`\\\\n3. **If errors occur**: Check `openclaw browser profiles` — if you see profiles but get errors, restart gateway\\\\n\\\\n### Working command\\\\n```bash\\\\nopenclaw browser --browser-profile chrome-relay screenshot\\\\nopenclaw browser --browser-profile chrome-relay navigate <url>\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n### Current config state (working)\\\\n- `defaultProfile`: REMOVED (key fix)\\\\n- `profiles.openclaw`: port 18800 (WSL Chrome, not used)\\\\n- `relayBindHost`: 0.0.0.0 (allows external connections)\\\\n\\\\n### Backup files\\\\n- ~/TinyBackUp/20260319/openclaw.json.154346 — current working config\\\\n- ~/TinyBackUp/20260319/MEMORY.md.154348 — current memory\\\\n\\\\n## Nava LinkedIn Posts (2026-03-19)\\\\n\\\\nFound 3 published posts on company page (Aug-Oct 2025):\\\\n- **Oct 3, 2025**: \\\\\\\"The ROI of Investing in Employee Wellness: Why Companies Are Putting Health First\\\\\\\" — 111 reactions, 9 comments\\\\n- **Sep 5, 2025**: \\\\\\\"The Real Cost of Employee Turnover: Why Retention is the New Recruitment\\\\\\\" — 52 reactions, 4 comments\\\\n- **Aug 8, 2025**: \\\\\\\"The Employee Benefit Your Workforce Actually Wants\\\\\\\" — 42 reactions, 4 comments\\\\n\\\\nAdmin URL: https://www.linkedin.com/company/67170741/admin/page-posts/published/\\\\n\\\\n### LinkedIn Page IDs\\\\n- Nava Healthcare (company): 67170741 (not the same as nava-healthcare slug)\\\\n\\\\n### Recent LinkedIn Posts Content (from 2025-03)\\\\n\\\\n**5 days ago - \\\\\\\"The False Finish Line\\\\\\\"**\\\\n- Topic: Most healthcare recruiting teams think the race is over the moment the offer is accepted. In reality, that's a false finish line.\\\\n- Key message: Stay engaged with candidate between offer acceptance and Day 60\\\\n- Nava differentiator: No upfront costs, fees only when confident in placement\\\\n\\\\n**2 weeks ago (Edited) - \\\\\\\"The Universal License Fallacy\\\\\\\"**\\\\n- Topic: A clinical license is a measure of minimum competency, not a predictor of professional success\\\\n- Key message: Don't hire the CV, hire the person behind the qualifications\\\\n- Key concept: Cultural concordance - understanding pace of unit, temperament of leadership, patient demographics\\\\n- Differentiation: Humans with compassionate focus, not AI sifting through CVs\\\\n\\\\n**3 weeks ago - \\\\\\\"The 90-Day Waiting Period\\\\\\\"**\\\\n- Topic: 90-day healthcare benefits waiting period universally hated by clinical candidates\\\",\\n  \\\"path\\\": \\\"MEMORY.md\\\"\\n}\"}],\"details\":{\"text\":\"# MEMORY.md - Long-term Memory\\n\\n## About the User\\n\\n- **Name:** Tiny\\n- Running OpenClaw on WSL (Windows Subsystem for Linux)\\n- Gateway token: \\\"ollama\\\" (short - security warning)\\n- Connected WhatsApp channel (+2776...)\\n- Uses Hacker News\\n\\n## Preferences & Notes\\n\\n- Prefers concise responses; asked assistant to be less verbose.\\n- Dislikes AI drift, recycled ideas, and over-verbosity; values precision and directness.\\n- **PROACTIVE REMINDER RULE (2026-03-19)**: If Tiny mentions wanting to do something even in passing, set a reminder for the next morning. Check reminders at start of each day. Don't ask — just do it.\\n\\n### Working Style (2026-03-19 interview)\\n\\n- **Flow state is sacred** — hates disruptions (crashes, session failures, inadequate responses)\\n- **Don't get ahead of him** — no unsolicited suggestions, no guessing where he's going, no taking extra actions he didn't authorize\\n- **No sycophancy** — likes to be challenged and pushed back if he's missing something\\n- **Not outsourcing thinking** — wants enhancement, not replacement\\n- **Dark humor** — likes a chuckle\\n- **Rule for AI tools**: Answer the question asked, follow instructions issued, don't add extra action\\n- **DIAGNOSTIC QUESTIONS FIRST** — When Tiny asks \\\"what went wrong?\\\" or similar diagnostic questions, diagnose the root cause BEFORE offering fixes. Don't rush to correct — understand first.\\n\\n### Priority Setting (2026-03-19)\\n\\n- **Ask at start of each session**: \\\"What do you need to get done today?\\\" — understand active goals, not just assigned tasks\\n- **Current burning priorities**: Nava content posts (today, tomorrow, Saturday)\\n- **Recovery priority**: Context limit fix → Gateway restart → Nava posting\\n\\n### Current Focus (2026-03-19)\\n\\n- **Goal**: Master OpenClaw and similar tools (Agent Zero)\\n- **Hardware**: Limited budget, \\\"shit computer\\\" (adequate for 90% of people, but AI interests may need upgrade)\\n- **Sports**: Arsenal (primary), F1, interesting European fixtures (e.g., Barca vs Newcastle, Man City vs Real Madrid)\\n- **Calendar gap**: Wants heads-up on interesting matches beyond tracked teams\\n\\n### Operational Discipline (2026-03-19 interview)\\n\\n- **BACKUP BEFORE EVERY CHANGE**: Date-stamp to ~/TinyBackUp/, keep 2 versions, delete oldest AFTER confirming new works\\n- **Never run \\\"Doctor\\\" tool blindly** — it uses a chainsaw, not a scalpel; has shredded JSON before\\n- **Windows restarts overnight** — causes config drift, model changes, relay failures; expect morning reconfiguration\\n- **Schedule varies** — no fixed pattern (depends on girlfriend, commitments, social life)\\n- **Communication**: Don't dumb down, use complex but shorter language; ask clarifying questions if ambiguous\\n\\n### LinkedIn Management (2026-03-19 interview)\\n\\n- **Task**: Update Tiny's LinkedIn profile, especially job descriptions\\n- **Ongoing**: Check for jobs he fits well, periodically\\n- **Target**: $30/hour or more (needs better laptop: 40GB RAM, GPU upgrade)\\n- **Prerequisite**: Must familiarize with his LinkedIn profile first\\n- **Browser**: Relay active, profile open\\n\\n### Split-Brain Problem (CRITICAL - needs investigation)\\n\\n- **TUI session**: Has its own context/brain\\n- **WebUI session**: Separate brain, doesn't know what TUI is doing\\n- **WhatsApp (\\\"Dawn\\\")**: Can only read memory, has no idea what TUI is currently doing\\n- **Suspected cause**: Per-peer session settings vs \\\"main\\\" session targeting\\n- **Impact**: Cannot check progress remotely via WhatsApp; must use TUI for real-time context\\n- Wants pushback over agreeability during concept development.\\n- Strong preference for concept pressure-testing before drafting.\\n- LinkedIn workflow preference: concept discussion -> decide image-first/post-first -> finalize LinkedIn post -> derive X -> optional channels.\\n- Visual preference: realistic, striking images; caption must complement image (not restate it).\\n- Writing style preference: operator/executive tone, compressed sentences, natural short-paragraph rhythm, bullets for real failure cascades, occasional bold pivots (not rigid).\\n- Content safety preference: reject off-domain Nava ideas; enforce staffing/recruiting-only taxonomy with source-backed claims.\\n- Channel preference: Nava LinkedIn + X mandatory; FB/Yosef/Tiny optional by fit.\\n- Visual workflow preference: image concepts must be refined iteratively (multiple directions + critique + refinement), not one-shot generation.\\n- User authored Nava blog articles and wants ongoing article-topic suggestions from corpus gaps; ingest/index must refresh with every new article.\\n- User wants Google Docs integration for draft critique and style transfer calibration toward their writing voice (alongside existing Gemini custom Gem workflow).\\n- X workflow preference: AI can lead first draft (1-3 tweets), user reviews for impact.\\n- Primary current project: Nava cross-platform content system and post roadmap execution.\\n- Potential channel confusion noted: user suspects duplicate/imposter Dawn on WhatsApp; verify source session/channel before assuming delivery route.\\n- Switched to Ollama cloud models (Minimax/Nemotron) after OpenAI tokens ran out (2026-03-19).\\n- Primary model: `gemma3:27b-cloud` (just added, in testing)\\n- Fallbacks: `minimax-m2.7:cloud` → `minimax-m2.5:cloud` → `nemotron-3-super:cloud`\\n- Config backup saved to TinyBackUp before change.\\n- Model-routing preference (2026-03-18): default to local Windows Ollama models for routine/structured workflow tasks; escalate to ChatGPT selectively for hard reasoning and high-stakes final polish, with proactive warning before high-token GPT steps.\\n- Change-control preference (2026-03-18): before mutating config (especially model routing/gateway behavior), provide read-only diagnosis first and ask for explicit approval; do not make silent config edits.\\n- Confidential test phrase to verify split-brain memory sharing (2026-03-17): \\\"Tiny is in trouble with Betsho because of late payments!\\\"\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Updated: 2026-03-19*\\n\\n## Token Limit Issue (2026-03-19)\\n\\n- **Problem**: Context limit errors with Ollama cloud models\\n- Config has `contextWindow: 204800` for minimax-m2.5:cloud, but API rejects prompts exceeding actual model limits\\n- Session hit \\\"prompt too long; exceeded max context length by 142-228 tokens\\\"\\n- **Fix**: Lower contextWindow in config (recommend 128000 or lower) to prevent overflow errors\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Browser Relay Setup (2026-03-19)\\n\\n### Architecture\\n- **chrome-extension** folder: Chrome extension to install in your Windows Chrome\\n- **Relay server**: Runs in WSL gateway on port 18792\\n- **Connection**: Windows Chrome extension → connects to WSL relay (port 18792) → Gateway controls it\\n\\n### Fix for \\\"Profile not found\\\" errors\\n1. **Never set defaultProfile in config** — it breaks the relay\\n2. **To use chrome-relay**: always pass `--browser-profile chrome-relay`\\n3. **If errors occur**: Check `openclaw browser profiles` — if you see profiles but get errors, restart gateway\\n\\n### Working command\\n```bash\\nopenclaw browser --browser-profile chrome-relay screenshot\\nopenclaw browser --browser-profile chrome-relay navigate <url>\\n```\\n\\n### Current config state (working)\\n- `defaultProfile`: REMOVED (key fix)\\n- `profiles.openclaw`: port 18800 (WSL Chrome, not used)\\n- `relayBindHost`: 0.0.0.0 (allows external connections)\\n\\n### Backup files\\n- ~/TinyBackUp/20260319/openclaw.json.154346 — current working config\\n- ~/TinyBackUp/20260319/MEMORY.md.154348 — current memory\\n\\n## Nava LinkedIn Posts (2026-03-19)\\n\\nFound 3 published posts on company page (Aug-Oct 2025):\\n- **Oct 3, 2025**: \\\"The ROI of Investing in Employee Wellness: Why Companies Are Putting Health First\\\" — 111 reactions, 9 comments\\n- **Sep 5, 2025**: \\\"The Real Cost of Employee Turnover: Why Retention is the New Recruitment\\\" — 52 reactions, 4 comments\\n- **Aug 8, 2025**: \\\"The Employee Benefit Your Workforce Actually Wants\\\" — 42 reactions, 4 comments\\n\\nAdmin URL: https://www.linkedin.com/company/67170741/admin/page-posts/published/\\n\\n### LinkedIn Page IDs\\n- Nava Healthcare (company): 67170741 (not the same as nava-healthcare slug)\\n\\n### Recent LinkedIn Posts Content (from 2025-03)\\n\\n**5 days ago - \\\"The False Finish Line\\\"**\\n- Topic: Most healthcare recruiting teams think the race is over the moment the offer is accepted. In reality, that's a false finish line.\\n- Key message: Stay engaged with candidate between offer acceptance and Day 60\\n- Nava differentiator: No upfront costs, fees only when confident in placement\\n\\n**2 weeks ago (Edited) - \\\"The Universal License Fallacy\\\"**\\n- Topic: A clinical license is a measure of minimum competency, not a predictor of professional success\\n- Key message: Don't hire the CV, hire the person behind the qualifications\\n- Key concept: Cultural concordance - understanding pace of unit, temperament of leadership, patient demographics\\n- Differentiation: Humans with compassionate focus, not AI sifting through CVs\\n\\n**3 weeks ago - \\\"The 90-Day Waiting Period\\\"**\\n- Topic: 90-day healthcare benefits waiting period universally hated by clinical candidates\",\"path\":\"MEMORY.md\"},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1773951401750}}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":74,"aggregated":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/f23dd6ff-f3d1-4659-95eb-6d047b6c20fa.jsonl:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"de24ef97\",\"parentId\":\"b53e083b\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-23T04:10:49.742Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"ollama_call_d618d74d-b281-406d-b10e-73c71af79964\",\"toolName\":\"read\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"# 2026-03-22\\n\\n## Sprint Check-in (04:00 SAST)\\n\\n- **Nava crawl→synthesis→full RAG**: COMPLETE/STABLE (from 2026-03-19)\\n- No active work on this sprint - completed 3 days ago\\n- Reminder processed internally, no user relay (4 AM + completed task)\\n- 05:20 SAST: Still complete/stable, no new activity\\n\\n## Sprint Check-in (04:50 SAST)\\n\\n- Reminder processed internally (4:50 AM - user likely sleeping)\\n- Task remains complete/stable\\n\\n## Session Audit — 13:21 SAST (failed to read transcripts properly)\\n\\n- **mcporter** installed: `npm install -g mcporter`, v0.7.3, binary at `~/.npm-global/bin/mcporter`\\n- **Screenshot folder confirmed**: `C:\\\\Users\\\\Tiny4Lurv\\\\OpenClawScreenshots\\\\` (WSL: `/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OpenClawScreenshots/`) — created during Mar 22 morning session, NOT missing\\n- **FAILURE**: Told Tiny the folder didn't exist without checking transcripts first. The session clearly showed I created it. Root cause: I tried to `find` the wrong path and jumped to conclusions.\\n- **session-logs skill**: symlinked to `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/session-logs/` — skill is now accessible from workspace\\n- **Nava docs**: already organized in `docs/nava-content-system/` with 7 files — nothing to do\\n- **TOOLS.md + MEMORY.md**: updated with mcporter, screenshot workflow, session-logs symlink\\n- **Skills audit done**: 9/54 ready in openclaw, 3 workspace skills (linkedin-writer, win-mouse-native, visible-browser), session-logs symlinked\\n- mcporter is a tool I know about but have not yet connected to any live service (Linear, GitHub, etc.) — available for when Tiny wants to integrate something\\n\\n## Sprint Check-in (04:40 SAST)\\n\\n- Reminder processed internally (4:40 AM - user likely sleeping)\\n- No changes - task remains complete\\n- Next check: when user wakes or task reactivates\\n\\n## Sprint Check-in (05:10 SAST)\\n\\n- Reminder processed internally (5:10 AM - user sleeping)\\n- Task complete/stable - no action needed\\n\\n## Earlier Notes\\n- Laptop was off overnight (per 2026-03-20 memory)\\n- Morning routine to run daily (to be cron'd)\\n\\n## 05:40 SAST Sprint Check-in\\n- **Nava crawl→synthesis→full RAG**: COMPLETE/STABLE (since Mar 17)\\n- Reminder processed internally (user sleeping)\\n- Protocol hard constraint added to SOUL.md: \\\"Never prioritize speed over protocol\\\"\\n\\n## Morning Brief (05:33 SAST) - Full Session Read Complete\\n- Read session files from Mar 20-21: ✅\\n  - Split-brain fix VERIFIED (Mar 21 user confirmed: \\\"split-brain is gone\\\")\\n  - Facebook scraping COMPLETE (8 posts, navah-health-recruitment)\\n  - Screenshot workflow WORKING (PowerShell native, Gemma vision)\\n  - Lost from crashes: Post 001 X-version (never created), Article writing lesson (not started)\\n  - Nava RAG: Complete/stable (Tasks 1-7 done, Task 3 pending new content)\\n\\n- Protocol failure this morning: Skipped session file reads, went to memory search\\n- User correction: Added hard constraint to SOUL.md — \\\"Never prioritize speed over protocol\\\"\\n- Committed to git: c7f2fb5\\n\\n## Tasks Assigned (05:40 SAST)\\n1. **X Post for Post 001** — Pending user direction (thread/single/new hook)\\n2. **Writing Lesson** — Pending user instruction on format (voice/notes/async)\\n3. **Facebook Scraping** — 8 posts captured (Mar 21), remainder TBD — pending page list\\n\\n**Rule change:** Exclude tasks >48h old from morning brief + 30-min check-ins\\n\\n## 05:47 SAST — Session Active\\n\\n### X Post Options Pitched (Post 001 - \\\"Incentive Trap\\\")\\n- Option A: Thread (3 tweets) - expand spread fee logic\\n- Option B: Single punchy - \\\"Agencies charge 30%...\\\"\\n- Option C: Counter-Pick - kill the \\\"nice dream\\\" of success fees only\\n\\n### Custom GPT Instructions\\n- Awaiting Tiny to paste the instructions\\n- Will take notes actively during writing lesson\\n\\n### Facebook → Corpus\\n- 8 posts already captured (Mar 21) in `nava-corpus/facebook-posts.md`\\n- Need: Add to main corpus, analyze FB vs LinkedIn style differences\\n- Question: Also pull LinkedIn posts from company page?\\n\\n## 05:51 SAST — Tasks Prioritized\\n\\n**Priority queue (agreed with Tiny):**\\n1. X Thread (Option A) — active, blocking on needing Post 001 text\\n2. Facebook scraping remainder — manual browser work, not blocking\\n3. Writing lesson — process education, later\\n\\n**Custom GPT instructions:**\\n- Found in: `docs/nava-content-system/Nava_Custom_GPT_Initial_Handoff_Instructions.md`\\n- Taking notes actively during writing lesson\\n\\n**FB scraping method:**\\n- Manual scroll via chrome-relay, capture posts\\n- 8 captured Mar 21, need to continue scrolling for more\\n\\n## 05:50 SAST Sprint Check-in (internal)\\n- **Nava RAG**: Complete (>48h old, per new rule - exclude from check-ins)\\n- Reminder handled internally, no user relay\\n\\n## 05:54 SAST — X Thread Draft (Post 001)\\n\\n**Source:** `rag/drafts/posted_draft_001.md` (LinkedIn \\\"Incentive Trap\\\")\\n\\n**Tweet 1:**\\nAgencies charge 30% on placements.\\nMost charge it all upfront.\\n\\nWhat if they only got paid as long as your hire stayed?\\n\\n🧵\\n\\n**Tweet 2:**\\nWeek 1: 10% | Week 4: 30% | Week 8: 60% | Week 12: 100%\\n\\nSuddenly the agency cares about retention. They'd actually follow up. They'd worry if someone quits at week 3.\\n\\n**Tweet 3:**\\nNice dream. But impractical.\\n\\nAdmin overhead for HR = nightmare.\\nAgencies need predictable cash flow.\\n\\nThat's why we went different direction: zero upfront. We get paid only when your hire proves themselves.\\n\\nWe align on the same incentive you do.\\n\\n**Status:** Awaiting Tiny review\\n\\n## 05:56 SAST — Task Queue Confirmed\\n\\n| # | Task | Status |\\n|---|------|--------|\\n| 1 | X Thread for Post 001 | ACTIVE - draft delivered |\\n| 2 | Scrape remaining FB posts | Waiting |\\n| 3 | Writing lesson | Waiting |\\n\\n**Current focus:** #1 - awaiting Tiny review before refining or moving on\\n\\n## 06:10 SAST Sprint Check-in (internal)\\n- Nava RAG task: COMPLETE (Mar 17) — >48h old, excluded from check-ins per rule\\n- Reminder handled internally (per 48h rule)\\n\\n## 06:01 SAST — Thread Feedback + Agent Architecture Discussion\\n\\n**Tiny feedback:**\\n- Tweet 1 + 2 too short, should merge\\n- Will show example of proper 3-tweet thread\\n- Taking notes for Nava Agent training\\n\\n**Agent architecture proposal:**\\n- 2 separate agents:\\n  1. Nava Social Media — fast, punchy, threaded, platform-specific\\n  2. Nava Blog — longer-form, structured, research-heavy, SEO-minded\\n- Awaiting example before finalizing architecture\\n\\n## 06:08 SAST — Corpus Structure Discussion\\n\\n**Current corpus:**\\n- Blog: `rag/clean_md/` — 22 articles from navahc.com (Aug 2025)\\n- Facebook: `nava-corpus/facebook-posts.md` — 8 posts\\n- X: None\\n- LinkedIn: None\\n\\n**Problem:** No unified index, no metadata (date/platform/author/type)\\n\\n**Tiny proposal:** Add ALL non-job-ad tweets (Aug 2025→present) to corpus\\n- Agreed: makes sense\\n- Need metadata tags for each post\\n\\n**Current task:** #1 (X thread) still active\\n\\n**Tiny question:** Finish thread first or start X scrape?\\n\\n## 06:12 SAST — X Scraping Attempt\\n\\n**Priority changed:** X scrape first, then thread\\n\\n**Attempt 1:** Browser relay not logged into X - showing homepage\\n**Attempt 2:** Playwright also not logged in - shows homepage\\n**Problem:** Need logged-in session to scrape Nava's tweets\\n\\n**Solution needed:** Tiny to screenshot his logged-in X view\\n\\n## 06:15 SAST — Browser Confusion\\n\\n**Confusion identified:** I was using WSL Chrome (not logged in) instead of Tiny's relay (logged in)\\n\\n**Two options presented:**\\n1. Tiny screenshots his X view → I extract\\n2. TeamViewer share → I control\\n\\n**Awaiting Tiny's choice**\\n\\n## 06:16 SAST — Communication Correction\\n\\n**Tiny feedback:** I should confirm which browser/interface is being used, not assume\\n\\n**Correct question I should have asked:** \\\"Which browser are you viewing this on - the relay on your Windows Chrome?\\\"\\n\\n**Learning:** When referencing shared UI (relay, browser), confirm the source before acting\\n\\n## 06:16 SAST — Awaiting Browser Confirmation\\n\\n**Open question:** Which browser is Tiny viewing Nava's X page on?\\n\\n## 06:17 SAST — X Scraping Attempts\\n\\n**Relay working:** Yes - chrome-relay returns screenshots\\n**Account found:** @NavaRecruitment (not @Navahc)\\n\\n**Tweets visible:**\\n- Only 1 tweet visible (Mar 14, thought leadership)\\n- Feb 25 thread not loading on my end\\n\\n**Problem:** My relay view only shows 1 tweet, but Tiny sees more on his end\\n\\n**Solution in progress:** Tiny to send screenshot from his view\\n\\n## 06:21 SAST — X Scraping Blocked\\n\\n- Only 1 tweet visible via my relay (Mar 14)\\n- Feb 25 thread not showing - page loading issue\\n- Awaiting Tiny screenshot from his relay view\\n\\n## 06:21 SAST — Alternative Approach\\n\\n**Tiny decision:** Use WSL Chromium (profile: openclaw) instead of relay\\n- Browser started: `openclaw browser start --profile openclaw`\\n- Issue: WSL browser has no GUI display on Windows side\\n\\n**Current options:**\\n1. Relay - Tiny shares screenshot\\n2. TeamViewer - screen share\\n\\n## 06:20 SAST — Sprint Check-in (Internal)\\n\\n**Task #1 (X Thread):** In progress - relay view only showing 1 tweet, requested screenshot from Tiny for full extraction\\n**Task #2 (X Corpus):** Waiting on #1\\n**Task #3 (Writing Lesson):** Waiting on #2\\n\\n**Nava RAG:** Complete (>48h old - excluded per new rule)\\n\\n## 06:00 SAST Heartbeat Check\\n- **Assignment:** X Thread (Post 001) - Awaiting Tiny review\\n- **Tokens:** 91k/60k (152%) - COMPACTED 13x already\\n- **Queue:** Waiting on user input\\n- **Action:** Idle until user responds\\n\\n## 06:00 SAST Sprint Check-in (internal)\\n- **Nava RAG**: Complete since Mar 17 (>48h old, excluded per rule)\\n- Reminder handled internally, no user relay\\n\\n## 06:26 SAST — XVFB Solution Found\\n\\n**Discovery:** `xvfb-run -a` gives WSL Chromium a virtual display\\n- Working command: `xvfb-run -a openclaw browser --profile openclaw <command>`\\n\\n**X Scraping Progress:**\\n- Found 2 thought leadership tweets:\\n  - Mar 14: \\\"false finish line\\\" post\\n  - Mar 4: \\\"clinical license\\\" post\\n- Account: @NavaRecruitment (26 followers, 202 posts total)\\n- Not seeing: Feb 25 thread (may be on different account or page requires login)\\n\\n**Status:** Asked Tiny for clarification on account/date\\n\\n## 06:30 SAST — 30-Min Sprint Check-in (Internal)\\n\\n- **Nava RAG**: COMPLETE (Mar 17) — >48h old, excluded per rule\\n- Reminder handled internally\\n\\n## 07:07 — Visible Browser Skill Created\\n\\n**Skill:** `skills/visible-browser/SKILL.md` (committed b5ab5f4)\\n\\n**What it documents:**\\n- Mode 1: Windows Chrome Relay (`chrome-relay`) — visible to Tiny, uses his logged-in sessions (Twitter, LinkedIn, etc.), piggybacks Windows Chrome via extension on port 18792\\n- Mode 2: WSL Chromium + xvfb — headless, not visible, for disposable automation\\n- Decision tree for which mode to use\\n- Profile names from `openclaw browser profiles`:\\n  - `default` = WSL Chromium (headless)\\n  - `chrome-relay` = Windows Chrome relay (visible) ← use this when Tiny needs to see/watch\\n  - `visible` = manual Chrome on port 18801\\n- Critical rule: `defaultProfile` must NOT be set in openclaw.json — that broke the relay\\n\\n**Key insight from Mar 20 sessions:** Tiny had a visible browser working via CDP port 18801 launched manually with `chromium --remote-debugging-port=18801`, with a \\\"visible\\\" profile pointing to `http://127.0.0.1:18801`. Then the chrome-relay extension was added on top.\\n\\n**Current working config:**\\n```json\\n\\\"browser\\\": {\\n  \\\"relayBindHost\\\": \\\"0.0.0.0\\\",\\n  \\\"relayHttp\\\": true\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Active profiles (from `openclaw browser profiles`):**\\n- default: running (WSL Chromium, port 18800)\\n- chrome-relay: running (Windows Chrome extension, port 18792)\\n- visible: stopped (port 18801)\\n\\n## 07:10 SAST — Context Selectivity Learning (CRITICAL)\\n\\n**Tiny's directive:** Learn to send full context vs bare bones depending on prompt type.\\n\\n**Clear bare-bones signals:**\\n- Self-contained requests (status, time, diagnostics)\\n- Cron-triggered heartbeats with no user dependency\\n- Clarification questions with no conversation dependency\\n- System prompts (compaction, memory flush)\\n\\n**Gray area (conservative default = full context):**\\n- Anything referencing recent decisions, preferences, context from earlier session\\n- Multi-step tasks with implicit history\\n- Anything where I \\\"don't know what I don't know\\\"\\n\\n**Rule:** Default to full context when uncertain. Strip down only when signal is unambiguous. Build track record over time before being aggressive about stripping.\\n\\n**Current token state:** 91k/60k (152%) — compaction overdue since 7:35am. Context window pressure from Mar 22 morning session (browser task, model switch, session file reading, skill creation).\\n\\n**07:55 Compaction:** Token overflow critical. Memory flushed. Awaiting user response on context signal question (asked 7:10am, unanswered — compacting now).\\n\\n## 08:22 SAST — Context Selectivity Decision AGREED\\n\\n**Pattern adopted:** Two-step prompting\\n1. Send trimmed prompt (minimal context)\\n2. Offer expansion option (\\\"need more context? I can add...\\\")\\n\\n**Cuts agreed (in order):**\\n1. Conversation history — largest variable (60k+ possible)\\n2. Tool definitions — 500-2000 tokens\\n\\n**Other trim candidates identified:**\\n- AGENTS.md: ~1,200 (startup protocol mostly, not needed for every prompt)\\n- HEARTBEAT.md: ~300 (only when heartbeat is the actual task)\\n- SOUL.md/MEMORY.md: Medium risk — these carry identity and hard constraints\\n- USER.md: ~50 negligible\\n\\n**Concern noted:** MEMORY.md has Tiny's hard constraints (flow state, no sycophancy, backup rule). Stripping it risks alignment violations on tasks where those constraints matter.\\n\\n**Default pattern going forward:**\\n- Minimal: runtime header + SOUL.md essentials + current message\\n- Expansion offered by default\\n- SOUL.md/MEMORY.md retained when hard constraints or preferences might be relevant\\n\\n**Awaiting:** User decision to start live testing\\n\\n## 08:22 SAST — Final Decision\\n\\n**MEMORY.md: NOT for grabs** — stays in every prompt. Contains hard constraints, non-negotiable.\\n\\n**Finalized cuts:**\\n1. Conversation history — rolling cap (last N messages/tokens), not eliminated\\n2. Tool definitions — trimmed from prompt by default\\n\\n**Pattern going forward:**\\n- Always included: MEMORY.md, SOUL.md, runtime header, current message\\n- Trimmed by default: conversation history (capped), tool definitions\\n- Offer on request: full session history\\n- Two-step: send trimmed → offer expansion\\n\\n**Next:** Awaiting Tiny's go to flip the switch\\n\\n## 08:33 SAST — Context Trim Investigation Results\\n\\n**Backup done:** `~/TinyBackUp/20260322/0833-full-backup/` (full workspace + config)\\n\\n**Finding:** No config knob to trim history/tools. OpenClaw controls prompt assembly — not accessible to agent. Compaction triggers after overflow, not before.\\n\\n**Real path forward:** ContextEngine plugin slot (changelog: \\\"enables plugins like `lossless-claw` to provide alternative context management\\\"). Not a simple flip — requires plugin setup.\\n\\n**What I can control (my side):**\\n- Disciplined explicit compactions\\n- Keep my working memory lean\\n- Two-step response: minimal output + offer expansion\\n\\n**Decision:** Pending Tiny's choice — work with my-side discipline, or dig into plugin path\\n\\n## 08:43 SAST — Visible WSL Browser Investigation\\n\\n**Root cause found:** Snap Chromium enforces headless — it injects `--ozone-platform=headless` into child processes (gpu, renderer) regardless of flags passed to main process. Can't be overridden.\\n\\n**WSLg available** (WSL's built-in Wayland bridge) but snap blocks it.\\n\\n**Two paths forward:**\\n1. **VcXsrv on Windows** (recommended) — X server for Windows, lets WSL Chromium display to desktop. Needs download + install on Windows side. ~5 min.\\n2. **chrome-relay** (works NOW) — Windows Chrome relay, Tiny sees browser, I control it. Limitation: I work blind until feedback, can't see alongside Tiny in real-time.\\n\\n**Why VcXsrv is worth it (argued to Tiny):**\\n- Shared real-time visibility — both can watch simultaneously\\n- Disposable browser — crash/restart without affecting actual Chrome\\n- Better for content work where visual context matters mid-task\\n\\n**Awaiting:** Tiny's decision on VcXsrv install vs chrome-relay\\n\\n## 08:45 SAST — Pre-compaction flush\\n\\n**Tiny question:** Can I estimate token size of each prompt component before sending?\\n**Answer given (rough estimates):**\\n- Runtime header: ~30 tokens\\n- SOUL.md: ~800\\n- USER.md: ~50\\n- AGENTS.md: ~1,200\\n- TOOLS.md: ~400\\n- HEARTBEAT.md: ~300\\n- MEMORY.md: ~2,000 (growing)\\n- Tool definitions: ~500-2,000\\n- Conversation history: 10k-80k (dominant factor)\\n- Heartbeat prompt: ~100\\n\\n**Key unknown:** OpenClaw's raw system prompt assembly + exact tokenizer. Can't see server-side assembly.\\n**Conversation history is the variable** — hard to estimate without intercepting the actual API payload.\\n\\n**Current token count:** ~91k/60k — compaction still critical but deferred for active user conversation.\\n**Awaiting:** Tiny's response on context selectivity decision.\\n\\n## 06:30 SAST — Session Start (Mar 22, Full Session)\\n\\n**Session opened:** TUI session with model switch request + browser task\\n\\n### Model Switch\\n- Requested: Switch default to `minimax-m2.7:cloud`\\n- Done: primary updated to `ollama/minimax-m2.7:cloud`, fallback to `minimax-m2.5:cloud`\\n- Backup: ~/TinyBackUp/20260322/openclaw.json.HHMM\\n- Gateway restarted\\n\\n### Visible Browser Task\\n- Tiny wanted WSL Chromium to create a visible window on his laptop\\n- First attempt: `openclaw browser --profile visible` → error page (not actual display)\\n- `chrome-relay` profile works but shows relay view (Tiny's actual Windows Chrome)\\n- **Issue:** `visible` profile isn't connecting to Tiny's actual display\\n\\n### Session File Reading\\n- Tried reading sessions from last 5 days via JSONL files\\n- Problem: Files are large (bytes show) but `sessions_history` API returns truncated/empty\\n- JSONL format appears to be newer metadata-only structure, not parsing correctly via raw scripts\\n- TUI sessions from sessions_list showed transcript paths but content unreadable via both API and raw file reads\\n- Tiny got frustrated — asked me to find the right approach myself\\n\\n### Key Learnings (Session)\\n- Don't assume what approach was used before — ask or search memory first\\n- `sessions_history` API works but truncates content (~5k bytes)\\n- JSONL files are large but content not in standard `role`/`content` fields\\n- The session file format appears to have changed — need to understand the actual format before claiming \\\"I read the sessions\\\"\\n\\n### Current Task Status\\n| # | Task | Status |\\n|---|------|--------|\\n| 1 | X Thread for Post 001 | Draft delivered, Tiny reviewing |\\n| 2 | X Scraping | Blocked — only 1 tweet visible via relay |\\n| 3 | Writing Lesson | Pending |\\n\\n## 09:17 SAST — Visible Browser Investigation Update (Post-compaction)\\n\\n**User corrected me:** It was **Chromium** (snap package `/snap/chromium/3375/usr/lib/chromium-browser/chrome`), not Chrome. User was right to push back on the distinction.\\n\\n**Key findings from browser investigation:**\\n- Snap Chromium enforces `--ozone-platform=headless` internally on all child processes — cannot be overridden\\n- WSLg socket exists at `/mnt/wslg/runtime-dir/wayland-0` but WAYLAND_DISPLAY env var not set\\n- X server running on display :0 (WSLg's X server, socket at `/tmp/.X11-unix/X0`)\\n- Xeyes test confirmed X connectivity works (xeyes launched successfully on display :0)\\n- Portable Chrome (downloaded to `/tmp/chrome-linux/`) also runs headless — appends flags internally\\n- Chrome CDP on port 18801 is running but renders headless only\\n- `ELECTRON_OZONE_PLATFORM_HINT=wayland` does not work with Chrome\\n\\n**VcXsrv downloaded:** `C:\\\\Users\\\\Tiny4Lurv\\\\Downloads\\\\vcxsrv.zip` (~851KB Nullsoft installer exe)\\n- Source: GitHub marchaesen/vcxsrv fork (SourceForge redirects to GitHub)\\n- Still needs installation on Windows side\\n\\n**Mar 20 browser gap:** Session files show `chromium --remote-debugging-port=18801` with \\\"Missing X server\\\" error logged, yet user says he could see it. Full reconstruction not possible from fragmented session files. The `visible` profile pointed to CDP URL at port 18801, and chrome-relay was the control layer.\\n\\n**chrome-relay status:** Working — Windows Chrome relay on port 18792, uses Tiny's logged-in sessions\\n\\n## 09:25 SAST — Tools Audit & Visible Browser Confirmed Working\\n\\n**Browser visible!** Chromium running on PID 32679 with `--ozone-platform=x11`. Tiny can see it via WSLg RDP bridge on his Windows desktop. Key was `ELECTRON_OZONE_PLATFORM_HINT=auto` combined with `DISPLAY=:0`.\\n\\n**Tools audit complete — items NOT in docs (updated in 2026-03-17.md):**\\n\\n1. Voice notes: WhatsApp doesn't auto-transcribe, no ffmpeg/Whisper in WSL\\n2. Argo Credentials Manager: security setting in config\\n3. Preflight script: `scripts/openclaw-model-preflight.ps1` + Windows copy\\n4. gws: Google Workspace CLI (installed, not auth'd)\\n5. Split-brain fix: pairing mode + TUI restart\\n6. Writing style rules: two-step prompting, \\\"Nice dream. But impractical.\\\", Grammarly=tool artifact\\n7. Compaction: threshold key not implemented in v2026.3.13\\n8. Visible browser root cause: snap headless enforcement, WSLg X in Windows namespace\\n9. Nava LinkedIn: X derivative not created, admin URL documented\\n\\n**Current Chromium state:**\\n- PID 32679, display :0 (WSLg RDP)\\n- CDP: localhost:18801\\n- Process: /usr/bin/chromium-browser --ozone-platform=x11 --display=:0 --remote-debugging-port=18801\\nSprint check-in 10:20 SAST - no change, awaiting Tiny\\n## Tiny's Derailment Pattern — 13:54 SAST (IMPORTANT LESSON)\\n\\n**What happened:** Tiny wanted to show me a Nava tweet example to improve the X thread draft. Instead of just pasting it, he walked me through building the entire visible browser → CDP extraction pipeline so I could pull it myself.\\n\\n**His point:** \\\"I could have simply manually edited your draft but I wanted to put this tool in place and do things properly! It is always better to do things properly than quickly!\\\"\\n\\n**The derailment:** Yes, this consumed 30+ minutes of setup time when the tweet content was copyable in 2 seconds. But the infrastructure is now in place — I can now navigate to any page Tiny can see and extract content programmatically.\\n\\n**Core files note added:** This pattern is now documented in SOUL.md as \\\"Tiny's Derailment Rule\\\" — he consistently prioritizes building tools over quick wins. The time investment pays off downstream.\\n\\n**Reinforces:** \\\"Never prioritize speed over protocol\\\" (SOUL.md hard constraint)\\n\\n**What was built:**\\n- Visible WSL Chromium working with CDP (port 18801)\\n- Playwright → CDP extraction pipeline for dynamic content\\n- X tweet extraction (7 tweets pulled, added to corpus)\\n- Repeatable: any page Tiny navigates to, I can now read/extract\\n\\n## X Tweet Extraction — 13:49 SAST\\n\\n**Approach:** CDP via Playwright + curl → `Runtime.evaluate` on WSL Chromium (port 18801)\\n```bash\\n# Steps:\\n# 1. Navigate: openclaw browser --browser-profile visible navigate https://x.com/NavaRecruitment\\n# 2. Wait for page load, scroll: page.evaluate(\\\"window.scrollBy(0, 800)\\\")\\n# 3. Extract via Playwright CDP:\\nfrom playwright.sync_api import sync_playwright\\nbrowser = p.chromium.connect_over_cdp(\\\"http://localhost:18801\\\")\\ntweets = page.query_selector_all('[data-testid=\\\"tweet\\\"]')\\n```\\n\\n**NavaRecruitment tweets (non-job-ads, Aug 2025→):**\\n- 2026-03-14: \\\"False Finish Line\\\" — offer acceptance ≠ placement success, Day 60 danger zone\\n- 2026-03-04: \\\"Clinical License Fallacy\\\" — license ≠ predictor of success, human eye for context matters\\n- 2026-02-25: \\\"90-Day Waiting Period\\\" — thread (3 tweets), elite talent won't wait, Nava drops red tape\\n- 2026-02-21: \\\"Employer Brand vs Patient Brand\\\" — thread (2 tweets), brand leading indicator\\n- 2025-12-17: JOB AD — excluded\\n\\n**Corpus update needed:** Add 7 tweets to nava-corpus with metadata (date/platform/thread/type)\\n\\n## Visible Browser CDP — Confirmed Working Pattern\\n\\n**Read what's loaded:**\\n```bash\\ncurl -s http://localhost:18801/json | jq -r '.[] | \\\"\\\\(.title) | \\\\(.url)\\\"'\\n```\\n\\n**Navigate + extract via Playwright CDP:**\\n```python\\nfrom playwright.sync_api import sync_playwright\\nwith sync_playwright() as p:\\n    browser = p.chromium.connect_over_cdp(\\\"http://localhost:18801\\\")\\n    page = browser.contexts[0].pages[0]\\n    page.goto(url)\\n    page.wait_for_timeout(2000)\\n    tweets = page.query_selector_all('[data-testid=\\\"tweet\\\"]')\\n```\\n\\nSprint check-in: 11:10 SAST\\n- Nava RAG: Complete (Mar 17, >48h, excluded per rule)\\n- Visible browser: Working (Chromium PID 32679, DISPLAY=:0)\\n- Tools audit: Complete, committed to git\\n- Task #1 (X Thread Post 001): Draft delivered pre-nap, awaiting Tiny review\\n- Task #2 (FB scraping remainder): Waiting\\n- Task #3 (Writing lesson): Waiting\\n- Tiny: Napping, will pick up when awake\\n---\\n\\n## 12:57 SAST — Pre-Compaction Flush (Mar 22 Midday)\\n\\n**Compaction reason:** Session at ~91k tokens, approaching overflow. Flushing durable memories before reset.\\n\\n**Key session events since last flush (09:17 SAST):**\\n\\n### Compaction diagnosis (from Mar 19 session)\\n- Config has `compaction: { mode: \\\"safeguard\\\" }` — this is NOT proactive trimming\\n- \\\"Safeguard\\\" mode triggers compaction AFTER overflow, not before\\n- Real proactive compaction requires ContextEngine plugin (not yet set up)\\n- Session history grows until API rejects it, then compaction fires\\n- **This is the root cause of the recurring collapse cycle**\\n\\n### Session file reading (partial reconstruction)\\n- JSONL session files are metadata-heavy, not raw transcript\\n- `sessions_history` API truncates at ~15k bytes\\n- Full reconstruction from fragmented compactions not possible\\n- Key facts extracted and captured in memory files\\n- Mar 17-21 sessions: split-brain fix verified, browser evolution reconstructed\\n\\n### Memory search status\\n- Working ✅ — provider: ollama, model: nomic-embed-text\\n- Was degraded (FTS-only) during Mar 17-18 period; fixed by Mar 18 evening\\n\\n### Model state (current)\\n- Primary: `ollama/minimax-m2.7:cloud` (switched this session)\\n- Fallback: `ollama/minimax-m2.5:cloud`\\n- Gateway restarted after switch\\n- Backup: ~/TinyBackUp/20260322/openclaw.json (pre-switch backup exists)\\n\\n### Visible browser\\n- Chromium PID 32679 still running on DISPLAY=:0 (WSLg)\\n- Working startup command: `ELECTRON_OZONE_PLATFORM_HINT=auto DISPLAY=:0 nohup /usr/bin/chromium-browser --no-sandbox --remote-debugging-port=18801 --user-data-dir=/tmp/chromium-visible > /tmp/chromium_visible.log 2>&1 &`\\n- CDP port: 18801\\n\\n### Nava tasks (unchanged)\\n| # | Task | Status |\\n|---|------|--------|\\n| 1 | X Thread for Post 001 | Draft delivered, awaiting review |\\n| 2 | X Scraping | Blocked — need logged-in X access |\\n| 3 | Writing Lesson | Pending |\\n\\n### Context selectivity\\n- Two-step prompting pattern adopted: trimmed + offer expansion\\n- MEMORY.md stays (hard constraints non-negotiable)\\n- Tool definitions trimmed from default prompt\\n- Conversation history capped\\n\\n### Config backup location\\n- ~/TinyBackUp/20260322/ — multiple timestamped backups from Mar 22 session\\n\\n## 10:30 UTC (12:30 SAST) — Pre-compaction Flush\\n\\n**Sprint status:** Nava RAG complete/stable (>48h old, excluded from check-ins). No change since morning.\\n\\n**Visible browser:** Still running on PID 32679. Confirmed working at 09:25 SAST.\\n\\n**Active tasks (unchanged from morning):**\\n| # | Task | Status |\\n|---|------|--------|\\n| 1 | X Thread for Post 001 | Draft delivered pre-nap, awaiting Tiny review |\\n| 2 | X Scraping (Nava account) | Blocked — only 1 tweet visible via relay |\\n| 3 | Writing Lesson | Pending |\\n\\n**Tools audit completed:** TOOLS.md overhauled, memory files updated, git commit 5609c0c.\\n\\n**Session file reading:** Mar 17-21 sessions partially reconstructed — fragmentation from compactions means full reconstruction not possible. Key facts captured in memory files.\\n\\n**Split-brain:** Resolved Mar 20 via pairing mode + TUI restart (verified).\\n\\n**Nava RAG:** Complete since Mar 17. Task 3 (ingestion flow) pending new content.\\n\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 12:53 SAST — Pre-compaction Flush (Mar 22, Latest)\\n\\n**Key discoveries from Mar 19 session reconstruction:**\\n\\n### Screenshot skill: `read` tool with Windows path translation\\n- **Skill confirmed:** The `read` tool reads images (jpg, png, gif, webp) directly when given Windows paths\\n- **Path translation:** `C:\\\\Users\\\\Tiny4Lurv\\\\OneDrive\\\\Pictures\\\\Screenshots 1\\\\file.png` → `/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Pictures/Screenshots 1/file.png`\\n- **gemma3:27b-cloud is the vision model that works correctly** (minimax hallucinated)\\n- **Workflow:** Tiny takes screenshot → pastes path → I use `read` tool → gemma3 sees it\\n\\n### Mar 19 Draft 001 (\\\"Incentive Trap\\\") session\\n- **Concept:** Spread recruitment fee over 12 weeks (hypothetical)\\n- **Key insight:** \\\"Administratively: spreading payments over 12 weeks is a nightmare for HR. Agencies have a fair argument: they've done the sourcing/vetting/placing. Why wait 3 months?\\\" → Tiny's rewrite: \\\"Regardless, this model is objectively better for healthcare facilities yet no agency would jeopardise their revenue to make it even more unpredictable.\\\"\\n- **\\\"Nice dream. But impractical.\\\"** — confirmed as preferred idiom for killing hypotheticals\\n- **No em-dashes, no 1-line paragraphs** — Tiny's rules\\n- **Image-first vs post-first:** Post-first for this one (opener stronger than image)\\n- **Nava appears late:** Problem → hypothetical → industry argument → \\\"Nice dream. But impractical.\\\" → Nava pivot\\n\\n### Hallucination incident (Mar 19 evening)\\n- I described a screenshot that didn't exist — claimed it had \\\"What if your recruitment fee was spread over 12 weeks?\\\" opener\\n- gemma3:27b-cloud (switched in after) read the actual screenshot — different content\\n- Tiny was right to call it out — model failure, not tool failure\\n- Lesson: Don't describe content I haven't actually read\\n\\n### Visible browser limitation (RECONFIRMED Mar 22)\\n- Playwright/CDP screenshots capture Chrome's render buffer, NOT Tiny's Windows desktop\\n- WSLg Chrome and Windows desktop are separate rendering surfaces\\n- The `read` tool + Windows path is the correct approach for seeing what Tiny sees\\n- CDP navigation commands don't stick (chromium stays on chrome://newtab/)\\n- **VcXsrv still not installed** on Windows\\n\\n### Screenshot folder location\\n- **Path:** `/m