gle ✅\\n- Post 5: Woman Yelling at a Cat ✅\\n- Post 6: Boardroom Suggestion ✅\\n- Post 7: Gru's Plan ✅\\n- Post 9: Anakin/Padmé \\\"Red Flag\\\" ✅\\n- Post 11: Mother Ignoring Kid Drowning in a Pool ✅\\n- Post 12: Distracted Boyfriend ✅\\n\\n**Next task: X corpus**\\n- 14 screenshots in OpenClawScreenshots root (not in FbPosts): 144427–144940\\n- User says all relevant X screenshots are in OpenClawScreenshots folder\\n- Need to identify which are X posts vs other (LinkedIn?)\\n- Need to create XPosts subfolder (parallel to FbPosts)\\n- Instruction: stay in Chromium, do NOT use relay browser\\n- Corpus plan: X post paired with LinkedIn counterpart (some X posts have multiple tweets in a thread)\\n\\n## Memory Flush 16:00 SAST\\n\\n### X Corpus — COMPLETE\\n- 14 X screenshots extracted via Gemma (full-text, style, theme, meme ID)\\n- Screenshots moved to `OpenClawScreenshots/XPosts/` (14 files, 144427–144940)\\n- New file: `nava-corpus/x-linkedin-paired-corpus.md` (15,265 bytes, commit 845f563)\\n- LinkedIn logged in via Chromium (verification code entered by Tiny himself)\\n\\n### X Corpus Coverage\\n| Bundle | X Posts | LI Pair | Notes |\\n|--------|---------|---------|-------|\\n| Crisis by Design Parts 1–4 | X01–X06 | LI Posts 3–6 | All paired |\\n| Hiring Gamble | X07 | LI Post 7 | Paired |\\n| Numbers Game | X08 | LI Post 8 | Paired |\\n| Perfect on Paper | X09 | None | X-only (LI was native format) |\\n| Clinical DNA | X10 | LI Post 13 | Paired |\\n| Staff vs Agency | X11 | LI Post 11 | Paired |\\n| Sign-On/90-Day | X12 | LI Post 12 | Paired |\\n| False Finish Line | X13+X14 | LI Post 12 | Partial (thematic extension) |\\n\\n### LinkedIn-Only Posts (no X counterpart)\\n- LI Post 1: \\\"Recruiting Isn't the Problem. Misalignment Is.\\\" (Sep 3, 2025)\\n- LI Post 2: \\\"Choosing the Lesser Evil / Staffing Roulette\\\" (Sep 8, 2025) — Two Buttons meme\\n- LI Post 9: \\\"New Grad RN / Preceptor Story\\\" (Oct 18, 2025) — Anakin/Padme meme\\n\\n### X Meme Index\\n- X01: \\\"This Is Fine\\\" (KC Green dog) ✅\\n- X03: Grim Reaper waiting room ✅\\n- X04: Woman Yelling at Cat ✅\\n- X05–X06: Boardroom Suggestion ✅\\n- X07: Gru's Plan ✅\\n- X08: UNO Draw 25 ✅\\n- X09: POV / Class Type RPG framework (original format) ✅\\n- X10: Split-screen comparison (original format) ✅\\n- X11: Mother Ignoring Kid Drowning ✅\\n- X12: Distracted Boyfriend ✅\\n- X13: Expectation vs Reality / Road Not Taken (adapted) ✅\\n- X02, X14: Text-only thread continuations ✅\\n\\n### All 3 corpora now complete\\n1. `nava-corpus/facebook-posts.md` — 13 posts, screenshot-sourced ✅\\n2. `nava-corpus/x-linkedin-paired-corpus.md` — 14 X posts + 11 LI pairings ✅\\n3. `nava-corpus/nava-linkedin-posts.md` — existing LinkedIn corpus (separate) ✅\\n\\n### Screenshots organized\\n- `OpenClawScreenshots/FbPosts/` — 13 FB posts\\n- `OpenClawScreenshots/XPosts/` — 14 X posts\\n\\n### Git commits today\\n- 845f563: X+LinkedIn paired corpus\\n- fe2fe69, e1de1b8, f8cce36: earlier flushes\\n\\n### Still pending (from earlier)\\n- Crisis by Design series discussion (deferred by user)\\n- mcporter not yet connected to any live service\\n\\n---\\n\\n## LinkedIn Full Re-Scrape — 16:09-16:24 SAST\\n\\n**User request:** Re-do LinkedIn extraction — not convinced I had all posts. User expanded posts in Chromium.\\n\\n**Method:** Playwright CDP → scroll + \\\"See more\\\" clicks on admin page\\n**Script:** `/tmp/linkedin_scroll5.py` (see earlier session for full code)\\n\\n**Result:**\\n- **78 posts** captured (52 unique dates)\\n- **Date range:** Oct 14, 2025 → Mar 19, 2026\\n- **Nov 24 covered:** ✅ Yes (2 posts on that date)\\n- **Raw file:** `/tmp/linkedin_all_posts_raw.txt` (145,715 bytes)\\n- **JSON backup:** `/tmp/linkedin_all_posts.json`\\n\\n**November coverage (unique dates):**\\n```\\n10/14, 10/15, 10/16, 10/17, 10/18, 10/21, 10/22, 10/23, 10/24, 10/25,\\n10/27, 10/28, 10/29, 10/30, 10/31,\\n11/1, 11/3, 11/6, 11/7, 11/8, 11/9, 11/10, 11/11, 11/12, 11/13, 11/14,\\n11/19, 11/20, 11/21, 11/22, 11/23, 11/24, 11/26, 11/27, 11/28, 11/29,\\n12/1, 12/4, 12/5, 12/9, 12/11, 12/13, 12/15, 12/22, 12/23,\\n1/22/2026,\\n2/21, 2/25,\\n3/3, 3/4, 3/14, 3/19\\n```\\n\\n**Gaps (likely LinkedIn lazy-load):** Nov 2, 4, 5, 15, 16, 17, 18, 25, 30\\n\\n**Unique post count by date (sample):**\\n- 1/22/2026: 4 posts\\n- 10/16/2025: 3 posts\\n- 11/7, 11/20-24, 11/27-29: 2 posts each\\n\\n**Status at flush:** Delivered summary to Tiny. Awaiting direction on:\\n1. Extract full text of each post → add to corpus?\\n2. Try alternative method to fill November gaps?\\n3. Move forward with 78 posts as-is?\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 16:24 SAST — LinkedIn Screenshot Extraction Complete + Cross-Reference\\n\\n**Source:** 28 LinkedIn screenshots in `OpenClawScreenshots/LIPosts/` (moved from root)\\n\\n**Two extraction batches completed successfully (no abort):**\\n- Batch 1: 28 screenshots → `/tmp/li_screenshot_extractions.json`\\n- Batch 2: 28 screenshots → `/tmp/li_full_extractions.json`\\n\\n**28 screenshots → 4 confirmed X matches, 24 LinkedIn-only:**\\n\\n| Screenshot | Date | X Match | Topic |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| 162218.png | 9/8/2025 | ✅ X01–X06 | Crisis by Design |\\n| 162114.png | 9/25/2025 | ✅ X07 | Hiring Gamble |\\n| 162019.png | 10/14/2025 | ✅ X08 | Numbers Game |\\n| 161404.png | 12/23/2025 | ✅ X11 | Staff vs Agency |\\n| 24 others | Various | 📝 LI-only | Various |\\n\\n\\n[Read output capped at 50KB for this call. Use offset=1114 to continue.]\"}],\"details\":{\"truncation\":{\"truncated\":true,\"truncatedBy\":\"bytes\",\"totalLines\":1487,\"totalBytes\":69037,\"outputLines\":1113,\"outputBytes\":51181,\"lastLinePartial\":false,\"firstLineExceedsLimit\":false,\"maxLines\":2000,\"maxBytes\":51200}},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1774231208739}}\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/81925542-1588-4cfc-8284-8adba71eb832.jsonl:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"12f03ff8\",\"parentId\":\"e2238409\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-19T18:32:45.106Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"ollama_call_dd482d45-2b87-4374-9f1c-dcb867b7a518\",\"toolName\":\"read\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"# MEMORY.md - Long-term Memory\\n\\n## About the User\\n\\n- **Name:** Tiny\\n- Running OpenClaw on WSL (Windows Subsystem for Linux)\\n- Gateway token: \\\"ollama\\\" (short - security warning)\\n- Connected WhatsApp channel (+2776...)\\n- Uses Hacker News\\n\\n## Preferences & Notes\\n\\n- Prefers concise responses; asked assistant to be less verbose.\\n- Dislikes AI drift, recycled ideas, and over-verbosity; values precision and directness.\\n- Wants pushback over agreeability during concept development.\\n- Strong preference for concept pressure-testing before drafting.\\n- LinkedIn workflow preference: concept discussion -> decide image-first/post-first -> finalize LinkedIn post -> derive X -> optional channels.\\n- Visual preference: realistic, striking images; caption must complement image (not restate it).\\n- Writing style preference: operator/executive tone, compressed sentences, natural short-paragraph rhythm, bullets for real failure cascades, occasional bold pivots (not rigid).\\n- Content safety preference: reject off-domain Nava ideas; enforce staffing/recruiting-only taxonomy with source-backed claims.\\n- Channel preference: Nava LinkedIn + X mandatory; FB/Yosef/Tiny optional by fit.\\n- Visual workflow preference: image concepts must be refined iteratively (multiple directions + critique + refinement), not one-shot generation.\\n- User authored Nava blog articles and wants ongoing article-topic suggestions from corpus gaps; ingest/index must refresh with every new article.\\n- User wants Google Docs integration for draft critique and style transfer calibration toward their writing voice (alongside existing Gemini custom Gem workflow).\\n- X workflow preference: AI can lead first draft (1-3 tweets), user reviews for impact.\\n- Primary current project: Nava cross-platform content system and post roadmap execution.\\n- Potential channel confusion noted: user suspects duplicate/imposter Dawn on WhatsApp; verify source session/channel before assuming delivery route.\\n- Switched to Ollama cloud models (Minimax/Nemotron) after OpenAI tokens ran out (2026-03-19).\\n- Primary model: `gemma3:27b-cloud` (just added, in testing)\\n- Fallbacks: `minimax-m2.7:cloud` → `minimax-m2.5:cloud` → `nemotron-3-super:cloud`\\n- Config backup saved to TinyBackUp before change.\\n- Model-routing preference (2026-03-18): default to local Windows Ollama models for routine/structured workflow tasks; escalate to ChatGPT selectively for hard reasoning and high-stakes final polish, with proactive warning before high-token GPT steps.\\n- Change-control preference (2026-03-18): before mutating config (especially model routing/gateway behavior), provide read-only diagnosis first and ask for explicit approval; do not make silent config edits.\\n- Confidential test phrase to verify split-brain memory sharing (2026-03-17): \\\"Tiny is in trouble with Betsho because of late payments!\\\"\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Updated: 2026-03-19*\\n\\n## Token Limit Issue (2026-03-19)\\n\\n- **Problem**: Context limit errors with Ollama cloud models\\n- Config has `contextWindow: 204800` for minimax-m2.5:cloud, but API rejects prompts exceeding actual model limits\\n- Session hit \\\"prompt too long; exceeded max context length by 142-228 tokens\\\"\\n- **Fix**: Lower contextWindow in config (recommend 128000 or lower) to prevent overflow errors\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Browser Relay Setup (2026-03-19)\\n\\n### Architecture\\n- **chrome-extension** folder: Chrome extension to install in your Windows Chrome\\n- **Relay server**: Runs in WSL gateway on port 18792\\n- **Connection**: Windows Chrome extension → connects to WSL relay (port 18792) → Gateway controls it\\n\\n### Fix for \\\"Profile not found\\\" errors\\n1. **Never set defaultProfile in config** — it breaks the relay\\n2. **To use chrome-relay**: always pass `--browser-profile chrome-relay`\\n3. **If errors occur**: Check `openclaw browser profiles` — if you see profiles but get errors, restart gateway\\n\\n### Working command\\n```bash\\nopenclaw browser --browser-profile chrome-relay screenshot\\nopenclaw browser --browser-profile chrome-relay navigate <url>\\n```\\n\\n### Current config state (working)\\n- `defaultProfile`: REMOVED (key fix)\\n- `profiles.openclaw`: port 18800 (WSL Chrome, not used)\\n- `relayBindHost`: 0.0.0.0 (allows external connections)\\n\\n### Backup files\\n- ~/TinyBackUp/20260319/openclaw.json.154346 — current working config\\n- ~/TinyBackUp/20260319/MEMORY.md.154348 — current memory\\n\\n## Nava LinkedIn Posts (2026-03-19)\\n\\nFound 3 published posts on company page (Aug-Oct 2025):\\n- **Oct 3, 2025**: \\\"The ROI of Investing in Employee Wellness: Why Companies Are Putting Health First\\\" — 111 reactions, 9 comments\\n- **Sep 5, 2025**: \\\"The Real Cost of Employee Turnover: Why Retention is the New Recruitment\\\" — 52 reactions, 4 comments\\n- **Aug 8, 2025**: \\\"The Employee Benefit Your Workforce Actually Wants\\\" — 42 reactions, 4 comments\\n\\nAdmin URL: https://www.linkedin.com/company/67170741/admin/page-posts/published/\\n\\n### LinkedIn Page IDs\\n- Nava Healthcare (company): 67170741 (not the same as nava-healthcare slug)\\n\\n### Recent LinkedIn Posts Content (from 2025-03)\\n\\n**5 days ago - \\\"The False Finish Line\\\"**\\n- Topic: Most healthcare recruiting teams think the race is over the moment the offer is accepted. In reality, that's a false finish line.\\n- Key message: Stay engaged with candidate between offer acceptance and Day 60\\n- Nava differentiator: No upfront costs, fees only when confident in placement\\n\\n**2 weeks ago (Edited) - \\\"The Universal License Fallacy\\\"**\\n- Topic: A clinical license is a measure of minimum competency, not a predictor of professional success\\n- Key message: Don't hire the CV, hire the person behind the qualifications\\n- Key concept: 