ements.\\\\nMost charge it all upfront.\\\\n\\\\nWhat if they only got paid as long as your hire stayed?\\\\n\\\\n🧵\\\\n\\\\n**Tweet 2:**\\\\nWeek 1: 10% | Week 4: 30% | Week 8: 60% | Week 12: 100%\\\\n\\\\nSuddenly the agency cares about retention. They'd actually follow up. They'd worry if someone quits at week 3.\\\\n\\\\n**Tweet 3:**\\\\nNice dream. But impractical.\\\\n\\\\nAdmin overhead for HR = nightmare.\\\\nAgencies need predictable cash flow.\\\\n\\\\nThat's why we went different direction: zero upfront. We get paid only when your hire proves themselves.\\\\n\\\\nWe align on the same incentive you do.\\\\n\\\\n**Status:** Awaiting Tiny review\\\\n\\\\n## 05:56 SAST — Task Queue Confirmed\\\\n\\\\n| # | Task | Status |\\\\n|---|------|--------|\\\\n| 1 | X Thread for Post 001 | ACTIVE - draft delivered |\\\\n| 2 | Scrape remaining FB posts | Waiting |\\\\n| 3 | Writing lesson | Waiting |\\\\n\\\\n**Current focus:** #1 - awaiting Tiny review before refining or moving on\\\\n\\\\n## 06:10 SAST Sprint Check-in (internal)\\\\n- Nava RAG task: COMPLETE (Mar 17) — >48h old, excluded from check-ins per rule\\\\n- Reminder handled internally (per 48h rule)\\\\n\\\\n## 06:01 SAST — Thread Feedback + Agent Architecture Discussion\\\\n\\\\n**Tiny feedback:**\\\\n- Tweet 1 + 2 too short, should merge\\\\n- Will show example of proper 3-tweet thread\\\\n- Taking notes for Nava Agent training\\\\n\\\\n**Agent architecture proposal:**\\\\n- 2 separate agents:\\\\n  1. Nava Social Media — fast, punchy, threaded, platform-specific\\\\n  2. Nava Blog — longer-form, structured, research-heavy, SEO-minded\\\\n- Awaiting example before finalizing architecture\\\\n\\\\n## 06:08 SAST — Corpus Structure Discussion\\\\n\\\\n**Current corpus:**\\\\n- Blog: `rag/clean_md/` — 22 articles from navahc.com (Aug 2025)\\\\n- Facebook: `nava-corpus/facebook-posts.md` — 8 posts\\\\n- X: None\\\\n- LinkedIn: None\\\\n\\\\n**Problem:** No unified index, no metadata (date/platform/author/type)