ng extra actions he didn't authorize\\\\\\\\n- **No sycophancy** — likes to be challenged and pushed back if he's missing something\\\\\\\\n- **Not outsourcing thinking** — wants enhancement, not replacement\\\\\\\\n- **Dark humor** — likes a chuckle\\\\\\\\n- **Rule for AI tools**: Answer the question asked, follow instructions issued, don't add extra action\\\\\\\\n- **DIAGNOSTIC QUESTIONS FIRST** — When Tiny asks \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"what went wrong?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" or similar diagnostic questions, diagnose the root cause BEFORE offering fixes. Don't rush to correct — understand first.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### Priority Setting (2026-03-19)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n- **Ask at start of each session**: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"What do you need to get done today?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" — understand active goals, not just assigned tasks\\\\\\\\n- **Current burning priorities**: Nava content posts (today, tomorrow, Saturday)\\\\\\\\n- **Recovery priority**: Context limit fix → Gateway restart → Nava posting\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### Current Focus (2026-03-19)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n- **Goal**: Master OpenClaw and similar tools (Agent Zero)\\\\\\\\n- **Hardware**: Limited budget, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"shit computer\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" (adequate for 90% of people, but AI interests may need upgrade)\\\\\\\\n- **Sports**: Arsenal (primary), F1, interesting European fixtures (e.g., Barca vs Newcastle, Man City vs Real Madrid)\\\\\\\\n- **Calendar gap**: Wants heads-up on interesting matches beyond tracked teams\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### Operational Discipline (2026-03-19 interview)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n- **BACKUP BEFORE EVERY CHANGE**: Date-stamp to ~/TinyBackUp/, keep 2 versions, delete oldest AFTER confirming new works\\\\\\\\n- **Never run \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Doctor\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" tool blindly** — it uses a chainsaw, not a scalpel; has shredded JSON before\\\\\\\\n- **Windows restarts overnight** — causes config drift, model changes, relay failures; expect morning reconfiguration\\\\\\\\n- **Schedule varies** — no fixed pattern (depends on girlfriend, commitments, social life)\\\\\\\\n- **Communication**: Don't dumb down, use complex but shorter language; ask clarifying questions if ambiguous\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### LinkedIn Management (2026-03-19 interview)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n- **Task**: Update Tiny's LinkedIn profile, especially job descriptions\\\\\\\\n- **Ongoing**: Check for jobs he fits well, periodically\\\\\\\\n- **Target**: $30/hour or more (needs better laptop: 40GB RAM, GPU upgrade)\\\\\\\\n- **Prerequisite**: Must familiarize with his LinkedIn profile first\\\\\\\\n- **Browser**: Relay active, profile open\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### Split-Brain Problem (CRITICAL - needs investigation)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n- **TUI session**: Has its own context/brain\\\\\\\\n- **WebUI session**: Separate brain, doesn't know what TUI is doing\\\\\\\\n- **WhatsApp (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Dawn\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")**: Can only read memory, has no idea what TUI is currently doing\\\\\\\\n- **Suspected cause**: Per-peer session settings vs \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"main\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" session targeting\\\\\\\\n- **Impact**: Cannot check progress remotely via WhatsApp; must use TUI for real-time context\\\\\\\\n- Wants pushback over agreeability during concept development.\\\\\\\\n- Strong preference for concept pressure-testing before drafting.\\\\\\\\n- LinkedIn workflow preference: concept discussion -> decide image-first/post-first -> finalize LinkedIn post -> derive X -> optional channels.\\\\\\\\n- Visual preference: realistic, striking images; caption must complement image (not restate it).\\\\\\\\n- Writing style preference: operator/executive tone, compressed sentences, natural short-paragraph rhythm, bullets for real failure cascades, occasional bold pivots (not rigid).\\\\\\\\n- Content safety preference: reject off-domain Nava ideas; enforce staffing/recruiting-only taxonomy with source-backed claims.\\\\\\\\n- Channel preference: Nava LinkedIn + X mandatory; FB/Yosef/Tiny optional by fit.\\\\\\\\n- Visual workflow preference: image concepts must be refined iteratively (multiple directions + critique + refinement), not one-shot generation.\\\\\\\\n- User authored Nava blog articles and wants ongoing article-topic suggestions from corpus gaps; ingest/index must refresh with every new article.\\\\\\\\n- User wants Google Docs integration for draft critique and style transfer calibration toward their writing voice (alongside existing Gemini custom Gem workflow).\\\\\\\\n- X workflow preference: AI can lead first draft (1-3 tweets), user reviews for impact.\\\\\\\\n- Primary current project: Nava cross-platform content system and post roadmap execution.\\\\\\\\n- Potential channel confusion noted: user suspects duplicate/imposter Dawn on WhatsApp; verify source session/channel before assuming delivery route.\\\\\\\\n- Switched to Ollama cloud models (Minimax/Nemotron) after OpenAI tokens ran out (2026-03-19).\\\\\\\\n- Primary model: `gemma3:27b-cloud` (just added, in testing)\\\\\\\\n- Fallbacks: `minimax-m2.7:cloud` → `minimax-m2.5:cloud` → `nemotron-3-super:cloud`\\\\\\\\n- Config backup saved to TinyBackUp before change.\\\\\\\\n- Model-routing preference (2026-03-18): default to local Windows Ollama models for routine/structured workflow tasks; escalate to ChatGPT selectively for hard reasoning and high-stakes final polish, with proactive warning before high-token GPT steps.\\\\\\\\n- Change-control preference (2026-03-18): before mutating config (especially model routing/gateway behavior), provide read-only diagnosis first and ask for explicit approval; do not make silent config edits.\\\\\\\\n- Confidential test phrase to verify split-brain memory sharing (2026-03-17): \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Tiny is in trouble with Betsho because of late payments!\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n---\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n*Updated: 2026-03-19*\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## Token Limit Issue (2026-03-19)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n- **Problem**: Context limit errors with Ollama cloud models\\\\\\\\n- Config has `contextWindow: 204800` for