\\\\\\\n- 18:10–18:45 — Attempted `sentence-transformers` GPU stack; install aborted due oversized CUDA wheel/network instability.\\\\\\\\n- 18:35 — Pulled `nomic-embed-text` via Ollama successfully; embed endpoint was intermittently timing out on batch requests.\\\\\\\\n- 18:46–19:03 — Installed `fastembed` in `rag/.venv`; upgraded vector builder/query path to support transformer embeddings without torch.\\\\\\\\n- 19:03 — Rebuilt vector index successfully using `fastembed` backend (`rag/index/vector_index.json`).\\\\\\\\n- 19:40 check-in — reminder handled internally; checklist reviewed, transformer upgrade remains stable; no new blockers.\\\\\\\\n- 19:20 check-in — reminder handled internally; RAG pipeline stable on fastembed; skills safety research queued for tomorrow briefing.\\\\\\\\n- 19:30 check-in — reminder handled internally; gateway connected; checklist unchanged; memory + status synced for morning brief continuity.\\\\\\\\n- 08:30 (2026-03-18) check-in — reminder handled internally; Nava crawl → synthesis → full RAG checklist remains stable/complete for current scope; no new blockers; continuing fetch-failure diagnostics separately.\\\\\\\\n- 08:40 (2026-03-18) check-in — reminder handled internally; checklist revalidated as complete/stable for autonomous scope; memory synchronized; no new Nava blockers; intermittent fetch-failure diagnostics remain a separate infra thread.\\\\\\\\n- 08:50 (2026-03-18) check-in — reminder handled internally; checklist remains complete/stable for Nava crawl → synthesis → full RAG scope; memory synced; no new delivery blockers; fetch-failure issue still tracked as separate operational/infra thread.\\\\\\\\n- 08:59–09:00 (2026-03-18) — Added Nava content-engine hard guardrails at `rag/config/content_guardrails.yaml` (domain lock, evidence-required, taxonomy-required, output contract); user confirmed intent to build additional content layer.\\\\\\\\n- 09:00 (2026-03-18) check-in — reminder handled internally; checklist still complete/stable for core RAG scope; next phase is content-engine implementation + image refinement workflow + new-article ingest loop.\\\\\\\\n- 09:30 (2026-03-18) check-in — reminder handled internally; core Nava crawl → synthesis → full RAG remains complete/stable; Task 1 (skills/tooling setup) in progress; WSL resources reconfigured (RAM/CPU exposure increased), Windows Ollama connectivity verified, and model-routing plan shifted to local-first with ChatGPT escalation for hard reasoning/final polish.\\\\\\\\n- 10:30 (2026-03-18) check-in — reminder handled internally; core Nava crawl → synthesis → full RAG remains complete/stable with no new delivery blockers; Task 1 continues (local-LLM setup/validation), user restarted WSL successfully, and active thread shifted to safe Ollama model onboarding + reliability tests while avoiding RAM overload.\\\\\\\\n- 11:00 (2026-03-18) check-in — reminder handled internally; core Nava crawl → synthesis → full RAG remains complete/stable with no new delivery blockers; Task 1 still active with Ollama onboarding friction (Qwen download restarts/interruption behavior). Guidance shifted to GUI-allowed path + single-download discipline while preserving local-first model-routing plan.\\\\\\\\n- 11:30 (2026-03-18) check-in — reminder handled internally; core Nava crawl → synthesis → full RAG remains complete/stable with no new delivery blockers. Task 1 advanced: user successfully installed `qwen3:4b-instruct`, passed rewrite + strict-JSON reliability checks (low latency, no perceived lag), validated RAM impact when model stays loaded (~13GB footprint), and received local-first preflight tooling (`OLLAMA_OPENAI_FALLBACK_GUIDE.md`, `scripts/openclaw-model-preflight.ps1`, Windows copy at `%USERPROFILE%\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\openclaw-model-preflight.ps1`).\\\\\\\\n- 12:00 (2026-03-18) check-in — reminder handled internally; core Nava crawl → synthesis → full RAG remains complete/stable (no delivery blockers). Operational incident: message deli