3:**\\\\\\\\nNice dream. But impractical.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAdmin overhead for HR = nightmare.\\\\\\\\nAgencies need predictable cash flow.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThat's why we went different direction: zero upfront. We get paid only when your hire proves themselves.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe align on the same incentive you do.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Status:** Awaiting Tiny review\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 05:56 SAST — Task Queue Confirmed\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n| # | Task | Status |\\\\\\\\n|---|------|--------|\\\\\\\\n| 1 | X Thread for Post 001 | ACTIVE - draft delivered |\\\\\\\\n| 2 | Scrape remaining FB posts | Waiting |\\\\\\\\n| 3 | Writing lesson | Waiting |\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Current focus:** #1 - awaiting Tiny review before refining or moving on\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 06:10 SAST Sprint Check-in (internal)\\\\\\\\n- Nava RAG task: COMPLETE (Mar 17) — >48h old, excluded from check-ins per rule\\\\\\\\n- Reminder handled internally (per 48h rule)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 06:01 SAST — Thread Feedback + Agent Architecture Discussion\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Tiny feedback:**\\\\\\\\n- Tweet 1 + 2 too short, should merge\\\\\\\\n- Will show example of proper 3-tweet thread\\\\\\\\n- Taking notes for Nava Agent training\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Agent architecture proposal:**\\\\\\\\n- 2 separate agents:\\\\\\\\n  1. Nava Social Media — fast, punchy, threaded, platform-specific\\\\\\\\n  2. Nava Blog — longer-form, structured, research-heavy, SEO-minded\\\\\\\\n- Awaiting example before finalizing architecture\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 06:08 SAST — Corpus Structure Discussion\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Current corpus:**\\\\\\\\n- Blog: `rag/clean_md/` — 22 articles from navahc.com (Aug 2025)\\\\\\\\n- Facebook: `nava-corpus/facebook-posts.md` — 8 posts\\\\\\\\n- X: None\\\\\\\\n- LinkedIn: None\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Problem:** No unified index, no metadata (date/platform/author/type)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Tiny proposal:** Add ALL non-job-ad tweets (Aug 2025→present) to corpus\\\\\\\\n- Agreed: makes sense\\\\\\\\n- Need metadata tags for each post\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Current task:** #1 (X thread) still active\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Tiny question:** Finish thread first or start X scrape?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 06:12 SAST — X Scraping Attempt\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Priority changed:** X scrape first, then thread\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Attempt 1:** Browser relay not logged into X - showing homepage\\\\\\\\n**Attempt 2:** Playwright also not logged in - shows homepage\\\\\\\\n**Problem:** Need logged-in session to scrape Nava's tweets\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Solution needed:** Tiny to screenshot his logged-in X view\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 06:15 SAST — Browser Confusion\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Confusion identified:** I was using WSL Chrome (not logged in) instead of Tiny's relay (logged in)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Two options presented:**\\\\\\\\n1. Tiny screenshots his X view → I extract\\\\\\\\n2. TeamViewer share → I control\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Awaiting Tiny's choice**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 06:16 SAST — Communication Correction\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Tiny feedback:** I should confirm which browser/interface is being used, not assume\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Correct question I should have asked:** \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Which browser are you viewing this on - the relay on your Windows Chrome?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Learning:** When referencing shared UI (relay, browser), confirm the source before acting\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 06:16 SAST — Awaiting Browser Confirmation\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Open question:** Which browser is Tiny viewing Nava's X page on?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 06:17 SAST — X Scraping Attempts\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Relay working:** Yes - chrome-relay returns screenshots\\\\\\\\n**Account found:** @NavaRecruitment (not @Navahc)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Tweets visible:**\\\\\\\\n- Only 1 tweet visible (Mar 14, thought leadership)\\\\\\\\n- Feb 25 thread not loading on my end\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Problem:** My relay view only shows 1 tweet, but Tiny sees more on his end\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Solution in progress:** Tiny to send screenshot from his view\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 06:21 SAST — X Scraping Blocked\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n- Only 1 tweet visible via my relay (Mar 14)\\\\\\\\n- Feb 25 thread not showing - page loading issue\\\\\\\\n- Awaiting Tiny screenshot from his relay view\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 06:21 SAST — Alternative Approach\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Tiny decision:** Use WSL Chromium (profile: openclaw) instead of relay\\\\\\\\n- Browser started: `openclaw browser start --profile openclaw`\\\\\\\\n- Issue: WSL browser has no GUI display on Windows side\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Current options:**\\\\\\\\n1. Relay - Tiny shares screenshot\\\\\\\\n2. TeamViewer - screen share\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 06:20 SAST — Sprint Check-in (Internal)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Task #1 (X Thread):** In progress - relay view only showing 1 tweet, requested screenshot from Tiny for full extraction\\\\\\\\n**Task #2 (X Corpus):** Waiting on #1\\\\\\\\n**Task #3 (Writing Lesson):** Waiting on #2\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Nava RAG:** Complete (>48h old - excluded per new rule)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 06:00 SAST Heartbeat Check\\\\\\\\n- **Assignment:** X Thread (Post 001) - Awaiting Tiny review\\\\\\\\n- **Tokens:** 91k/60k (152%) - COMPACTED 13x already\\\\\\\\n- **Queue:** Waiting on user input\\\\\\\\n- **Action:** Idle until user responds\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 06:00 SAST Sprint Check-in (internal)\\\\\\\\n- **Nava RAG**: Complete since Mar 17 (>48h old, excluded per rule)\\\\\\\\n- Reminder handled internally, no user relay\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 06:26 SAST — XVFB Solution Found\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Discovery:** `xvfb-run -a` gives WSL Chromium a virtual display\\\\\\\\n- Working command: `xvfb-run -a openclaw browser --profile openclaw <command>`\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**X Scraping Progress:**\\\\\\\\n- Found 2 thought leadership tweets:\\\\\\\\n  - Mar 14: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"false finish line\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" post\\\\\\\\n  - Mar 4: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"clinical license\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" post\\\\\\\\n- Account: @NavaRecruitment (26 followers, 202 posts total)\\\\\\\\n- Not seeing: Feb 25 thread (may be on different account or page requires login)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Status:** Asked Tiny for clarification on account/date\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 06:30 SAST — 30-Min Sprint Check-in (Internal)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n- **Nava RAG**: COMPLETE (Mar 17) — >48h old, excluded per rule\\\\\\\\n- Reminder handled internally\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 07:07 — Visible Browser Skill Created\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Skill:** `skills/visible-browser/SKILL.md` (committed b5ab5f4)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**What it documents:**\\\\\\\\n- Mode 1: Windows Chrome Relay (`chrome-relay`) — visible to Tiny, uses his logged-in sessions (Twitter, LinkedIn, etc.), piggybacks Windows Chrome via extension on port 18792\\\\\\\\n- Mode 2: WSL Chromium + xvfb — headless, not visible, for disposable automation\\\\\\\\n- Decision tree for which mode to use\\\\\\\\n- Profile names from `openclaw browser profiles`:\\\\\\\\n  - `default` = WSL Chromium (headless)\\\\\\\\n  - `chrome-relay` = Windows Chrome relay (visible) ← use this when Tiny needs to see/watch\\\\\\\\n  - `visible` = manual Chrome on port 18801\\\\\\\\n- Critical rule: `defaultProfile` must NOT be set in openclaw.json — that broke the relay\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Key insight from Mar 20 sessions:** Tiny had a visible browser working via CDP port 18801 launched manually with `chromium --remote-debugging-port=18801`, with a \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"visible\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" profile pointing to `http://127.0.0.1:18801`. Then the chrome-relay extension was added on top.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Current working config:**\\\\\\\\n```json\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"browser\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"relayBindHost\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"0.0.0.0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"relayHttp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": true\\\\\\\\n}\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Active profiles (from `openclaw browser profiles`):**\\\\\\\\n- default: running (WSL Chromium, port 18800)\\\\\\\\n- chrome-relay: running (Windows Chrome extension, port 18792)\\\\\\\\n- visible: stopped (port 18801)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 07:10 SAST — Context Selectivity Learning (CRITICAL)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Tiny's directive:** Learn to send full context vs bare bones depending on prompt type.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Clear bare-bones signals:**\\\\\\\\n- Self-contained requests (status, time, diagnostics)\\\\\\\\n- Cron-triggered heartbeats with no user dependency\\\\\\\\n- Clarification questions with no conversation dependency\\\\\\\\n- System prompts (compaction, memory flush)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Gray area (conservative default = full context):**\\\\\\\\n- Anything referencing recent decisions, preferences, context from earlier session\\\\\\\\n- Multi-step tasks with implicit history\\\\\\\\n- Anything where I \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"don't know what I don't know\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Rule:** Default to full context when uncertain. Strip down only when signal is unambiguous. Build track record over time before being aggressive about stripping.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Current token state:** 91k/60k (152%) — compaction overdue since 7:35am. Context window pressure from Mar 22 morning session (browser task, model switch, session file reading, skill creation).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**07:55 Compaction:** Token overflow critical. Memory flushed. Awaiting user response on context signal question (asked 7:10am, unanswered — compacting now).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 08:22 SAST — Context Selectivity Decision AGREED\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Pattern adopted:** Two-step prompting\\\\\\\\n1. Send trimmed prompt (minimal context)\\\\\\\\n2. Offer expansion option (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"need more context? I can add...\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Cuts agreed (in order):**\\\\\\\\n1. Conversation history — largest variable (60k+ possible)\\\\\\\\n2. Tool definitions — 500-2000 tokens\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Other trim candidates identified:**\\\\\\\\n- AGENTS.md: ~1,200 (startup protocol mostly, not needed for every prompt)\\\\\\\\n- HEARTBEAT.md: ~300 (only when heartbeat is the actual task)\\\\\\\\n- SOUL.md/MEMORY.md: Medium risk — these carry identity and hard constraints\\\\\\\\n- USER.md: ~50 negligible\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Concern noted:** MEMORY.md has Tiny's hard constraints (flow state, no sycophancy, backup rule). Stripping it risks alignment violations on tasks where those constraints matter.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Default pattern going forward:**\\\\\\\\n- Minimal: runtime header + SOUL.md essentials + current message\\\\\\\\n- Expansion offered by default\\\\\\\\n- SOUL.md/MEMORY.md retained when hard constraints or preferences might be relevant\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Awaiting:** User decision to start live testing\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 08:22 SAST — Final Decision\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**MEMORY.md: NOT for grabs** — stays in every prompt. Contains hard constraints, non-negotiable.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Finalized cuts:**\\\\\\\\n1. Conversation history — rolling cap (last N messages/tokens), not eliminated\\\\\\\\n2. Tool definitions — trimmed from prompt by default\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Pattern going forward:**\\\\\\\\n- Always included: MEMORY.md, SOUL.md, runtime header, current message\\\\\\\\n- Trimmed by default: conversation history (capped), tool definitions\\\\\\\\n- Offer on request: full session history\\\\\\\\n- Two-step: send trimmed → offer expansion\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Next:** Awaiting Tiny's go to flip the switch\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 08:33 SAST — Context Trim Investigation Results\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Backup done:** `~/TinyBackUp/20260322/0833-full-backup/` (full workspace + config)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Finding:** No config knob to trim history/tools. OpenClaw controls prompt assembly — not accessible to agent. Compaction triggers after overflow, not before.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Real path forward:** ContextEngine plugin slot (changelog: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"enables plugins like `lossless-claw` to provide alternative context management\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"). Not a simple flip — requires plugin setup.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**What I can control (my side):**\\\\\\\\n- Disciplined explicit compactions\\\\\\\\n- Keep my working memory lean\\\\\\\\n- Two-step response: minimal output + offer expansion\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Decision:** Pending Tiny's choice — work with my-side discipline, or dig into plugin path\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 08:43 SAST — Visible WSL Browser Investigation\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Root cause found:** Snap Chromium enforces headless — it injects `--ozone-platform=headless` into child processes (gpu, renderer) regardless of flags passed to main process. Can't be overridden.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**WSLg available** (WSL's built-in Wayland bridge) but snap blocks it.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Two paths forward:**\\\\\\\\n1. **VcXsrv on Windows** (recommended) — X server for Windows, lets WSL Chromium display to desktop. Needs download + install on Windows side. ~5 min.\\\\\\\\n2. **chrome-relay** (works NOW) — Windows Chrome relay, Tiny sees browser, I control it. Limitation: I work blind until feedback, can't see alongside Tiny in real-time.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Why VcXsrv is worth it (argued to Tiny):**\\\\\\\\n- Shared real-time visibility — both can watch simultaneously\\\\\\\\n- Disposable browser — crash/restart without affecting actual Chrome\\\\\\\\n- Better for content work where visual context matters mid-task\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Awaiting:** Tiny's decision on VcXsrv install vs chrome-relay\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 08:45 SAST — Pre-compaction flush\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Tiny question:** Can I estimate token size of each prompt component before sending?\\\\\\\\n**Answer given (rough estimates):**\\\\\\\\n- Runtime header: ~30 tokens\\\\\\\\n- SOUL.md: ~800\\\\\\\\n- USER.md: ~50\\\\\\\\n- AGENTS.md: ~1,200\\\\\\\\n- TOOLS.md: ~400\\\\\\\\n- HEARTBEAT.md: ~300\\\\\\\\n- MEMORY.md: ~2,000 (growing)\\\\\\\\n- Tool definitions: ~500-2,000\\\\\\\\n- Conversation history: 10k-80k (dominant factor)\\\\\\\\n- Heartbeat prompt: ~100\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Key unknown:** OpenClaw's raw system prompt assembly + exact tokenizer. Can't see server-side assembly.\\\\\\\\n**Conversation history is the variable** — hard to estimate without intercepting the actual API payload.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Current token count:** ~91k/60k — compaction still critical but deferred for active user conversation.\\\\\\\\n**Awaiting:** Tiny's response on context selectivity decision.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 06:30 SAST — Session Start (Mar 22, Full Session)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Session opened:** TUI session with model switch request + browser task\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### Model Switch\\\\\\\\n- Requested: Switch default to `minimax-m2.7:cloud`\\\\\\\\n- Done: primary updated to `ollama/minimax-m2.7:cloud`, fallback to `minimax-m2.5:cloud`\\\\\\\\n- Backup: ~/TinyBackUp/20260322/openclaw.json.HHMM\\\\\\\\n- Gateway restarted\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### Visible Browser Task\\\\\\\\n- Tiny wanted WSL Chromium to create a visible window on his laptop\\\\\\\\n- First attempt: `openclaw browser --profile visible` → error page (not actual display)\\\\\\\\n- `chrome-relay` profile works but shows relay view (Tiny's actual Windows Chrome)\\\\\\\\n- **Issue:** `visible` profile isn't connecting to Tiny's actual display\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### Session File Reading\\\\\\\\n- Tried reading sessions from last 5 days via JSONL files\\\\\\\\n- Problem: Files are large (bytes show) but `sessions_history` API returns truncated/empty\\\\\\\\n- JSONL format appears to be newer metadata-only structure, not parsing correctly via raw scripts\\\\\\\\n- TUI sessions from sessions_list showed transcript paths but content unreadable via both API and raw file reads\\\\\\\\n- Tiny got frustrated — asked me to find the right approach myself\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### Key Learnings (Session)\\\\\\\\n- Don't assume what approach was used before — ask or search memory first\\\\\\\\n- `sessions_history` API works but truncates content (~5k bytes)\\\\\\\\n- JSONL files are large but content not in standard `role`/`content` fields\\\\\\\\n- The session file format appears to have changed — need to understand the actual format before claiming \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I read the sessions\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### Current Task Status\\\\\\\\n| # | Task | Status |\\\\\\\\n|---|------|--------|\\\\\\\\n| 1 | X Thread for Post 001 | Draft delivered, Tiny reviewing |\\\\\\\\n| 2 | X Scraping | Blocked — only 1 tweet visible via relay |\\\\\\\\n| 3 | Writing Lesson | Pending |\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 09:17 SAST — Visible Browser Investigation Update (Post-compaction)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**User corrected me:** It was **Chromium** (snap package `/snap/chromium/3375/usr/lib/chromium-browser/chrome`), not Chrome. User was right to push back on the distinction.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Key findings from browser investigation:**\\\\\\\\n- Snap Chromium enforces `--ozone-platform=headless` internally on all child processes — cannot be overridden\\\\\\\\n- WSLg socket exists at `/mnt/wslg/runtime-dir/wayland-0` but WAYLAND_DISPLAY env var not set\\\\\\\\n- X server running on display :0 (WSLg's X server, socket at `/tmp/.X11-unix/X0`)\\\\\\\\n- Xeyes test confirmed X connectivity works (xeyes launched successfully on display :0)\\\\\\\\n- Portable Chrome (downloaded to `/tmp/chrome-linux/`) also runs headless — appends flags internally\\\\\\\\n- Chrome CDP on port 18801 is running but renders headless only\\\\\\\\n- `ELECTRON_OZONE_PLATFORM_HINT=wayland` does not work with Chrome\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**VcXsrv downloaded:** `C:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\Users\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\Tiny4Lurv\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\Downloads\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\vcxsrv.zip` (~851KB Nullsoft installer exe)\\\\\\\\n- Source: GitHub marchaesen/vcxsrv fork (SourceForge redirects to GitHub)\\\\\\\\n- Still needs installation on Windows side\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Mar 20 browser gap:** Session files show `chromium --remote-debugging-port=18801` with \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Missing X server\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" error logged, yet user says he could see it. Full reconstruction not possible from fragmented session files. The `visible` profile pointed to CDP URL at port 18801, and chrome-relay was the control layer.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**chrome-relay status:** Working — Windows Chrome relay on port 18792, uses Tiny's logged-in sessions\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 09:25 SAST — Tools Audit & Visible Browser Confirmed Working\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Browser visible!** Chromium running on PID 32679 with `--ozone-platform=x11`. Tiny can see it via WSLg RDP bridge on his Windows desktop. Key was `ELECTRON_OZONE_PLATFORM_HINT=auto` combined with `DISPLAY=:0`.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Tools audit complete — items NOT in docs (updated in 2026-03-17.md):**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n1. Voice notes: WhatsApp doesn't auto-transcribe, no ffmpeg/Whisper in WSL\\\\\\\\n2. Argo Credentials Manager: security setting in config\\\\\\\\n3. Preflight script: `scripts/openclaw-model-preflight.ps1` + Windows copy\\\\\\\\n4. gws: Google Workspace CLI (installed, not auth'd)\\\\\\\\n5. Split-brain fix: pairing mode + TUI restart\\\\\\\\n6. Writing style rules: two-step prompting, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Nice dream. But impractical.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", Grammarly=tool artifact\\\\\\\\n7. Compaction: threshold key not implemented in v2026.3.13\\\\\\\\n8. Visible browser root cause: snap headless enforcement, WSLg X in Windows namespace\\\\\\\\n9. Nava LinkedIn: X derivative not created, admin URL documented\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Current Chromium state:**\\\\\\\\n- PID 32679, display :0 (WSLg RDP)\\\\\\\\n- CDP: localhost:18801\\\\\\\\n- Process: /usr/bin/chromium-browser --ozone-platform=x11 --display=:0 --remote-debugging-port=18801\\\\\\\\nSprint check-in 10:20 SAST - no change, awaiting Tiny\\\\\\\\n## Tiny's Derailment Pattern — 13:54 SAST (IMPORTANT LESSON)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**What happened:** Tiny wanted to show me a Nava tweet example to improve the X thread draft. Instead of just pasting it, he walked me through building the entire visible browser → CDP extraction pipeline so I could pull it myself.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**His point:** \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I could have simply manually edited your draft but I wanted to put this tool in place and do things properly! It is always better to do things properly than quickly!\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**The derailment:** Yes, this consumed 30+ minutes of setup time when the tweet content was copyable in 2 seconds. But the infrastructure is now in place — I can now navigate to any page Tiny can see and extract content programmatically.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Core files note added:** This pattern is now documented in SOUL.md as \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Tiny's Derailment Rule\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" — he consistently prioritizes building tools over quick wins. The time investment pays off downstream.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Reinforces:** \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Never prioritize speed over protocol\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" (SOUL.md hard constraint)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**What was built:**\\\\\\\\n- Visible WSL Chromium working with CDP (port 18801)\\\\\\\\n- Playwright → CDP extraction pipeline for dynamic content\\\\\\\\n- X tweet extraction (7 tweets pulled, added to corpus)\\\\\\\\n- Repeatable: any page Tiny navigates to, I can now read/extract\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## X Tweet Extraction — 13:49 SAST\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Approach:** CDP via Playwright + curl → `Runtime.evaluate` on WSL Chromium (port 18801)\\\\\\\\n```bash\\\\\\\\n# Steps:\\\\\\\\n# 1. Navigate: openclaw browser --browser-profile visible navigate https://x.com/NavaRecruitment\\\\\\\\n# 2. Wait for page load, scroll: page.evaluate(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"window.scrollBy(0, 800)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\n# 3. Extract via Playwright CDP:\\\\\\\\nfrom playwright.sync_api import sync_playwright\\\\\\\\nbrowser = p.chromium.connect_over_cdp(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"http://localhost:18801\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\ntweets = page.query_selector_all('[data-testid=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tweet\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"]')\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**NavaRecruitment tweets (non-job-ads, Aug 2025→):**\\\\\\\\n- 2026-03-14: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"False Finish Line\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" — offer acceptance ≠ placement success, Day 60 danger zone\\\\\\\\n- 2026-03-04: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Clinical License Fallacy\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" — license ≠ predictor of success, human eye for context matters\\\\\\\\n- 2026-02-25: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"90-Day Waiting Period\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" — thread (3 tweets), elite talent won't wait, Nava drops red tape\\\\\\\\n- 2026-02-21: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Employer Brand vs Patient Brand\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" — thread (2 tweets), brand leading indicator\\\\\\\\n- 2025-12-17: JOB AD — excluded\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Corpus update needed:** Add 7 tweets to nava-corpus with metadata (date/platform/thread/type)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## Visible Browser CDP — Confirmed Working Pattern\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Read what's loaded:**\\\\\\\\n```bash\\\\\\\\ncurl -s http://localhost:18801/json | jq -r '.[] | \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\(.title) | \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\(.url)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"'\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Navigate + extract via Playwright CDP:**\\\\\\\\n```python\\\\\\\\nfrom playwright.sync_api import sync_playwright\\\\\\\\nwith sync_playwright() as p:\\\\\\\\n    browser = p.chromium.connect_over_cdp(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"http://localhost:18801\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\n    page = browser.contexts[0].pages[0]\\\\\\\\n    page.goto(url)\\\\\\\\n    page.wait_for_timeout(2000)\\\\\\\\n    tweets = page.query_selector_all('[data-testid=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tweet\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"]')\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSprint check-in: 11:10 SAST\\\\\\\\n- Nava RAG: Complete (Mar 17, >48h, excluded per rule)\\\\\\\\n- Visible browser: Working (Chromium PID 32679, DISPLAY=:0)\\\\\\\\n- Tools audit: Complete, committed to git\\\\\\\\n- Task #1 (X Thread Post 001): Draft delivered pre-nap, awaiting Tiny review\\\\\\\\n- Task #2 (FB scraping remainder): Waiting\\\\\\\\n- Task #3 (Writing lesson): Waiting\\\\\\\\n- Tiny: Napping, will pick up when awake\\\\\\\\n---\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## 12:57 SAST — Pre-Compaction Flush (Mar 22 Midday)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Compaction reason:** Session at ~91k tokens, approaching overflow. Flushing durable memories before reset.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**Key session events since last flush (09:17 SAST):**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### Compaction diagnosis (from Mar 19 session)\\\\\\\\n- Config has `compaction: { mode: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"safeguard\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" }` — this is NOT proactive trimming\\\\\\\\n- \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Safeguard\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" mode triggers compaction AFTER overflow, not before\\\\\\\\n- Real proactive compaction requires ContextEngine plugin (not yet set up)\\\\\\\\n- Session history grows until API rejects it, then compaction fires\\\\\\\\n- **This is the root cause of the recurring collapse cycle**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### Session file reading (partial reconstruction)\\\\\\\\n- JSONL session files are metadata-heavy, not raw transcript\\\\\\\\n- `sessions_history` API truncates at ~15k bytes\\\\\\\\n- Full reconstruction from fragmented compactions not possible\\\\\\\\n- Key facts extracted and captured in memory files\\\\\\\\n- Mar 17-21 sessions: split-brain fix verified, browser evolution reconstructed\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### Memory search status\\\\\\\\n- Working ✅ — provider: ollama, model: nomic-embed-text\\\\\\\\n- Was degraded (FTS-only) during Mar 17-18 period; fixed by Mar 18 evening\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### Model state (current)\\\\\\\\n- Primary: `ollama/minimax-m2.7:cloud` (switched this session)\\\\\\\\n- Fallback: `ollama/minimax-m2.5:cloud`\\\\\\\\n- Gateway restarted after switch\\\\\\\\n- Backup: ~/TinyBackUp/20260322/openclaw.json (pre-switch backup exists)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### Visible browser\\\\\\\\n- Chromium PID 32679 still running on DISPLAY=:0 (WSLg)\\\\\\\\n- Working startup command: `ELECTRON_OZONE_PLATFORM_HINT=auto DISPLAY=:0 nohup /usr/bin/chromium-browser --no-sandbox --remote-debugging-port=18801 --user-data-dir=/tmp/chromium-visible > /tmp/chromium_visible.log 2>&1 &`\\\\\\\\n- CDP port: 18801\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### Nava tasks (unchanged)\\\\\\\\n| # | Task | Status |\\\\\\\\n|---|------|--------|\\\\\\\\n| 1 | X Thread for Post 001 | Draft delivered, awaiting review |\\\