d 2 reposts of Tiny's posts by Yosef: \\\"Escaping the Volume Trap\\\" (3mo), \\\"Care With Purpose\\\" (5mo)\\n- [x] TUI session global fix implemented (now uses shared \\\"main\\\" session)\\n\\n### In Progress\\n- [ ] Verify TUI session global fix by testing context persistence\\n\\n### Blocked\\n- None\\n\\n## Key Decisions\\n- **TUI session sharing**: Changed from unique `tui-<uuid>` sessions to shared `session: global` to allow TUI ↔ WebChat ↔ WhatsApp to share context\\n\\n## Next Steps\\n1. Ask TUI about something discussed in morning webchat session (e.g., \\\"Incentive Trap\\\" LinkedIn post) to verify context persistence\\n2. Continue sprint work on Task 3 ingestion update flow\\n\\n## Critical Context\\n- Current time: Friday, March 20th, 2026 — 12:10 PM SAST\\n- Memory files: memory/2026-03-17.md, memory/2026-03-20.md\\n- TUI should now show `agent:main:main` instead of `agent:main:tui-...`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Decisions\\n- TUI now joins shared \\\"main\\\" session instead of spawning unique sessions per connection\\n\\n## Open TODOs\\n- Verify TUI session global fix works (test context recall)\\n- Continue Task 3 ingestion update flow for Nava RAG\\n\\n## Constraints/Rules\\n- Handle reminders internally unless user explicitly requests relay\\n- Memory persistence: memory/2026-03-17.md for sprint notes, MEMORY.md only for long-term items\\n\\n## Pending user asks\\n- None explicitly stated\\n\\n## Exact identifiers\\n- CDP port: `18801`\\n- TUI session type: `session: global` (was `tui-<uuid>`)\\n- LinkedIn URLs: `https://www.linkedin.com/in/yosef-roston/activity/`, `https://www.linkedin.com/in/yosef-roston/recent-activity/all/`\\n- Memory files: `memory/2026-03-17.md`, `memory/2026-03-20.md`\\n- Backup path: `~/TinyBackUp/20260320/`\\n- LinkedIn posts found: \\\"The False Finish Line\\\" (5d), \\\"The Universal License Fallacy\\\" (2w), \\\"The 90-Day Waiting Period\\\" (3w), \\\"The Cost of Vacancies\\\" (3w), \\\"The Brand Gap\\\" (3w), \\\"In the dynamic world of healthcare\\\" (10mo)\\n- Tiny posts reposted by Yosef: \\\"Escaping the Volume Trap\\\" (3mo ago), \\\"Care With Purpose | PM&R Physician\\\" (5mo ago)\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\\n\\n## Goal\\nInvestigate why WhatsApp is not working or not listening in the OpenClaw system. Use all resources required to diagnose the issue.\\n\\n## Constraints & Preferences\\n- Use all resources required to investigate\\n- Same approach as previous investigations\\n\\n## Progress\\n### Done\\n- [x] Ran `openclaw status` - shows gateway at ws://127.0.0.1:18789 but \\\"unreachable (missing scope: operator.read)\\\"\\n- [x] Attempted to filter logs for WhatsApp entries\\n- [x] Listed sessions via `sessions_list(kinds=[\\\"whatsapp\\\"])` - returned 14 sessions but none specifically whatsapp kind\\n- [x] Read config file `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/openclaw.json` - WhatsApp is configured and enabled\\n- [x] Grep log file `/tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-03-20.log` for WhatsApp entries\\n- [x] Reviewed log entries showing WhatsApp listening status and errors\\n\\n### In Progress\\n- [ ] Determining root cause of WhatsApp connection issues from detailed log analysis\\n\\n### Blocked\\n- None explicitly stated\\n\\n## Key Decisions\\n- **Investigation approach**: Started with system status, then logs, then session listing, then config review, now detailed log analysis\\n- **Multiple issues identified**: Cron job error with E.164 format, WebSocket timeout, auto-restart behavior\\n\\n## Next Steps\\n1. Review WhatsApp plugin status directly\\n2. Verify WhatsApp service connectivity and authentication\\n3. Check if the cron job error is related to missing phone number format\\n4. Investigate the WebSocket timeout cause (connection to WhatsApp service)\\n\\n## Critical Context\\n- WhatsApp config in openclaw.json: `enabled: true`, `dmPolicy: \\\"allowlist\\\"`, `allowFrom: [\\\"+27763674298\\\"]`, `groupPolicy: \\\"allowlist\\\"`\\n- Gateway shows as \\\"unreachable\\\" with missing scope \\\"operator.read\\\"\\n- 14 sessions exist but none specifically whatsapp kind\\n- WhatsApp appears to be listening but has delivery errors\\n- Auto-restart mechanism is attempting to recover the connection\\n\\n## Decisions\\n- Investigation approach: Sequential steps from status → logs → sessions → config → detailed log analysis\\n- Focus on root cause analysis from log entries showing WhatsApp listening status and errors\\n\\n## Open TODOs\\n- Review WhatsApp plugin status directly\\n- Verify WhatsApp service connectivity and authentication\\n- Investigate E.164 format issue in cron job\\n- Investigate WebSocket timeout (ETIMEDOUT, statusCode 408)\\n\\n## Constraints/Rules\\n- Use all resources required to investigate\\n- Same approach as previous investigations\\n\\n## Pending user asks\\n- Investigate why WhatsApp is not working or not listening in the OpenClaw system\\n\\n## Exact identifiers\\n- Config: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/openclaw.json`\\n- Log: `/tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-03-20.log`\\n- Phone: +27763674298\\n- Gateway: ws://127.0.0.1:18789\\n- Dashboard: http://127.0.0.1:18789/\\n- OS: linux 6.6.87.2-microsoft-standard-WSL2 (x64)\\n- Node: 22.22.1\\n- Session IDs: 36da5e41-d038-4c2e-87ad-3477fd17181d, 442c8a16-5b42-46b1-9999-a65dc2ba6db5, 00166a9a-efe7-49aa-be75-e8d1f4246908\\n- Job ID: fc7ed016-5bd8-4ac2-bc84-87c3a91ccb3e\\n- Job Name: Morning interview reminder\\n- Error: \\\"Delivering to WhatsApp requires target <E.164|group JID>\\\"\\n- Error: WebSocket Error (ETIMEDOUT, statusCode 408)\\n\\n## Recent turns preserved verbatim\\n- User: Sender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"gateway-client\\\",\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui\\\",\\n  \\\"username\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n[Fri 2026-03-20 12:12 GMT+2] Uhm, I wanna give the WebUI a shot.\\n- Assistant: Go for it — that's the perfect test.\\n\\nURL should be: `http://localhost:18791` (or whatever port your Gateway web UI runs on)\\n\\nIf split-brain is fixed, WebUI should now see this conversation (with all our morning context about the LinkedIn posts, split-brain investigation, etc.) instead of a blank slate.\\n\\nLet me know what it shows!\\n- User: Sender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"openclaw-control-ui\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"openclaw-control-ui\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n[Fri 2026-03-20 12:13 GMT+2] Hi there, Dawn :-)\\n- Assistant: Hey! 👋\\n\\nWelcome to the WebUI. The question is — do you have memory of this morning?\\n\\nQuick test: What were we just investigating, and what's the LinkedIn post we posted yesterday? \\n\\n(If this is a fresh session with no context, you'll have to tell me. But if split-brain is fixed, you should already know.)\\n- User: Sender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"openclaw-control-ui\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"openclaw-control-ui\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n[Fri 2026-03-20 12:14 GMT+2] No, I am convinced the split-brain is gone! I will test my WhatsApp next.\\n- Assistant: 🎉 **SPLIT-BRAIN FIX CONFIRMED WORKING!**\\n\\nThat's a huge win. The WebUI now shares context with TUI — all our morning work (LinkedIn activity review, session scope investigation, config changes) is visible.\\n\\nThis should also fix the WhatsApp \\\"Dawn\\\" issue. When you test there, you should now see the full context of everything we've discussed today.\\n\\nLet me know what WhatsApp shows — if it works there too, this problem is fully solved.\\n[non-text content: toolCall]\\n- Tool result (edit): Successfully replaced text in memory/2026-03-20.md.\\n- Assistant: Updated memory with the fix confirmation. Let me know what WhatsApp shows!\\n\\n<read-files>\\n/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/openclaw.json\\n</read-files>\\n\\n<modified-files>\\nmemory/2026-03-20.md\\n</modified-files>\\n\\n<workspace-critical-rules>\\n## Session Startup\\n\\nBefore doing anything else:\\n\\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\\n\\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\\n\\n## Red Lines\\n\\n- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\\n- Don't run destructive commands without asking.\\n- `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\\n- When in doubt, ask.\\n</workspace-critical-rules>\",\"firstKeptEntryId\":\"80e02a87\",\"tokensBefore\":40052,\"details\":{\"readFiles\":[\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/openclaw.json\"],\"modifiedFiles\":[\"memory/2026-03-20.md\"]},\"fromHook\":true}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":81,"aggregated":"iv class=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"_96be6219 _0e7ed0e4 _8f478d46 f682a6c8 b9e4e23e d02cbba5 ae00ce14\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"><p class=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"fd835fbb _846596fa bbc4d4bf fb4e632b _213a24e7 _809b127f _9be53d94 e521201b\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\">Operational wizard, CEO of Nava HC Recruitment, and leading 15 premier rehab, skilled nursing, and long-term care centers across the South. Follow our journey on Facebook and LinkedIn @ Arabella Healthcare Management!</p></div></div></div></a></div></div><div class=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"_89785f5c _225a1781 _2b60d1cc _821d5731 ac4cc985 d3b98d87\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"><div class=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"_298010f8 df803e28 _19f4bd76\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" style=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"margin-inline-start: 5.6rem;\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"></div><div class=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"_6f335b77 _89785f5c _19b5f421 _2b60d1cc _821d5731 ac4cc985 d3b98d87\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"><div class=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"_60aba533\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" data-display-contents=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"true\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"><a class=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"_527a0782 _97698c20 _70f9a957 bf4c7917 _39fb1c9c f682a6c8 _28e0c4dd e1d97aa6 _1b76ece7 _9844331e _0616f1f0 _906c9b2f _96a09043 _19f4bd76\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" aria-disabled=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" href=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/messaging/compose/?profileUrn=urn%3Ali%3Afsd_profil