>\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"_meta\\\":{\\\"runtime\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"runtimeVersion\\\":\\\"22.22.1\\\",\\\"hostname\\\":\\\"unknown\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"openclaw\\\",\\\"date\\\":\\\"2026-03-20T02:46:16.280Z\\\",\\\"logLevelId\\\":3,\\\"logLevelName\\\":\\\"INFO\\\",\\\"path\\\":{\\\"fullFilePath\\\":\\\"file:///home/tiny4lurv/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-BDbeCphF.js:944:46\\\",\\\"fileName\\\":\\\"subsystem-BDbeCphF.js\\\",\\\"fileNameWithLine\\\":\\\"subsystem-BDbeCphF.js:944\\\",\\\"fileColumn\\\":\\\"46\\\",\\\"fileLine\\\":\\\"944\\\",\\\"filePath\\\":\\\"/home/tiny4lurv/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-BDbeCphF.js\\\",\\\"filePathWithLine\\\":\\\"/home/tiny4lurv/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-BDbeCphF.js:944\\\",\\\"method\\\":\\\"console.log\\\"}},\\\"time\\\":\\\"2026-03-20T04:46:16.280+02:00\\\"}\\n{\\\"0\\\":\\\"{\\\\\\\"subsystem\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"gateway/channels/whatsapp\\\\\\\"}\\\",\\\"1\\\":\\\"Listening for personal WhatsApp inbound messages.\\\",\\\"_meta\\\":{\\\"runtime\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"runtimeVersion\\\":\\\"22.22.1\\\",\\\"hostname\\\":\\\"unknown\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"{\\\\\\\"subsystem\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"gateway/channels/whatsapp\\\\\\\"}\\\",\\\"parentNames\\\":[\\\"openclaw\\\"],\\\"date\\\":\\\"2026-03-20T02:53:15.601Z\\\",\\\"logLevelId\\\":3,\\\"logLevelName\\\":\\\"INFO\\\",\\\"path\\\":{\\\"fullFilePath\\\":\\\"file:///home/tiny4lurv/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-CDcEQtQK.js:805:14\\\",\\\"fileName\\\":\\\"subsystem-CDcEQtQK.js\\\",\\\"fileNameWithLine\\\":\\\"subsystem-CDcEQtQK.js:805\\\",\\\"fileColumn\\\":\\\"14\\\",\\\"fileLine\\\":\\\"805\\\",\\\"filePath\\\":\\\".npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-CDcEQtQK.js\\\",\\\"filePathWithLine\\\":\\\".npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-CDcEQtQK.js:805\\\",\\\"method\\\":\\\"logToFile\\\"}},\\\"time\\\":\\\"2026-03-20T04:53:15.601+02:00\\\"}\\n{\\\"0\\\":\\\"[whatsapp] Listening for personal WhatsApp inbound messages.\\\",\\\"_meta\\\":{\\\"runtime\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"runtimeVersion\\\":\\\"22.22.1\\\",\\\"hostname\\\":\\\"unknown\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"openclaw\\\",\\\"date\\\":\\\"2026-03-20T02:53:15.603Z\\\",\\\"logLevelId\\\":3,\\\"logLevelName\\\":\\\"INFO\\\",\\\"path\\\":{\\\"fullFilePath\\\":\\\"file:///home/tiny4lurv/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-D2xHvZZd.js:852:46\\\",\\\"fileName\\\":\\\"subsystem-D2xHvZZd.js\\\",\\\"fileNameWithLine\\\":\\\"subsystem-D2xHvZZd.js:852\\\",\\\"fileColumn\\\":\\\"46\\\",\\\"fileLine\\\":\\\"852\\\",\\\"filePath\\\":\\\".npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-D2xHvZZd.js\\\",\\\"filePathWithLine\\\":\\\".npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-D2xHvZZd.js:852\\\"}},\\\"time\\\":\\\"2026-03-20T04:53:15.603+02:00\\\"}\\n{\\\"0\\\":\\\"\\\\\\\"0 notifications total\\\\\\\\nSkip to search\\\\\\\\nSkip to main content\\\\\\\\nKeyboard shortcuts\\\\\\\\nClose jump menu\\\\\\\\nSearch\\\\\\\\nnew feed updates notifications\\\\\\\\nHome\\\\\\\\nMy Network\\\\\\\\nJobs\\\\\\\\n1\\\\\\\\n1 new message notification\\\\\\\\nMessaging\\\\\\\\n25\\\\\\\\n25 new notifications\\\\\\\\nNotifications\\\\\\\\nMe\\\\\\\\nFor Business\\\\\\\\nLearning\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston \\\\\\\\nChief Operating Officer & Co-Founder at Nava Healthcare Recruitment. Managing Director at Roston Management & Consulting.\\\\\\\\nFollowers\\\\\\\\n6,088\\\\\\\\nMessage\\\\\\\\nAll activity\\\\\\\\nPosts\\\\\\\\nComments\\\\\\\\nImages\\\\\\\\nReactions\\\\\\\\nLoaded 20 Posts posts\\\\\\\\nFeed post number 1\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston\\\\\\\\n   • 1st\\\\\\\\nPremium • 1st\\\\\\\\nChief Operating Officer & Co-Founder at Nava Healthcare Recruitment. Managing Director at Roston Management & Consulting.\\\\\\\\nChief Operating Officer & Co-Founder at Nava Healthcare Recruitment. Managing Director at Roston Management & Consulting.\\\\\\\\nVisit my website\\\\\\\\n3w • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n3 weeks ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\nPatients read billboards, but clinicians read the room.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nA 7-figure rebranding campaign might get patients through the door, but let's be honest, they only stay and leave good scores because of the actual care they receive at the bedside. And the clinicians providing that care see right past the marketing slogans.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI always ask facility leaders: have you ever wondered how many elite nurses walk into your hospital for an interview, get a feel for the chaos on the floor, and just quietly decide to take an offer somewhere else? They look at the ratios, they spot the exhaustion in the eyes of your core staff. You can't fix an overwhelmed unit by panic-hiring the first warm body whose resume happens to match a job description.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nA few weeks ago my team was sourcing for a standard floor RN role for a skilled nursing partner. The industry standard is usually to just check the license, fill the shift, and move on. But we spent some time with one candidate and realized he had the exact temperament and leadership potential needed to actually stabilize a busy floor.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWhen we presented him to the facility, their leadership saw it too. They didn't just hire him for the floor, they upgraded the offer on the spot and brought him on as a Unit Manager to help mentor the team and protect the unit's culture.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThat’s how you actually protect your reputation. A great clinical environment starts with humans understanding humans, not an algorithm just checking a box for an active license.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWhile marketing makes the promise, it’s your clinical culture that delivers it. Are you relying on a billboard to do the heavy lifting, or are you building a room that clinicians actually want to stay in?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HealthcareLeadership \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#Nursing \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HospitalAdministration \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#PatientExperience \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#NavaHealthcare\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n3w • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n3 weeks ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\nIt takes 6 months and millions of dollars to approve a hospital rebranding. It takes one exhausted unit and 6 minutes to destroy it.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗬𝗼𝘂 𝗰𝗮𝗻 𝗯𝘂𝘆 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗺𝗮𝗿𝗸𝗲𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴, 𝗯𝘂𝘁 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝗰𝗮𝗻'𝘁 𝗳𝗮𝗯𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗮𝘁𝗲 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗹𝗶𝘁𝘆.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe 𝘽𝙧𝙖𝙣𝙙 𝙂𝙖𝙥 happens when the external promise of \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"World-Class Care\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" collides with the internal reality of a burned-out, under-supported unit.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPatients don't judge your hospital by your mission statement. They judge it through the eyes and actions of the clinician standing at their bedside. If you are filling schedule gaps with unvetted \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"warm bodies\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" who don't fit your culture, or pushing your core staff to the breaking point, your marketing budget is being incinerated in real-time.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIn today's hyper-connected world, visible clinical friction is not only an HR problem but a viral risk event.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYour 𝗘𝗺𝗽𝗹𝗼𝘆𝗲𝗿 𝗕𝗿𝗮𝗻𝗱 (your reputation in a clinician-scarce market) is the most critical leading indicator of your 𝗣𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗕𝗿𝗮𝗻𝗱 (their experiences and what they say about you).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nMarketing makes the promise. Your clinical culture delivers it. At Nava Healthcare, we don't just verify licenses to fill a gap; we rigorously vet for the cultural concordance that keeps your unit stable. Because your 5-star reputation isn't built on a billboard—it's built at the bedside.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nRead our full strategy on protecting your healthcare brand: https://lnkd.in/dXuv7BdE\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HealthcareMarketing \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#PatientExperience \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HospitalAdministration \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#EmployerBranding \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#NavaHealthcare\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nPlay\\\\\\\\nLoaded: 100.00%\\\\\\\\nRemaining time \\\\\\\\n0:06\\\\\\\\n1x\\\\\\\\nPlayback speed\\\\\\\\nUnmute\\\\\\\\nTurn fullscreen on\\\\\\\\n5\\\\\\\\nLike\\\\\\\\nComment\\\\\\\\nRepost\\\\\\\\nSend\\\\\\\\nFeed post number 2\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston reposted this\\\\\\\\nMarquis Health Consulting Services\\\\\\\\nMarquis Health Consulting Services\\\\\\\\n18,617 followers\\\\\\\\n18,617 followers\\\\\\\\n3w • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n3 weeks ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\nFollow\\\\\\\\nEvery heartbeat tells a story. Here at Marquis Health Consulting Services, those stories inspire everything we do.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe invite you to hear from our Mid-Atlantic Division President, Michael Smith and discover how the centers we service\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"_meta\\\":{\\\"runtime\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"runtimeVersion\\\":\\\"22.22.1\\\",\\\"hostname\\\":\\\"unknown\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"openclaw\\\",\\\"date\\\":\\\"2026-03-20T03:04:39.804Z\\\",\\\"logLevelId\\\":3,\\\"logLevelName\\\":\\\"INFO\\\",\\\"path\\\":{\\\"fullFilePath\\\":\\\"file:///home/tiny4lurv/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-BDbeCphF.js:944:46\\\",\\\"fileName\\\":\\\"subsystem-BDbeCphF.js\\\",\\\"fileNameWithLine\\\":\\\"subsystem-BDbeCphF.js:944\\\",\\\"fileColumn\\\":\\\"46\\\",\\\"fileLine\\\":\\\"944\\\",\\\"filePath\\\":\\\"/home/tiny4lurv/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-BDbeCphF.js\\\",\\\"filePathWithLine\\\":\\\"/home/tiny4lurv/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-BDbeCphF.js:944\\\",\\\"method\\\":\\\"console.log\\\"}},\\\"time\\\":\\\"2026-03-20T05:04:39.804+02:00\\\"}\\n{\\\"0\\\":\\\"\\\\\\\"0 notifications total\\\\\\\\nSkip to search\\\\\\\\nSkip to main content\\\\\\\\nKeyboard shortcuts\\\\\\\\nClose jump menu\\\\\\\\nSearch\\\\\\\\nnew feed updates notifications\\\\\\\\nHome\\\\\\\\nMy Network\\\\\\\\nJobs\\\\\\\\n1\\\\\\\\n1 new message notification\\\\\\\\nMessaging\\\\\\\\n25\\\\\\\\n25 new notifications\\\\\\\\nNotifications\\\\\\\\nMe\\\\\\\\nFor Business\\\\\\\\nLearning\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston \\\\\\\\nChief Operating Officer & Co-Founder at Nava Healthcare Recruitment. Managing Director at Roston Management & Consulting.\\\\\\\\nFollowers\\\\\\\\n6,088\\\\\\\\nMessage\\\\\\\\nAll activity\\\\\\\\nPosts\\\\\\\\nComments\\\\\\\\nImages\\\\\\\\nReactions\\\\\\\\nLoaded 20 Posts posts\\\\\\\\nFeed post number 1\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston\\\\\\\\n   • 1st\\\\\\\\nPremium • 1st\\\\\\\\nChief Operating Officer & Co-Founder at Nava Healthcare Recruitment. Managing Director at Roston Management & Consulting.\\\\\\\\nChief Operating Officer & Co-Founder at Nava Healthcare Recruitment. Managing Director at Roston Management & Consulting.\\\\\\\\nVisit my website\\\\\\\\n3w • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n3 weeks ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\nPatients read billboards, but clinicians read the room.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nA 7-figure rebranding campaign might get patients through the door, but let's be honest, they only stay and leave good scores because of the actual care they receive at the bedside. And the clinicians providing that care see right past the marketing slogans.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI always ask facility leaders: have you ever wondered how many elite nurses walk into your hospital for an interview, get a feel for the chaos on the floor, and just quietly decide to take an offer somewhere else? They look at the ratios, they spot the exhaustion in the eyes of your core staff. You can't fix an overwhelmed unit by panic-hiring the first warm body whose resume happens to match a job description.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nA few weeks ago my team was sourcing for a standard floor RN role for a skilled nursing partner. The industry standard is usually to just check the license, fill the shift, and move on. But we spent some time with one candidate and realized he had the exact temperament and leadership potential needed to actually stabilize a busy floor.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWhen we presented him to the facility, their leadership saw it too. They didn't just hire him for the floor, they upgraded the offer on the spot and brought him on as a Unit Manager to help mentor the team and protect the unit's culture.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThat’s how you actually protect your reputation. A great clinical environment starts with humans understanding humans, not an algorithm just checking a box for an active license.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWhile marketing makes the promise, it’s your clinical culture that delivers it. Are you relying on a billboard to do the heavy lifting, or are you building a room that clinicians actually want to stay in?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HealthcareLeadership \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#Nursing \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HospitalAdministration \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#PatientExperience \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#NavaHealthcare\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n3w • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n3 weeks ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\nIt takes 6 months and millions of dollars to approve a hospital rebranding. It takes one exhausted unit and 6 minutes to destroy it.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗬𝗼𝘂 𝗰𝗮𝗻 𝗯𝘂𝘆 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗺𝗮𝗿𝗸𝗲𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴, 𝗯𝘂𝘁 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝗰𝗮𝗻'𝘁 𝗳𝗮𝗯𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗮𝘁𝗲 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗹𝗶𝘁𝘆.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe 𝘽𝙧𝙖𝙣𝙙 𝙂𝙖𝙥 happens when the external promise of \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"World-Class Care\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" collides with the internal reality of a burned-out, under-supported unit.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPatients don't judge your hospital by your mission statement. They judge it through the eyes and actions of the clinician standing at their bedside. If you are filling schedule gaps with unvetted \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"warm bodies\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" who don't fit your culture, or pushing your core staff to the breaking point, your marketing budget is being incinerated in real-time.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIn today's hyper-connected world, visible clinical friction is not only an HR problem but a viral risk event.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYour 𝗘𝗺𝗽𝗹𝗼𝘆𝗲𝗿 𝗕𝗿𝗮𝗻𝗱 (your reputation in a clinician-scarce market) is the most critical leading indicator of your 𝗣𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗕𝗿𝗮𝗻𝗱 (their experiences and what they say about you).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nMarketing makes the promise. Your clinical culture delivers it. At Nava Healthcare, we don't just verify licenses to fill a gap; we rigorously vet for the cultural concordance that keeps your unit stable. Because your 5-star reputation isn't built on a billboard—it's built at the bedside.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nRead our full strategy on protecting your healthcare brand: https://lnkd.in/dXuv7BdE\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HealthcareMarketing \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#PatientExperience \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HospitalAdministration \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#EmployerBranding \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#NavaHealthcare\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nPlay\\\\\\\\nLoaded: 100.00%\\\\\\\\nRemaining time \\\\\\\\n0:06\\\\\\\\n1x\\\\\\\\nPlayback speed\\\\\\\\nUnmute\\\\\\\\nTurn fullscreen on\\\\\\\\n5\\\\\\\\nLike\\\\\\\\nComment\\\\\\\\nRepost\\\\\\\\nSend\\\\\\\\nFeed post number 2\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston reposted this\\\\\\\\nMarquis Health Consulting Services\\\\\\\\nMarquis Health Consulting Services\\\\\\\\n18,617 followers\\\\\\\\n18,617 followers\\\\\\\\n3w • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n3 weeks ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\nFollow\\\\\\\\nEvery heartbeat tells a story. Here at Marquis Health Consulting Services, those stories inspire everything we do.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe invite you to hear from our Mid-Atlantic Division President, Michael Smith and discover how the centers we service are redefining cardiac care through their unique CardioPro program. This program is expert led and focuses on results-driven recovery through evidence-based protocols and an unwavering commitment to helping patients return home stronger.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIn honor of \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#AmericanHeartMonth, we're honored to share stories that represent more than clinical excellence. They represent hope, partnership, and a safer path forward.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#PressPlay to see the Marquis difference in action!\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nTo find a center near you, visit our website: https://mqshealth.com/\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#progressparade\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAHCA/NCAL\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nPlay\\\\\\\\n135\\\\\\\\n1 comment\\\\\\\\n17 reposts\\\\\\\\nLike\\\\\\\\nComment\\\\\\\\nRepost\\\\\\\\nSend\\\\\\\\nFeed post number 3\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston\\\\\\\\n   • 1st\\\\\\\\nPremium • 1st\\\\\\\\nChief Operating Officer & Co-Founder at Nava Healthcare Recruitment. Managing Director at Roston Management & Consulting.\\\\\\\\nChief Operating Officer & Co-Founder at Nava Healthcare Recruitment. Managing Director at Roston Management & Consulting.\\\\\\\\nVisit my website\\\\\\\\n2mo • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n2 months ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\nWalk into any healthcare facility breakroom, and the narrative is the same: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"𝘐𝘧 𝘢𝘥𝘮𝘪𝘯𝘪𝘴𝘵𝘳𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘰𝘯 𝘫𝘶𝘴𝘵 𝘵𝘰𝘰𝘬 𝘵𝘩𝘦 $100/𝘩𝘳 𝘵𝘩𝘦𝘺 𝘱𝘢𝘺 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘢𝘨𝘦𝘯𝘤𝘺 𝘢𝘯𝘥 𝘨𝘢𝘷𝘦 𝘪𝘵 𝘵𝘰 𝘶𝘴, 𝘸𝘦 𝘸𝘰𝘶𝘭𝘥𝘯'𝘵 𝘣𝘦 𝘴𝘩𝘰𝘳𝘵-𝘴𝘵𝘢𝘧𝘧𝘦𝘥.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nTo the staff, it looks like indifference, or even callousness. It feels demoralizing to watch a stranger get paid double while your loyalty is ignored (even if they are splitting that hourly with an agency).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBut having sat in the executive chair, I know what it looks like from the other side: 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗧𝗲𝗻𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝗧𝗿𝗮𝗽.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWhen you are looking at the P&L, you are often staring at a brutal choice:\\\\\\\\n 1. Hire 10 Agency Nurses at a premium (Variable Cost).\\\\\\\\n 2. Raise the base rate to attract 10 Staff Nurses (Fixed Cost).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe math is unforgiving. Because of union step-scales or rigid pay bands, raising the Start Rate for those 10 new hires often legally triggers a pay reset for hundreds of existing clinicians.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI’ve seen the models where the cost of the agency contract was $2M, but the cost of the system-wide pay reset was $15M.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAdministrators don't sign that agency contract because they don't value their staff. 𝗧𝗵𝗲𝘆 𝘀𝗶𝗴𝗻 𝗶𝘁 𝗯𝗲𝗰𝗮𝘂𝘀𝗲 𝗮 𝗳𝗶𝘅𝗲𝗱-𝗰𝗼𝘀𝘁 𝗲𝘅𝗽𝗹𝗼𝘀𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝘄𝗼𝘂𝗹𝗱 𝗰𝗹𝗼𝘀𝗲 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗵𝗼𝘀𝗽𝗶𝘁𝗮𝗹 𝗱𝗼𝗼𝗿𝘀 𝗶𝗻 𝟴 𝗺𝗼𝗻𝘁𝗵𝘀.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe need to stop villainizing leaders for doing the only math that keeps the lights on.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe also need to give them a better tool than the agency. The smartest systems are now building Internal Resource Pools that capture the flexibility of the agency without the middleman markup.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYou don't need to break your pay scale. You just need to own the mechanism. 𝗧𝗵𝗮𝘁'𝘀 𝘄𝗵𝘆 𝘄𝗲 𝗯𝘂𝗶𝗹𝘁 𝗥𝗲𝗰𝗹𝗮𝗶𝗺𝗶𝘅. Watch this space...\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HealthcareLeadership \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HospitalAdministration \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#StaffingStrategy \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#CFO \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#Reclaimix\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n2mo • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n2 months ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"𝗨𝗻𝘀𝗼𝗹𝘃𝗮𝗯𝗹𝗲 𝗔𝗹𝗴𝗲𝗯𝗿𝗮\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" 𝗼𝗳 𝗛𝗲𝗮𝗹𝘁𝗵𝗰𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗳𝗳𝗶𝗻𝗴 📉: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"If you can afford to pay an agency nurse $100/hr, why can't you just pay your own staff $60/hr?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIt is the most common accusation thrown at healthcare leaders. On social media, it is framed as greed. In the boardroom, we know it is 𝗪𝗮𝗴𝗲 𝗖𝗼𝗺𝗽𝗿𝗲𝘀𝘀𝗶𝗼𝗻.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHere is the math that the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Agency vs. Staff\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" debate ignores:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝟭. 𝗧𝗵𝗲 \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"𝗕𝗶𝗹𝗹 𝗥𝗮𝘁𝗲\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" 𝗜𝗹𝗹𝘂𝘀𝗶𝗼𝗻 🎭 First, let’s kill the myth: The agency nurse is not pocketing that full $100/hr. Data shows the nurse typically takes home ~60-70% of the bill rate. The rest is the Agency Margin. You aren't just paying for labor. You are paying a premium for Flexibility and Liability Protection.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝟮. 𝗧𝗵𝗲 \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"𝗦𝘁𝗲𝗽 𝗦𝗰𝗮𝗹𝗲\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" 𝗛𝗮𝗻𝗱𝗰𝘂𝗳𝗳𝘀 🔗 But why not just pay your staff the $60? Because most hospital pay structures are rigid, locked by union contracts or tenure steps. \\\\\\\\n🔹 Step 1 (New Grad): $35/hr \\\\\\\\n🔹 Step 10 (20-Year Veteran): $55/hr\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝟯. 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗙𝗶𝘅𝗲𝗱-𝗖𝗼𝘀𝘁 𝗘𝘅𝗽𝗹𝗼𝘀𝗶𝗼𝗻 💥 To compete with the agency rate, you might want to raise that Step 1 offer to $50/hr. But you cannot just raise the floor; you have to raise the ceiling. If the New Grad gets a $15/hr bump, the 20-Year Veteran demands the same equity bump.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nLabor already consumes ~56% of hospital operating expenses. A targeted raise for 5 new hires triggers a mandatory systemic raise for 500 existing staff. Because reimbursement rates (Medicare/Medicaid) are fixed, that massive fixed-cost reset doesn't just cut into profits, it bankrupts the facility.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗦𝘁𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗲𝗴𝗶𝗰 𝗥𝗲𝗮𝗹𝗶𝘁𝘆: Hospitals use agencies to hedge their variable costs.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nUsing an agency allows a facility to pay a market premium for the specific, marginal labor they need right now (Variable Cost) without permanently resetting the base salary for their entire workforce (Fixed Cost).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe agency premium isn't wasted money. It is the cost of protecting your pay scale structure.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBut what if you could recapture that premium without the agency? There is a structural model that allows facilities to do exactly that. We call it 𝗥𝗲𝗰𝗹𝗮𝗶𝗺𝗶𝘅.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAnd we will be talking a lot more about it soon.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HealthcareFinance \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#StaffingStrategy \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#WageCompression \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HospitalAdministration \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#NavaHealthcare \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#Reclaimix\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nActivate to view larger image,\\\\\\\\nActivate to view larger image,\\\\\\\\n9\\\\\\\\n1 comment\\\\\\\\nLike\\\\\\\\nComment\\\\\\\\nRepost\\\\\\\\nSend\\\\\\\\nFeed post number 4\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston\\\\\\\\n   • 1st\\\\\\\\nPremium • 1st\\\\\\\\nChief Operating Officer & Co-Founder at Nava Healthcare Recruitment. Managing Director at Roston Management & Consulting.\\\\\\\\nChief Operating Officer & Co-Founder at Nava Healthcare Recruitment. Managing Director at Roston Management & Consulting.\\\\\\\\nVisit my website\\\\\\\\n3mo • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n3 months ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\nIf you hire your emergency team for a sunny day🌞🌞🌞, they, too, will need rescuing when the storm lands⛈️⛈️⛈️. \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAs leaders, we often write job descriptions for the facility we 𝘸𝘢𝘯𝘵 𝘵𝘰 𝘳𝘶𝘯: the one that is fully staffed, quiet, and operating perfectly with an occasional emergency or moment of chaos. But we usually need to hire for the facility we actually run 𝘁𝗼𝗱𝗮𝘆.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe recently helped a client in Alabama who was in the middle of a chaotic renovation. Walls were torn open. Contractors were drilling during shifts. Dust was everywhere.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThey needed a maintenance director. If we had sent them a \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"perfect on paper\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" candidate, someone with 10 years of experience in a pristine, 5-star facility, they likely would have quit in two weeks. Because a \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"peacetime\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" director often cannot survive in a warzone.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗜𝗻𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗮𝗱, 𝘄𝗲 𝗽𝗹𝗮𝗰𝗲𝗱 𝗚𝗿𝗲𝗴.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe didn't just vet Greg for his HVAC skills or safety compliance. We vetted him for Chaos Tolerance. He had specific experience managing maintenance in SNFs under construction. Where others would have seen a headache, Greg saw a project he knew how to finish.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHe didn’t just fill the role. 𝘏𝘦 𝘵𝘩𝘳𝘪𝘷𝘦𝘥 𝘪𝘯 𝘪𝘵.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nVisionaries make for great CEOs, building for a great future, but have a blind spot in accepting the reality of their current environment. If you are in a crisis, a renovation, or a turnaround, don't hire the candidate who looks good on the PDF. 𝗛𝗶𝗿𝗲 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗼𝗻𝗲 𝘄𝗵𝗼 𝗹𝗼𝗼𝗸𝘀 𝗴𝗼𝗼𝗱 𝗶𝗻 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗺𝘂𝗱.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#CEO \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#Leadership \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#CrisisManagement \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HealthcareOperations\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n3mo • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n3 months ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\n90% of recruitment focuses on the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"𝘞𝘩𝘢𝘵\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" (Skills/License). But retention depends almost entirely on the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"𝘞𝘩𝘦𝘳𝘦\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" (Environment) and \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"𝘞𝘩𝘦𝘯\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" (Timing and Personal Circumstances).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗪𝗲 𝗰𝗮𝗹𝗹 𝘁𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗮 𝗖𝗼𝗻𝘁𝗲𝘅𝘁 𝗚𝗮𝗽.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIn a static analysis, like a resume review, a candidate is defined by their past duties.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n • Can they chart?\\\\\\\\n • Do they have the credentials?\\\\\\\\n • Have they managed a team?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf the data points match the job description, the industry calls it a \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"placement\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBut healthcare facilities are not static environments. They are dynamic ecosystems. A facility under construction, a unit in a state of regulatory survey, a rural setting, or a floor experiencing high turnover requires a fundamentally different psychological profile than a stabilized, 5-star unit.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWhen agencies treat candidates as inventory (a collection of skills), they ignore the variable of 𝗘𝗻𝘃𝗶𝗿𝗼𝗻𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗮𝗹 𝗦𝘁𝗿𝗲𝘀𝘀.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHere is the 𝗡𝗮𝘃𝗮 𝗛𝗲𝗮𝗹𝘁𝗵𝗰𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗱𝗶𝗳𝗳𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗲: We sometimes must tell our candidates: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Your credentials are a perfect match. The salary is what you want. But trust us, this is not the right environment for you.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIt is a hard conversation. It means turning down a placement fee today to prevent a resignation next month.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nA \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"qualified\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" candidate in the wrong context is often not the asset you expect but a potential liability in the future. To fix retention, we must stop vetting for the 𝘳𝘰𝘭𝘦 and start vetting for the 𝘳𝘦𝘢𝘭𝘪𝘵𝘺.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe variable that predicts turnover isn't on the CV. It’s found in the 𝗿𝗲𝗹𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽𝘀 we build with our candidates and in the buildings in which they will save lives. If you want your talented staff to stay, it starts with cultural and environmental fit.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe break down why retention is the only recruitment metric that actually protects your units and financial health in our article: 👉 𝗛𝗼𝘄 𝘁𝗼 𝗘𝘃𝗮𝗹𝘂𝗮𝘁𝗲 𝗛𝗲𝗮𝗹𝘁𝗵𝗰𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗳𝗳𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗔𝗴𝗲𝗻𝗰𝘆 𝗣𝗲𝗿𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗺𝗮𝗻𝗰𝗲: https://lnkd.in/dD422E4B\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HealthcareRecruitment \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#OrganizationalDynamics \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#NavaHealthcare \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#RecruitmentStrategy\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nHow to Evaluate Healthcare Staffing Agency Performance in Healthcare Facilities\\\\\\\\nnavahc.com\\\\\\\\n5\\\\\\\\nYou and 4 others\\\\\\\\n3 reposts\\\\\\\\nLike\\\\\\\\nComment\\\\\\\\nRepost\\\\\\\\nSend\\\\\\\\nFeed post number 5\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston\\\\\\\\n   • 1st\\\\\\\\nPremium • 1st\\\\\\\\nChief Operating Officer & Co-Founder at Nava Healthcare Recruitment. Managing Director at Roston Management & Consulting.\\\\\\\\nChief Operating Officer & Co-Founder at Nava Healthcare Recruitment. Managing Director at Roston Management & Consulting.\\\\\\\\nVisit my website\\\\\\\\n3mo • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n3 months ago • Visible to Yosef’s connections\\\\\\\\nWe saved a client over $𝟲𝟬,𝟬𝟬𝟬 recently. Not through a sales call or getting them a new deal. We did it by making a phone call they didn't know they needed.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe were doing a routine check-in with a new star clinician when she told us, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I love the job, but I’m resigning next Thursday\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe facility had no idea; they were about to be blindsided.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe reason? Her son’s high school graduation was at 5:00 PM. She needed to leave her shift 2 hours early.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe facility’s handbook stated clearly: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"New employees don't qualify for PTO\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\". And so, she had tried to solve it the right way, but she hit a wall of necessary guardrails from her immediate superiors:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n 1. 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗳𝗳 𝗗𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗹𝗼𝗽𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗖𝗼𝗼𝗿𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗮𝘁𝗼𝗿 (𝗦𝗗𝗖): Denied the request. Her unit was already short-staffed. If she made an exception for the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"new hire,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" that would raise the eyebrows of tenured staff. She wasn't being mean; she was protecting her floor and avoiding a personal infraction.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n 2. 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗨𝗻𝗶𝘁 𝗠𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗿: Denied the request. The first question the unit manager asked was, “What did the SDC say?” The floor leader didn’t want to undermine the SDC’s authority and favor a new hire on a policy that is black and white.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝙀𝙫𝙚𝙧𝙮𝙤𝙣𝙚 𝙖𝙘𝙩𝙚𝙙 𝙧𝙖𝙩𝙞𝙤𝙣𝙖𝙡𝙡𝙮. 𝘼𝙣𝙙 𝙞𝙩 𝙬𝙖𝙨 𝙖𝙗𝙤𝙪𝙩 𝙩𝙤 𝙘𝙤𝙨𝙩 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙛𝙖𝙘𝙞𝙡𝙞𝙩𝙮 𝙖 𝙛𝙤𝙧𝙩𝙪𝙣𝙚.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBut we caught wind of the situation, intervened and called the CFO directly.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI didn't need to lecture him on retention economics. The moment I explained the impasse, that a policy technicality was forcing a resignation, he saw the math immediately.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHe knew exactly what was at stake:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n📉 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗙𝗶𝗻𝗮𝗻𝗰𝗶𝗮𝗹 𝗛𝗶𝘁: Over $60,000 in sunk costs (recruiting fees, background checks, credentialing, and 3 weeks of preceptor training).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n📉 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗢𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹 𝗛𝗶𝘁: Plunging the unit back into critical short-staffing.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n📉 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗠𝗼𝗿𝗮𝗹𝗲 𝗛𝗶𝘁: Losing a teammate the floor staff already loved.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAre we willing to burn that investment to save 2 hours of coverage? \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"𝗜𝘁'𝘀 𝗮 𝗻𝗼-𝗯𝗿𝗮𝗶𝗻𝗲𝗿,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" he said.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nShe got the time off and stayed. The investment was saved.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nMost recruiters would have never known she was unhappy until the resignation letter hit the desk. We knew because we never stopped talking to her.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Systemic Failure\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" is just one of three ways you are losing talented clinicians.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe mapped out the full diagnostic framework, and the underlying factors you are likely ignoring, in the breakdown below.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#CEO \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HealthcareLeadership \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#Retention\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n3mo • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n3 months ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\n𝗜𝗳 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝗵𝗶𝗿𝗲 𝗮 \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"𝗷𝗼𝗯 𝗯𝗼𝗮𝗿𝗱 𝘀𝗰𝗿𝗮𝗽𝗲𝗿\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" 𝗽𝗼𝘀𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝘀 𝗮 𝗿𝗲𝗰𝗿𝘂𝗶𝘁𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗽𝗮𝗿𝘁𝗻𝗲𝗿, 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝗰𝗮𝗻'𝘁 𝗯𝗲 𝘀𝘂𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲𝗱 𝘄𝗵𝗲𝗻 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗰𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝗰𝗼𝗺𝗲𝘀 𝗮 𝗿𝗲𝘃𝗼𝗹𝘃𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗱𝗼𝗼𝗿. And when that door spins fast, it's easier to blame the people than diagnose the problem.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nMost recruitment agencies operate on a simple, brutal logic: Volume.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThey hoover up CVs from job boards, scan for valid qualifications, and shove them into your inbox to hit a commission target. They don't vet for fit; they vet for a pulse.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis might get you a technical match on paper, but it leaves cultural alignment to chance. And in a talent-scarce market, a mismatch is a risk you can’t afford to take. Because when those mismatched hires inevitably quit within 90 days, the damage goes deeper than just an open shift.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYou aren't just facing financial loss; you are facing operational disarray, fractured team morale, and a burnout spiral for the staff left behind. In that high-pressure environment, administrators instinctively default to a binary blame game: Either the clinician was ill-equipped, or the agency was at fault.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nTo be clear: Often, 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝗰𝘆 𝗶𝘀 𝘁𝗼 𝗯𝗹𝗮𝗺𝗲.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf they treated your candidate like inventory, delivering the credentials on a CV rather than introducing the human behind the professional, the resignation is on them.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAfter analyzing our exit data, we found that turnover isn't just \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Bad Agency\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" vs \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Bad Candidate.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" It falls into three distinct buckets:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗨𝗻𝗮𝘃𝗼𝗶𝗱𝗮𝗯𝗹𝗲: Life events. (Data shows this accounts for less than 5% of early exits).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗧𝗿𝗮𝗻𝘀𝗮𝗰𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹: The mismatch. (The agency ignored your culture).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗦𝘆𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗺𝗶𝗰: The bureaucracy trap. (Minor internal barriers—like a rigid PTO policy or insurance wait time—that seem inconsequential to you but are critical to the clinician).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nMost agencies respond to a resignation by checking their warranty clause. They process the exit and send another warm body.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗪𝗲 𝗿𝗲𝘀𝗽𝗼𝗻𝗱 𝗯𝘆 𝗶𝗻𝘃𝗲𝘀𝘁𝗶𝗴𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗵𝗲 \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"𝘄𝗵𝘆?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe view retention as a structural puzzle. If a hire fails, we don't just look at 𝘸𝘩𝘰 𝘭𝘦𝘧𝘵; we look at 𝘸𝘩𝘢𝘵 𝘱𝘶𝘴𝘩𝘦𝘥 𝘵𝘩𝘦𝘮 𝘰𝘶𝘵.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWas it a preventable mismatch? Was it a rigid contractual condition or policy that needs to be bent? Or was it truly unavoidable?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf you aren't diagnosing the disease, you can't prevent it.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe break down the full anatomy of clinician turnover—and how to stop the bleeding—in our latest article.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n👉 Read \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"The Anatomy of a Clinician Turnover\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" here: [https://lnkd.in/dWibV3Hm]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#StaffingStrategy \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#Retention \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#CrisisByDesign \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#NavaHealthcare\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nActivate to view larger image,\\\\\\\\n1\\\\\\\\nLike\\\\\\\\nComment\\\\\\\\nFeed post number 6\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston reposted this\\\\\\\\nTiny Manyonga\\\\\\\\nTiny Manyonga\\\\\\\\n   • You\\\\\\\\nVerified • You\\\\\\\\nBusiness Development and Market Research Specialist | SQL + Python Data Scientist Professional | OpenClaw + Claude Code Enthusiast\\\\\\\\nBusiness Development and Market Research Specialist | SQL + Python Data Scientist Professional | OpenClaw + Claude Code Enthusiast\\\\\\\\n3mo • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n3 months ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\n𝗜𝗻 𝗮 𝗽𝗿𝗲𝘃𝗶𝗼𝘂𝘀 𝗹𝗶𝗳𝗲 𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝘀 𝗮𝗻 𝗦𝗗𝗥, 𝗜 𝗳𝗼𝘂𝗴𝗵𝘁 𝗮 𝗰𝗼𝗻𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗻𝘁 𝗯𝗮𝘁𝘁𝗹𝗲 𝗮𝗴𝗮𝗶𝗻𝘀𝘁 𝘁𝗵𝗲 \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"𝗩𝗼𝗹𝘂𝗺𝗲 𝗚𝗼𝗱\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\". 𝗡𝗼𝘄 𝗜 𝗮𝗺 𝗯𝗮𝘁𝘁𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗔𝗜𝘀 𝗯𝗮𝘁𝘁𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗼𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗿 𝗔𝗜𝘀.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe industry standard was simple: Make 200 cold calls per week. Send 500 emails. Play the numbers game. If you missed the target, the advice was always: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Do 𝘮𝘰𝘳𝘦\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\". \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBeing told to simply \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"do more\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" was demoralising. We were burning through leads and annoying prospects just to hit an activity metric.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThen, I moved to a new role at a different business.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHere, the primary KPIs were not 𝘰𝘶𝘵𝘳𝘦𝘢𝘤𝘩 𝘢𝘤𝘵𝘪𝘷𝘪𝘵𝘺, but a balance of clients onboarded and revenue potential. We understood that a new client with the capacity to grow was often more valuable than a stagnant account with higher immediate revenue.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗧𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗳𝘁 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗴𝗲𝗱 𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆𝘁𝗵𝗶𝗻𝗴.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI realized my most valuable assets, my time and my mind, were better deployed on high-quality interactions. I dropped the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"shotgun\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" approach and adopted a research-led strategy. When I made a call, I knew who I was talking to and what they needed.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe result? Conversion rates skyrocketed. That's how I found my way into leadership roles in business development: by escaping the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Volume Trap\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI’m seeing the same \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Volume Trap\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" playing out in recruitment with AI and Automation.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAs a Data Scientist, I love what AI can do. But I also know what it 𝘤𝘢𝘯'𝘵.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe are increasingly relying on algorithms and CV filters to screen human talent the same way bad sales teams rely on auto-dialers. But automation ≠ effectiveness.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAn algorithm can match a keyword. It cannot measure resilience, cultural fit, or leadership potential. Automating the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"vetting\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" process is automating the noise, not optimizing for quality. \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe result? An absurd arms race: To gain an edge, candidates use AI to write resumes to bypass the AI filters. Literally robots vs. robots, generating noise.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗗𝗮𝘁𝗮 𝘀𝗵𝗼𝘂𝗹𝗱 𝗶𝗻𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗺 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗱𝗲𝗰𝗶𝘀𝗶𝗼𝗻, 𝗯𝘂𝘁 𝗶𝘁 𝘀𝗵𝗼𝘂𝗹𝗱 𝗻𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿 𝗿𝗲𝗽𝗹𝗮𝗰𝗲 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗵𝘂𝗺𝗮𝗻 𝗶𝗻𝘀𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗰𝘁 𝗿𝗲𝗾𝘂𝗶𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗼 𝗮𝘀𝘀𝗲𝘀𝘀 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗿𝗮𝗰𝘁𝗲𝗿.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThat is why I resonate with the philosophy at Nava Healthcare. Just as I discarded the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Volume Model\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in sales, we are dismantling the transactional, speed-and-volume-first approach in healthcare recruitment to focus on retention and the humans in the process, not the data on the CV.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAI is an incredible tool I now rely on for previously week-long tasks I now do in hours. However, when dealing with humans - CFOs concerned about their bottom line, clinicians who may save a life - AI is simply 𝘨𝘶𝘦𝘴𝘴𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘸𝘪𝘵𝘩 𝘤𝘰𝘯𝘧𝘪𝘥𝘦𝘯𝘤𝘦. Just as sales prospects are more than a phone number and email address on a list, your candidates are more than certificates and keywords listed on a CV!\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSo, instead of an AI arms race, let's put humans back in recruitment.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#AI \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#SalesStrategy \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#Recruitment\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n3mo • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n3 months ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\n⛔𝗬𝗼𝘂 𝗸𝗻𝗼𝘄 𝘄𝗵𝗮𝘁? 𝗠𝗼𝘀𝘁 𝗿𝗲𝗰𝗿𝘂𝗶𝘁𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗶𝗲𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗲𝘅𝗽𝗲𝗻𝘀𝗶𝘃𝗲 𝗺𝗮𝗶𝗹-𝘀𝗼𝗿𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘀𝗲𝗿𝘃𝗶𝗰𝗲𝘀.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf you scroll through LinkedIn, it looks like staffing is just a marketing game. It’s a flood of \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Urgent Needs,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" stock photos of smiling teams, and generic promises of \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"quality candidates.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nRecruitment agents then find a resume on a job board, slap their logo on the top header, hit \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Forward,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" and wait for a 20% check.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThat isn't recruiting, that’s data entry.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAnd if you work inside the walls of a healthcare facility, you know that this \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"transactional\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" recruitment model is more than just an annoyance. Recruitment isn't a marketing problem. It is an 𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹 one.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIt’s about retention. It’s about compliance. It’s about the massive financial drag of vacancies that sit open because a resume didn't fit a keyword filter.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗔𝘁 𝗡𝗮𝘃𝗮 𝗛𝗲𝗮𝗹𝘁𝗵𝗰𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗥𝗲𝗰𝗿𝘂𝗶𝘁𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁, 𝘄𝗲 𝗵𝗮𝘃𝗲 𝗻𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿 𝗽𝗹𝗮𝘆𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗵𝗲 \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"𝘁𝗿𝗮𝗻𝘀𝗮𝗰𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" 𝗴𝗮𝗺𝗲.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFor years, we have operated on a different set of principles — focusing on the structures, the pipelines, and the long-term fit rather than the quick fee, which is why we have abandoned upfront fees altogether. We’ve been doing the heavy lifting in the background: fixing broken hiring processes and vetting for retention, not just licensure.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBut our social media hasn't always reflected that depth. We’ve been quiet about the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"how.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗧𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗴𝗲𝘀 𝗻𝗼𝘄.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe are bringing our internal philosophy to our public conversation. We are stepping away from the noise of the standard \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"job board\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" posting style to focus on what matters to C-Suites and decision-makers.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗠𝗼𝘃𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗳𝗼𝗿𝘄𝗮𝗿𝗱, 𝘁𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗽𝗮𝗴𝗲 𝘄𝗶𝗹𝗹 𝗯𝗲 𝗮 𝗿𝗲𝘀𝗼𝘂𝗿𝗰𝗲, 𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗮 𝗯𝘂𝗹𝗹𝗲𝘁𝗶𝗻 𝗯𝗼𝗮𝗿𝗱.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe are going to talk about: \\\\\\\\n🔹 The real financial impact of the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"DIY\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" recruitment myth. \\\\\\\\n🔹 How operational bottlenecks (like interpretation delays) are actually staffing issues. \\\\\\\\n🔹 The systemic cracks that cause burnout—and how to pave over them. \\\\\\\\n🔹 Real strategies to move from \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"reactive filling\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" to \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"proactive pipelines.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe vacancies aren't going away, and we will continue to help you fill them with the best talent in the market. That remains our core.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBut the conversation around 𝘩𝘰𝘸 we solve the shortage needs to level up.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe’re ready to have it, 𝘢𝘳𝘦 𝘺𝘰𝘶?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#NavaHealthcare \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#CrisisByDesign \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#StaffingStrategy \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HealthcareLeadership\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nPlay\\\\\\\\nLoaded: 100.00%\\\\\\\\nRemaining time \\\\\\\\n0:02\\\\\\\\n1x\\\\\\\\nPlayback speed\\\\\\\\nUnmute\\\\\\\\nTurn fullscreen on\\\\\\\\n5\\\\\\\\n1 repost\\\\\\\\nLike\\\\\\\\nComment\\\\\\\\nRepost\\\\\\\\nSend\\\\\\\\nFeed post number 7\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston reposted this\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n3mo • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n3 months ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\n⛔𝗬𝗼𝘂 𝗸𝗻𝗼𝘄 𝘄𝗵𝗮𝘁? 𝗠𝗼𝘀𝘁 𝗿𝗲𝗰𝗿𝘂𝗶𝘁𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗶𝗲𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗲𝘅𝗽𝗲𝗻𝘀𝗶𝘃𝗲 𝗺𝗮𝗶𝗹-𝘀𝗼𝗿𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘀𝗲𝗿𝘃𝗶𝗰𝗲𝘀.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf you scroll through LinkedIn, it looks like staffing is just a marketing game. It’s a flood of \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Urgent Needs,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" stock photos of smiling teams, and generic promises of \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"quality candidates.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nRecruitment agents then find a resume on a job board, slap their logo on the top header, hit \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Forward,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" and wait for a 20% check.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThat isn't recruiting, that’s data entry.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAnd if you work inside the walls of a healthcare facility, you know that this \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"transactional\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" recruitment model is more than just an annoyance. Recruitment isn't a marketing problem. It is an 𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹 one.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIt’s about retention. It’s about compliance. It’s about the massive financial drag of vacancies that sit open because a resume didn't fit a keyword filter.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗔𝘁 𝗡𝗮𝘃𝗮 𝗛𝗲𝗮𝗹𝘁𝗵𝗰𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗥𝗲𝗰𝗿𝘂𝗶𝘁𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁, 𝘄𝗲 𝗵𝗮𝘃𝗲 𝗻𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿 𝗽𝗹𝗮𝘆𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗵𝗲 \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"𝘁𝗿𝗮𝗻𝘀𝗮𝗰𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" 𝗴𝗮𝗺𝗲.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFor years, we have operated on a different set of principles — focusing on the structures, the pipelines, and the long-term fit rather than the quick fee, which is why we have abandoned upfront fees altogether. We’ve been doing the heavy lifting in the background: fixing broken hiring processes and vetting for retention, not just licensure.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBut our social media hasn't always reflected that depth. We’ve been quiet about the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"how.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗧𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗴𝗲𝘀 𝗻𝗼𝘄.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe are bringing our internal philosophy to our public conversation. We are stepping away from the noise of the standard \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"job board\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" posting style to focus on what matters to C-Suites and decision-makers.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗠𝗼𝘃𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗳𝗼𝗿𝘄𝗮𝗿𝗱, 𝘁𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗽𝗮𝗴𝗲 𝘄𝗶𝗹𝗹 𝗯𝗲 𝗮 𝗿𝗲𝘀𝗼𝘂𝗿𝗰𝗲, 𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗮 𝗯𝘂𝗹𝗹𝗲𝘁𝗶𝗻 𝗯𝗼𝗮𝗿𝗱.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe are going to talk about: \\\\\\\\n🔹 The real financial impact of the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"DIY\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" recruitment myth. \\\\\\\\n🔹 How operational bottlenecks (like interpretation delays) are actually staffing issues. \\\\\\\\n🔹 The systemic cracks that cause burnout—and how to pave over them. \\\\\\\\n🔹 Real strategies to move from \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"reactive filling\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" to \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"proactive pipelines.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe vacancies aren't going away, and we will continue to help you fill them with the best talent in the market. That remains our core.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBut the conversation around 𝘩𝘰𝘸 we solve the shortage needs to level up.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe’re ready to have it, 𝘢𝘳𝘦 𝘺𝘰𝘶?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#NavaHealthcare \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#CrisisByDesign \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#StaffingStrategy \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HealthcareLeadership\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nPlay\\\\\\\\n5\\\\\\\\n4 reposts\\\\\\\\nLike\\\\\\\\nComment\\\\\\\\nRepost\\\\\\\\nSend\\\\\\\\nFeed post number 8\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston reposted this\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n3mo • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n3 months ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\n⛔𝗬𝗼𝘂 𝗸𝗻𝗼𝘄 𝘄𝗵𝗮𝘁? 𝗠𝗼𝘀𝘁 𝗿𝗲𝗰𝗿𝘂𝗶𝘁𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗶𝗲𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗲𝘅𝗽𝗲𝗻𝘀𝗶𝘃𝗲 𝗺𝗮𝗶𝗹-𝘀𝗼𝗿𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘀𝗲𝗿𝘃𝗶𝗰𝗲𝘀.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf you scroll through LinkedIn, it looks like staffing is just a marketing game. It’s a flood of \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Urgent Needs,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" stock photos of smiling teams, and generic promises of \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"quality candidates.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nRecruitment agents then find a resume on a job board, slap their logo on the top header, hit \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Forward,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" and wait for a 20% check.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThat isn't recruiting, that’s data entry.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAnd if you work inside the walls of a healthcare facility, you know that this \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"transactional\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" recruitment model is more than just an annoyance. Recruitment isn't a marketing problem. It is an 𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹 one.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIt’s about retention. It’s about compliance. It’s about the massive financial drag of vacancies that sit open because a resume didn't fit a keyword filter.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗔𝘁 𝗡𝗮𝘃𝗮 𝗛𝗲𝗮𝗹𝘁𝗵𝗰𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗥𝗲𝗰𝗿𝘂𝗶𝘁𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁, 𝘄𝗲 𝗵𝗮𝘃𝗲 𝗻𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿 𝗽𝗹𝗮𝘆𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗵𝗲 \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"𝘁𝗿𝗮𝗻𝘀𝗮𝗰𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" 𝗴𝗮𝗺𝗲.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFor years, we have operated on a different set of principles — focusing on the structures, the pipelines, and the long-term fit rather than the quick fee, which is why we have abandoned upfront fees altogether. We’ve been doing the heavy lifting in the background: fixing broken hiring processes and vetting for retention, not just licensure.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBut our social media hasn't always reflected that depth. We’ve been quiet about the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"how.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗧𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗴𝗲𝘀 𝗻𝗼𝘄.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe are bringing our internal philosophy to our public conversation. We are stepping away from the noise of the standard \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"job board\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" posting style to focus on what matters to C-Suites and decision-makers.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n𝗠𝗼𝘃𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗳𝗼𝗿𝘄𝗮𝗿𝗱, 𝘁𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗽𝗮𝗴𝗲 𝘄𝗶𝗹𝗹 𝗯𝗲 𝗮 𝗿𝗲𝘀𝗼𝘂𝗿𝗰𝗲, 𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗮 𝗯𝘂𝗹𝗹𝗲𝘁𝗶𝗻 𝗯𝗼𝗮𝗿𝗱.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe are going to talk about: \\\\\\\\n🔹 The real financial impact of the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"DIY\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" recruitment myth. \\\\\\\\n🔹 How operational bottlenecks (like interpretation delays) are actually staffing issues. \\\\\\\\n🔹 The systemic cracks that cause burnout—and how to pave over them. \\\\\\\\n🔹 Real strategies to move from \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"reactive filling\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" to \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"proactive pipelines.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe vacancies aren't going away, and we will continue to help you fill them with the best talent in the market. That remains our core.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBut the conversation around 𝘩𝘰𝘸 we solve the shortage needs to level up.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWe’re ready to have it, 𝘢𝘳𝘦 𝘺𝘰𝘶?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#NavaHealthcare \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#CrisisByDesign \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#StaffingStrategy \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HealthcareLeadership\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nPlay\\\\\\\\n5\\\\\\\\n4 reposts\\\\\\\\nLike\\\\\\\\nComment\\\\\\\\nRepost\\\\\\\\nSend\\\\\\\\nFeed post number 9\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston reposted this\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n4mo • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n4 months ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\nAdvance Your Career | AM CNA & PM Nurse (RN/LPN) │📍 Montgomery County, AL \\\\\\\\n🕒 Schedule: Full-time (AM & PM Shifts Available, 12-hr for Nurses) \\\\\\\\n🎯 Perks: Up to $12K Bonus for RNs, Priority CNA Hiring\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n🧠 What You’ll Do: \\\\\\\\n🩺 Provide high-quality, compassionate direct care to residents. \\\\\\\\n🤝 Assist with ADLs, administer medications, and monitor health. \\\\\\\\n👥 Collaborate with a dedicated team across shifts.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n✅ What You Bring: \\\\\\\\n📋 Valid Alabama RN, LPN, or CNA license/certification. \\\\\\\\n🌟 Dedication to resident well-being and geriatric care. \\\\\\\\n💡 Reliability and commitment to consistent shifts.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n💡 Benefits & Culture: \\\\\\\\n💰 Competitive pay, with generous bonuses for RNs (up to $12K) and LPNs (up to $6K). \\\\\\\\n🎁 Bonuses distributed weekly after 30 days for eligible team members. \\\\\\\\n📅 Full-time, stable scheduling with priority for AM CNAs and 12-hour PM Nurse shifts. \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n🌟 Join a supportive team environment with urgent hiring needs.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n👉 Apply now: https://lnkd.in/dcK_Zi7v\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nActivate to view larger image,\\\\\\\\nActivate to view larger image,\\\\\\\\n5\\\\\\\\n1 repost\\\\\\\\nLike\\\\\\\\nComment\\\\\\\\nRepost\\\\\\\\nSend\\\\\\\\nFeed post number 10\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston reposted this\\\\\\\\nJoe Carvalho, B.Sc., MBA, ChFC®\\\\\\\\nJoe Carvalho, B.Sc., MBA, ChFC®\\\\\\\\n   • 2nd\\\\\\\\nPremium • 2nd\\\\\\\\nManaging Director at ROARANGE BUSINESS STRATEGIES, LLC and Learn To Pilot .COM®\\\\\\\\nManaging Director at ROARANGE BUSINESS STRATEGIES, LLC and Learn To Pilot .COM®\\\\\\\\n4mo • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n4 months ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\nFollow\\\\\\\\nEver thought of a career in Aviation? \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhttps://lnkd.in/ejUDmaSF\\\\\\\\nIn Focus🎥# 7: The YoJoeShow™ Podcast - Inside Aviation Careers - North Perry Airport Community Day!\\\\\\\\nyoutube.com\\\\\\\\n3\\\\\\\\n1 repost\\\\\\\\nLike\\\\\\\\nComment\\\\\\\\nRepost\\\\\\\\nSend\\\\\\\\nFeed post number 11\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston\\\\\\\\n   • 1st\\\\\\\\nPremium • 1st\\\\\\\\nChief Operating Officer & Co-Founder at Nava Healthcare Recruitment. Managing Director at Roston Management & Consulting.\\\\\\\\nChief Operating Officer & Co-Founder at Nava Healthcare Recruitment. Managing Director at Roston Management & Consulting.\\\\\\\\nVisit my website\\\\\\\\n4mo • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n4 months ago • Visible to Yosef’s connections\\\\\\\\nGreat company!\\\\\\\\nCool platform, very useful!\\\\\\\\nGreenClick\\\\\\\\nGreenClick\\\\\\\\n37 followers\\\\\\\\n37 followers\\\\\\\\n4mo • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n4 months ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\nFollow\\\\\\\\nIntroducing GreenClick — Where eCommerce Simplicity Meets MSP Complexity!\\\\\\\\nWe’re excited to officially launch GreenClick, a next-generation cloud management platform built to empower Managed Service Providers (MSPs), distributors, and resellers with the tools they need to scale smarter.\\\\\\\\nFor too long, managing cloud infrastructure has been complex, scattered systems, manual billing, and disconnected provisioning.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nGreenClick changes that.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nOur multi-tier multi-tenant SaaS platform brings the simplicity of eCommerce to the complexity of MSP operations, unifying provisioning, billing, automation, and analytics under one seamless experience.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n🤝 We’re proud to be working with Ofek Dist as our design partner — helping us shape GreenClick into the most intuitive, powerful platform for cloud distributors in Israel and beyond.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n💡 If you’re a distributor of SaaS solutions with a Microsoft 365 Tier 1 or Tier 2 agreement, we’re currently inviting additional design partners to collaborate on the next generation of MSP and cloud commerce infrastructure.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n🌍 Designed for global scalability.\\\\\\\\n⚙️ Built for those who build the future of cloud.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#GreenClick \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#CloudManagement \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#MSP \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#SaaS \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#Microsoft365 \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#DigitalTransformation \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#CloudInfrastructure \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#OfekDistribution \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#PartnerProgram \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#Innovation\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nGreenClick | LinkedIn\\\\\\\\nil.linkedin.com\\\\\\\\n1\\\\\\\\nLike\\\\\\\\nComment\\\\\\\\nFeed post number 12\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston reposted this\\\\\\\\nTiny Manyonga\\\\\\\\nTiny Manyonga\\\\\\\\n   • You\\\\\\\\nVerified • You\\\\\\\\nBusiness Development and Market Research Specialist | SQL + Python Data Scientist Professional | OpenClaw + Claude Code Enthusiast\\\\\\\\nBusiness Development and Market Research Specialist | SQL + Python Data Scientist Professional | OpenClaw + Claude Code Enthusiast\\\\\\\\n5mo • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n5 months ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\nCare With Purpose | PM&R Physician │📍 Bronx/Westchester, NY \\\\\\\\n💰 Salary: Up to $275K/year + Significant Bonuses \\\\\\\\n🎯 Perks: Performance-Based Comp, Specialized Cases\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n🧠 What You’ll Do: \\\\\\\\n🩺 Focus on Workers' Compensation and No-Fault/Lien cases. \\\\\\\\n🔄 Work at a few facilities across the Bronx and Westchester County. \\\\\\\\n🗓️ Require weekend availability, serving a unique patient population.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n✅ What You Bring: \\\\\\\\n📜 New York State WCB (Workers' Compensation Board) Certified. \\\\\\\\n⏱️ Minimum 2 years experience with WC/No-Fault/Lien cases. \\\\\\\\n🎓 Board Certified in Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation (PM&R).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n💡 Benefits & Culture: \\\\\\\\n💸 Compensation heavily weighted with significant performance-based bonuses. \\\\\\\\n📈 Opportunity to specialize in a specific patient population. \\\\\\\\n🌟 Varied work settings across multiple clinics.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n👉 Apply now: https://lnkd.in/dySKynrv\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nActivate to view larger image,\\\\\\\\nActivate to view larger image,\\\\\\\\n5\\\\\\\\n2 reposts\\\\\\\\nLike\\\\\\\\nComment\\\\\\\\nRepost\\\\\\\\nSend\\\\\\\\nFeed post number 13\\\\\\\\nYosef Roston reposted this\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n355 followers\\\\\\\\n5mo • \\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\n5 months ago • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn\\\\\\\\n𝗗𝗼𝗲𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗿𝗲𝗰𝗿𝘂𝗶𝘁𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗽𝗮𝗿𝘁𝗻𝗲𝗿’𝘀 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗰𝗲𝘀𝘀 𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿 𝗳𝗲𝗲𝗹 𝗹𝗲𝘀𝘀 𝗹𝗶𝗸𝗲 𝗮 𝘀𝘁𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗲𝗴𝗶𝗰 𝘀𝗲𝗮𝗿𝗰𝗵 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗺𝗼𝗿𝗲 𝗹𝗶𝗸𝗲 𝗮 𝗻𝘂𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿𝘀 𝗴𝗮𝗺𝗲?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe hard truth is that traditional agency models are built to reward 𝘴𝘱𝘦𝘦𝘥 𝘢𝘯𝘥 𝘷𝘰𝘭𝘶𝘮𝘦, not 𝗿𝗲𝘁𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗳𝗶𝘁. When the incentive is just to make a placement, the crucial work of vetting for cultural alignment and long-term commitment becomes an obstacle, not a priority.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe trust deficit in healthcare staffing isn't an accident; it's a feature of a broken system. In a recent article of our series, 𝗖𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗶𝘀 𝗯𝘆 𝗗𝗲𝘀𝗶𝗴𝗻, we diagnose the fractured trust between healthcare facilities and the agents meant to represent them in the talent market before outlining the blueprint for a better model.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nRead the full analysis here: https://lnkd.in/dHhnYYGb\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HealthcareRecruitment \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HealthcareLeadership \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#StaffingAgency \\\\\\\\nhashtag\\\\\\\\n#HiringStrategy\\\\\\\\n…more\\\\\\\\nActivate to view larger image,\\\\\\\\nActivate to view larger image,\\\\\\\\n2\\\\\\\\n2 reposts\\\\\\\\nLike\\\\\\\\nComment\\\\\\\\nRepost\\\\\\\\nSend\\\\\\\\nFeed post number 14\\\\\\\\nYosef Rost