],\\n          \\\"api\\\": \\\"openai-codex-responses\\\",\\n          \\\"provider\\\": \\\"openai-codex\\\",\\n          \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.3-codex\\\",\\n          \\\"stopReason\\\": \\\"error\\\",\\n          \\\"timestamp\\\": 1773769557039,\\n          \\\"errorMessage\\\": \\\"You have hit your ChatGPT usage limit (plus plan). Try again in ~148 min.\\\"\\n        }\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"key\\\": \\\"agent:main:main\\\",\\n      \\\"kind\\\": \\\"other\\\",\\n      \\\"channel\\\": \\\"webchat\\\",\\n      \\\"displayName\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui\\\",\\n      \\\"deliveryContext\\\": {\\n        \\\"channel\\\": \\\"webchat\\\",\\n        \\\"accountId\\\": \\\"default\\\"\\n      },\\n      \\\"updatedAt\\\": 1773816135080,\\n      \\\"sessionId\\\": \\\"044cb562-e9da-47a3-af53-8fb47df6e464\\\",\\n      \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.3-codex\\\",\\n      \\\"contextTokens\\\": 272000,\\n      \\\"totalTokens\\\": 16379,\\n      \\\"systemSent\\\": true,\\n      \\\"abortedLastRun\\\": false,\\n      \\\"lastChannel\\\": \\\"webchat\\\",\\n      \\\"lastAccountId\\\": \\\"default\\\",\\n      \\\"transcriptPath\\\": \\\"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/044cb562-e9da-47a3-af53-8fb47df6e464.jsonl\\\",\\n      \\\"messages\\\": [\\n        {\\n          \\\"role\\\": \\\"assistant\\\",\\n          \\\"content\\\": [\\n            {\\n              \\\"type\\\": \\\"thinking\\\",\\n              \\\"thinking\\\": \\\"**Summarizing yesterday's progress**\\\"\\n            },\\n            {\\n              \\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\",\\n              \\\"text\\\": \\\" Yep — yesterday’s progress was strong.  \\\\n\\\\n**Nava sprint (crawl → synthesis → full RAG):**\\\\n\\\\n**✅ Completed**\\\\n- Crawled **22 navahc.com articles** into corpus (`rag/raw_html`, `rag/clean_txt`)\\\\n- Built synthesis docs (`rag/synthesis/Nava_Website_Synthesis_v1.md` + midpoint notes)\\\\n- Built chunk corpus (`rag/index/chunks.jsonl`) — initially 723 chunks, later expanded\\\\n- Delivered working **RAG v1 pipeline** (crawl artifacts, synthesis, chunking, BM25 retrieval, query CLI, smoke tests, operator guide)\\\\n- Upgraded to **full RAG v2 scope**:\\\\n  - hybrid retrieval\\\\n  - vector fallback index\\\\n  - contradiction/gap matrix\\\\n  - best-practices doc\\\\n  - tomorrow report artifacts\\\\n- Vector backend stabilized via **fastembed** after sentence-transformers/CUDA path failed due network/install instability\\\\n- Rebuilt vector index successfully (**~1741 chunks**) with updated query path\\\\n\\\\n**🟡 In progress / carrying forward**\\\\n- Skill research for LinkedIn/X/RSS integrations (safety-first posture)\\\\n- Morning briefing/report handoff and optional next optimization pass\\\\n\\\\n**🚫 Blockers**\\\\n- No persistent project blockers on Nava pipeline itself by end of day.\\\\n- Separate intermittent issue observed: gateway/tool fetch instability (infra, not RAG content pipeline).\\\\n\\\\nIf you want, I can now turn this into a tight **“Yesterday / Today / Risks”** standup format in 6 lines.\\\",\\n              \\\"textSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"v\\\\\\\":1,\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"msg_09c1eed3dfa3a32d0169ba48987aa4819b8bd3b705a77be460\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"phase\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"final_answer\\\\\\\"}\\\"\\n            }\\n          ],\\n          \\\"api\\\": \\\"openai-codex-responses\\\",\\n          \\\"provider\\\": \\\"openai-codex\\\",\\n          \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.3-codex\\\",\\n          \\\"stopReason\\\": \\\"stop\\\",\\n          \\\"timestamp\\\": 1773815956110\\n        },\\n        {\\n          \\\"role\\\": \\\"user\\\",\\n          \\\"content\\\": [\\n            {\\n              \\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\",\\n              \\\"text\\\": \\\"This is fine. Can you explain this project blockers thing because it's not clear to me.\\\"\\n            }\\n          ],\\n          \\\"timestamp\\\": 1773816128501,\\n          \\\"senderLabel\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\\\"\\n        },\\n        {\\n          \\\"role\\\": \\\"assistant\\\",\\n          \\\"content\\\": [\\n            {\\n              \\\"type\\\": \\\"thinking\\\",\\n              \\\"thinking\\\": \\\"**Explaining blocker concept**\\\"\\n            },\\n            {\\n              \\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\",\\n              \\\"text\\\": \\\" Good call — “project blockers” was ambiguous.\\\\n\\\\nIn plain terms:\\\\n\\\\n- **Project blocker** = something that prevents progress on the Nava deliverable itself (crawl/synthesis/RAG), e.g. missing data, broken pipeline logic, unresolved access/permissions, failed indexing with no fallback.\\\\n- **Not a project blocker** = noisy but non-fatal issues around it, e.g. intermittent gateway fetch errors, if the actual Nava pipeline can still run and outputs are complete.\\\\n\\\\nSo when I said **“no persistent project blockers”**, I meant:\\\\n- The **Nava workstream was still deliverable** end-to-end.\\\\n- We had hiccups (like fetch/gateway instability), but they **didn’t stop completion** because we had working paths/fallbacks.\\\\n\\\\nIf you want, I’ll split future reports into:\\\\n1) **Delivery blockers (hard stop)**\\\\n2) **Operational issues (annoying but survivable)**\\\\n3) **Risks (could become blockers)**\\\",\\n              \\\"textSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"v\\\\\\\":1,\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"msg_09c1eed3dfa3a32d0169ba4943d59c819bb3fd7aa2bb977325\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"phase\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"final_answer\\\\\\\"}\\\"\\n            }\\n          ],\\n          \\\"api\\\": \\\"openai-codex-responses\\\",\\n          \\\"provider\\\": \\\"openai-codex\\\",\\n          \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.3-codex\\\",\\n          \\\"stopReason\\\": \\\"stop\\\",\\n          \\\"timestamp\\\": 1773816128503\\n        }\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"key\\\": \\\"agent:main:direct:me\\\",\\n      \\\"kind\\\": \\\"other\\\",\\n      \\\"channel\\\": \\\"webchat\\\",\\n      \\\"displayName\\\": \\\"webchat:g-age