{"type":"message","id":"3effd1df","parentId":"a32fcf21","timestamp":"2026-03-23T12:58:20.572Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_b0516b06-1fd3-47b3-a148-36fb8b0c95d0","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"57:navahc.com\n99:[Image of a graphic with text: 1. Counting the Costs: Why Reactive Recruitment Fails Medical Staffing Strategies navahc.com]\n146:[Image of a person with text: 2. Slow by Design: How Bureaucracy Is Crippling Medical Staffing navahc.com]\n201:[Image of a man in a suit in front of a blurred office background with text: \"3. The Job Board Trap: How It's Fueling a Healthcare Recruiter Crisis\" and \"navahc.com\"]\n238:This article explores the often-overlooked handoff between insight and action:\n250:🧵 Catch up on earlier parts → https://navahc.com/blog/\n253:[Image of article with title: 4. Bridging the Gap: Essential Requirements for Effective Medical Recruitment navahc.com]\n335:⚠️ In this article, we unpack: \n346:[Image of a man in a suit with the text \"5. The Architecture of Trust: Exposing Critical Failures in Healthcare Recruitment Agencies\" and the website \"navahc.com\"]\n382:The first article of our 10-part series, *Crisis By Design*, breaks down the quantifiable losses in liability, turnover, and revenue. Read the full analysis here.\n420:The trust deficit in healthcare staffing isn’t an accident; it’s a feature of a broken system. In a recent article of our series, *Crisis by Design*, we diagnose the fractured trust between healthcare facilities and the agents meant to represent them in the talent market before outlining the blueprint for a better model.\n598:We’re breaking down the full anatomy of clinician turnover—and how to stop the bleed—in our latest article.\n758:We break down why retention is the only recruitment metric that actually protects your units and financial health in our article: ✍️ How to Evaluate Healthcare Staffing Agency Performance: https://lnkd.in/dD422E4B\n762:[Image of a person with text \"How to Evaluate Healthcare Staffing Agency Performance in Healthcare Facilities navahc.com\"]\n852:[Image of a blog post titled \"The Anatomy of a Clinician Turnover: Why Your New Clinician Quit\" with the URL navahc.com]\n944:[Image of a book cover with text: Available vs. Adaptable: How to Fix Your Flexible Staffing Model in Healthcare Staffing. Website address: navahc.com]\n1195:[Image of article with text: How to Find the Best Medical Recruiting Agencies navahc.com]"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":11,"aggregated":"57:navahc.com\n99:[Image of a graphic with text: 1. Counting the Costs: Why Reactive Recruitment Fails Medical Staffing Strategies navahc.com]\n146:[Image of a person with text: 2. Slow by Design: How Bureaucracy Is Crippling Medical Staffing navahc.com]\n201:[Image of a man in a suit in front of a blurred office background with text: \"3. The Job Board Trap: How It's Fueling a Healthcare Recruiter Crisis\" and \"navahc.com\"]\n238:This article explores the often-overlooked handoff between insight and action:\n250:🧵 Catch up on earlier parts → https://navahc.com/blog/\n253:[Image of article with title: 4. Bridging the Gap: Essential Requirements for Effective Medical Recruitment navahc.com]\n335:⚠️ In this article, we unpack: \n346:[Image of a man in a suit with the text \"5. The Architecture of Trust: Exposing Critical Failures in Healthcare Recruitment Agencies\" and the website \"navahc.com\"]\n382:The first article of our 10-part series, *Crisis By Design*, breaks down the quantifiable losses in liability, turnover, and revenue. Read the full analysis here.\n420:The trust deficit in healthcare staffing isn’t an accident; it’s a feature of a broken system. In a recent article of our series, *Crisis by Design*, we diagnose the fractured trust between healthcare facilities and the agents meant to represent them in the talent market before outlining the blueprint for a better model.\n598:We’re breaking down 