{"type":"message","id":"ca12b07f","parentId":"10365aa6","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:18:01.233Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"It makes sense. Here's why you'd make this request:\n\nEvery time I can't find something I built, two things are usually true:\n1. The thing exists somewhere in the workspace\n2. I didn't check the right directory because I don't have a mental map of the full workspace structure\n\nThe solution is a disambiguation trigger — a heartbeat reminder that fires when I'm cold-starting a task and might reach for the wrong directory. The reminder tells me \"there's a resource map at X\" without loading the map into the initial prompt. When I need a specific resource, I check the map. When I don't need it, it costs nothing.\n\nThe pattern it's breaking is: **assert → wrong → admit**. If I check the map first, the assertions become verifiable before I make them.\n\nSo the full plan:\n\n1. **Write the map** — corpus locations, backup locations, key project paths — to MEMORY.md\n2. **Heartbeat reminder** — fires on startup, tells me \"resource map is in MEMORY.md, check it when working on Nava tasks\"\n3. **Map contents stay out of initial context** — only the reminder fires, not the full map\n\nWant me to also include the backup locations specifically, or just the corpus/project structure?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":47758,"output":505,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48263,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1774271881231}}
