{"type":"message","id":"9f94b59c","parentId":"364b95f1","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:23:32.745Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_bc11b49c-e59c-4383-b0ed-6911684b205c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Skills & Tools — Durable Facts (2026-03-22)\n\n**mcporter:** Binary installed (`npm install -g mcporter` 2026-03-22). Enables MCP server connectivity — connect to Linear, GitHub, Slack, or any MCP-compatible service.\n\n**Screenshot folder:** `C:\\Users\\Tiny4Lurv\\OpenClawScreenshots\\` — Tiny takes screenshots manually, I read via `read` tool and pipe to gemma3:27b-cloud vision.\n\n**win-mouse-native:** Workspace skill for Windows mouse control (move/click/drag via user32.dll). NOT used for screenshots — that's a manual process.\n\n**session-logs skill:** Symlinked to `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/session-logs/` — use jq to read session JSONL files, NOT `sessions_history` API (truncates at ~15k bytes).\n\n**Visible browser:** `skills/visible-browser/` — WSL Chromium visible on Windows desktop via WSLg. Startup: `export DISPLAY=:0 && export ELECTRON_OZONE_PLATFORM_HINT=auto && killall -9 chromium && nohup /usr/bin/chromium-browser --no-sandbox --remote-debugging-port=18801 --user-data-dir=/tmp/chromium-visible > /tmp/chromium_visible.log 2>&1 &`\n\n---\n\n*Updated: 2026-03-22*\n\n## Screenshot Workflow (2026-03-19)\n\n**Windows screenshots folder (WSL path):**\n`/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Pictures/Screenshots 1/`\n\nAlways `ls -lt` the folder to find the latest file — don't rely on memory for filenames.\n\n**Gemma vision workflow:**\n```python\npython3 - <<'PY'\nimport base64, json, urllib.request\nimg_path = \"/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Pictures/Screenshots 1/Screenshot 2026-03-19 233725.png\"\nwith open(img_path, \"rb\") as f:\n    img_b64 = base64.b64encode(f.read()).decode()\npayload = {\"model\": \"gemma3:27b-cloud\", \"messages\":[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Describe this image in detail.\", \"images\": [img_b64]}], \"stream\": False}\nreq = urllib.request.Request(\"http://localhost:11434/api/chat\", data=json.dumps(payload).encode(), headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}, method=\"POST\")\nwith urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=60) as r:\n    print(json.loads(r.read())[\"message\"][\"content\"])\nPY\n```\n\n## Token Limit Issue (2026-03-19)\n\n- **Problem**: Context limit errors with Ollama cloud models\n- Config has `contextWindow: 204800` for minimax-m2.5:cloud, but API rejects prompts exceeding actual model limits\n- Session hit \"prompt too long; exceeded max context length by 142-228 tokens\"\n- **Fix**: Lower contextWindow in config (recommend 128000 or lower) to prevent overflow errors\n\n---\n\n## Browser Relay Setup (2026-03-19)\n\n### Architecture\n- **chrome-extension** folder: Chrome extension to install in your Windows Chrome\n- **Relay server**: Runs in WSL gateway on port 18792\n- **Connection**: Windows Chrome extension → connects to WSL relay (port 18792) → Gateway controls it\n\n### Fix for \"Profile not found\" errors\n1. **Never set defaultProfile in config** — it breaks the relay\n2. **To use chrome-relay**: always pass `--browser-profile chrome-relay`\n3. **If errors occur**: Check `openclaw browser profiles` — if you see profiles but get errors, restart gateway\n\n### Working command\n```bash\nopenclaw browser --browser-profile chrome-relay screenshot\nopenclaw browser --browser-profile chrome-relay navigate <url>\n```\n\n### Current config state (working)\n- `defaultProfile`: REMOVED (key fix)\n- `profiles.openclaw`: port 18800 (WSL Chrome, not used)\n- `relayBindHost`: 0.0.0.0 (allows external connections)\n\n### Backup files\n- ~/TinyBackUp/20260319/openclaw.json.154346 — current working config\n- ~/TinyBackUp/20260319/MEMORY.md.154348 — current memory\n\n## Workspace Resource Map (2026-03-23)\n\n\n[75 more lines in file. Use offset=246 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774272212740}}
